ori-def.2: a lady's fillet for the hair
ori-def.6: travelling apparatus: from Ma-bissas, to make ready
ori-def.8: rust; ach o dippa, the rust of iron; ach o barrieg, the rustof copper; ach, and inach, ino-ach-en, injured by rust
ori-def.12: not yet; as acho aban ja ing, rummies mammabas, I do not yet know it, by and bye I shall know it; witten also achai, and achipa
ori-def.14: a certain small bird, less than a sparrow; variegated with a long tail; from whose cry future good or bad fortune may be presumed: if it cries out twice, or four times, it betokens misfortune; but if once, or thrice, or five times, then good success; if anything above this, it initiates a still greater blessing, according to the number of cries.
ori-def.15: a part or share; from mada, to divide
ori-def.16: a coral chain; it may be of poor materials, but much prized by the natives
ori-def.18: paddy; used for that production in its various stages. Numatojóarien, as it just shoots forth. Minochûrgaro, as it puts forth a broad leaf. Tummaabbi-alallabach, as it has two leaflets on the side, and one on the top; a resemblance being supposed to lallabach, a green leek.  Madocka jû adda, as it is now, 1+1/2  or 2 spans high: gûmmasor, túmmûbaron summatis, when it has attained its full length. Tummedinnid, when the grain begins to form. Pûikon ja adda, when the grain is perfect and hangs bent down. Tummaberook ja adda, when the grain is half  ripe and nearly scorched.
ori-def.19: a piece; adda o ariem, a piece of a lemon: from paddat, to cut or break.
ori-def.22: all kinds of missile weapons, as javelins, pikes: &c. from magga, to cast
ori-def.23: seems to mean, it is done, when any end is reached
ori-def.24: seems that, here, but not far off; ai-i, ai-ies, ai-inies, ailo, ailo-ies, and ailemons, the same
ori-def.26: there, but not far off. Aicho, aichoies, soo aicho echies, yonder. Pait o ta, so-o roman kallach, gannumma, there, beyond, yonder. Paia innai maro maicho, and mai-hoies, it is so, there it is.
ori-def.27: beyond, outside, far out of sight
ori-def.29: the following; a-i-or natta, the next; ajor narroa, &c. A-i-or a mato, next after the large one, that is smaller.
ori-def.31: is frequently used in different senses; if we meet with this expression alone, it seems to intimate the doing away with anything, as when anything is burnt: aissen o chau, it is burnt in the fire; aissen o cho, some one has taken it away.
ori-def.34: a word of excuse, when you unknowingly run against any one; as pray excuse me.
ori-def.35: a form of complaint, when any thing falls down
ori-def.36: a hunting net, placed in the field, to catch beasts; from pakobor, to catch in a net
ori-def.37: show finery, ornament; from Malla or Pallo, to set one's self off.
ori-def.39: called in the south, kalladóch, a sort of red beans, which the natives wear round their necks, instead of coral beads; they are very posonous.
ori-def.41: kindness; from ma-allal, to be kind
ori-def.42: all kinds of projeciles or missle weapons; from Malam, to fight with missle weapons.
ori-def.43: a basket , also a werd used in addressing children
ori-def.44: added to a word betokens doing or suffering; it also refers to the future. Súmmada, allecho na-amai, which is the same as sunmada na-a mamai, tomorrow  I will come
ori-def.45: fire-wood; as marach o ûllolo, go and get some fire-wood.
ori-def.47: a prohibitory expression, as ûmi a mochan, bring no food; ûmi a maú a dat-ai, do not pick it.
ori-def.48: the north. Matamis-mi-ma, northward. Patamis, transit.
ori-def.51: before  this. ago; ani rúmmies, in former days; ani zchieta rummies, ten days ago; aninaspaat ai das, four months ago; ani tarnacho a baas, nine years ago: animúnma, and anibanno, when did it happen? People say in the evening; ani mûrpesa, yesterday, or last evening: ani naassa, a little while ago; anissima, this morning early: annach, certainly, verily: ansia, yesterday: ansiûtta, the day before yesterday: ani bi-ini, and anbini, last night: anibaas, last year: ani mossa, like anibaas, like anibaas: animilip, a long time ago: aniaicho, d'cicin ani, a very long since.

ori-def.153: horns; figuratively, a buck; otherwise, o basan.

ori-def.213: everything that projects above another. Maborroch mi, ma, verb.

ori-def.223: a swelling under the ball of the foot.

almost: chadsia madich, almost sick: chadsja macha, almost dead: chadsja man ja ina, I have nearly had enough: as olachal adsia, olochaladsja, olamamoeda, all these

enough, as achoa, and ami, a
a word whereby men signify that they desire no more: it differs from kamicho, and o chal.

chacho-o, I. 
chachon, chinûcho, inochach-on, to polish.

chadden, chinad, inochadden,

chi, cha, chaddippa, 
to cut off any thing close to the ground.

chagchillan, chimagchillan, inochagchillan,

ma-achûchachil, a good runner that can overtake others.

chinummai, chachûmmai, g.
chai-a, *I. cha-in, chinai, inochaittin,

chi, cha, challakka, chilakken, chimallak, inochallakken,

chi, cho, chaisa, pass.
chaisas, a putting off. Pachais, transit.

challama, any thing that lies over another, as clothes, &c.

chi, cha, chalgalla, the barking of dogs.

Chachalgal, gebas nom. ma-achchalgal, to bark.

chi, cha, *channagha, channaghan, chinannaghan, 
inochannaghan, 
to make a notch in an arrow in order to fix it on the string.

chinmumaniod, chachummanied, g. *channida,
the screaming, howling, and crying, whether of children

inochattan, to pay a ransom for a murderer: according to

a stubborn, troublesome person.

chinummeocheo, chachúmmeocheo, cheoche-óa, cheocheoon,

chi. cha, charaddoa, charaddoon, chinaradodo, inocharadodoon,
the same as rûmmarro, to encircle. Pacharûdodo, transit.

ant thing; to guard the window with a bamboo: chacharapo, from

ori-def.263: chi, cha, charillochilloa, the writhing of snakes.

inicharop, inocharoppan, to gather amd take up with the hands,

from chacharop, such scraping together; ma-achacharop,
to scrape anything.

chinûmmaschas, chachûmmaschas, g. chaschàssa, I.

ori-def.269:
chi, cha. chattûdda, chattaddan, chinattaddan. *inocha_taddan,
to shadow, to over shadow. Pachattad, transit. nom. chattad.
a shadowing. Chatta dan aijan, a shadowy place, 
a covering for the sun.
ori-def.270:
chinûmmaû, chachûmmaû, g: chau-u, I. chaûan, *chiuaû, *inochaúnan,
to sweep. Pachaû, transit. Chachaû; a besom: ma-achachaû, a sweeper:
chochûmmaû, the man sweeps. Chauan ja don, the house is swept.
ori-def.271:
chi, cha, cheda, chedûan, chienda, inochedûan, early in the season:
as Padaat, Pachdo', transit. nom. chachda, early time.
ori-def.272: chinumme, chachumme, g. chía, to do that which is suitable.
ori-def.273:
chinummeriel, chachûmmeriel, to saw; cherila, cherilen, inocherilled.
Pacheriel, pi, pa, ipûcherilla. a saw.
ori-def.274:
chinûmmero, chachûmmero, g: chera, I. cheroan, chínero, inocheroon,
to make straight. As Pachero, transit. chûmmero-noties, chache-ro, nom.
sub. a making straight; also that by which any thing is made straight.
ori-def.275:
chinûmmi, chachûmmi, g. chia, I. chien, chini, inochieu, to bore a hole
with a bodkin. Chaegi, a bore.
ori-def.276:
chinûmmibar, chûchûmmibar, g. chibarra. I. chibarren, chinibar, 
mochibarreo, to stir about food in the cooking, that it may not be burned.
Also to row: Pachibar, chibûrren; inochan a bali, the food is well stirred;
the boat is rowed. Chachibar, a stiring about: chachibar o abak, the rowing
of a boat; ma-acha, chibar, a boatman, a rower.
ori-def.277:
chinummichi, chachûmmichi, g: ichichia, I: ichicha, inichicha, inochichi,
to pour in, to cast in, as in a pot, can, or bottle, &c. to pour out.
Pachichi, transit. from chumma. Otoichichi, the beer, wine, or water is
poured out. Chûmmichi, oto o bonoaad_ maibas tûmmis, chachichi,
a pouring out, or pouring in; chûche, chi oto, chamma, ma-achachichi,
a cup bearer.
ori-def.278:
chi, cha, chieddan, chidden, chinied, inochiëdden, to fence in, to inclose;
Porchied. transit. Chached, a fence; ma-achachied, to inclose.
ori-def.279:
chinummieg, chachummieg, g. chiegcha, I: chiegchegen, chiniegch,
inochiegchen, to roast; as summoso pachieg, chiegchen tsi biman,
the fish or flesh is fried. Chachieg, a roasting, or frying; maachachien, a fry.
ori-def.280:
chinûmmillip, chachûmmillip, g: chilippa, I. chilippen, chinilip, inochinilippen,
to cut with shears. Chummillip, naupoot, to cut linen; naupoot chilippen, the
linen is cut up. Chachilip, scissars; ma-achachilip, one who cuts with
scissars.
ori-def.281:
chinûmmimit, chachummimit, g: chimta, I. chimten, chinimit, inochimten,
to secure, to take care of, to protect, to rule, to take charge of. Pachimit,
transit. Ma-achachimt, a superintendent, a ruler. Chachimit, a rule.
Pachimit, to take care of. Pachimit o assaban, a garrison to take care of
a town.
ori-def.283:
chinummio, chachummio, chiou, chioan, chinio, inochioan, chummio, no-man,
michan patite, to do any thing when we do not want any one else near.
Chûmmio no cho, to get away the people: cho chioan, the people are gone.
ori-def.284:
chinûmmior, chachûmmior. to sport forth as trees.
Pachoir, transit. Gitas pûchior o barros, the rain makes the tress bud.
Chioor, a bud.
ori-def.285:
chinummischis, chachummischis, g: chischissa, l: chischissea, chinischis, 
inochischissen, to produce fire by the rubbing of two bamboos together.
Pûchischis, transitiv. Chûmmischis o chau: to produce fire.
ori-def.286:
chinûmmio, chachummo, *choachoon, chino, ino-choon; Pacho, transit.
to lace any thing with a string of rattan. Tairies choón o sarries chacho,
a birding together: chachono tairies,  a stringing of corals.
ori-def.287:
chinûmmoa, chachummonao, g. choa, I. choan, chinoa, inocho-an, 
to lace together. Pachoa, transit. Chachoa. a lacing together. 
*Chummoagagir, to lace the nets together, to fasten.
ori-def.288:
chinummine, chachummime, chemea, cheme-in, chineme, ino-cheme-in,
to press out pus from a *boil. Pûchemc, pinacheme, pûpûcheme, 
ipa-chemea, ipacheme. inipacheme, ino-ipacheme, to do as above. 
Chûmmime o soo, to press out a wound.
 Chemeis soa, the wound is pressed out. Cheme, pus.
ori-def.289:
chinumminoch, chachumminoch, chiuoch-a, chinoch-en, chininoch,
inochinochen, that which is disapproved of in anger, or cast away in contempt
Pachinoch, po, pa, ipachinocha, &c. to do as above. It betokens also to throw
away any thing in anger and break it into pieces.
ori-def.290:
chi, cha, chirra, chirron, chinir, inochirran, to hover as birds when they keep
their wings still. Pachier, to do as above. It is used also of trees or grass,
when they gently wave their heads.
ori-def.291:
chirrlchen, chinirrich, inochirrichen, to draw a tight line. Pachirrich, pi, pa,
ipachirricha, ipachirrich, inipachirrich, ino-ipachirrich, to do as above.
Chûmmirrich, as kûmmirrich, chachirrich, a right line.
ori-def.293:
chinummomach, cha-chummomach, chomûcha, chomachen, chinomach,
inccho-machen, to rule. Chummomach o sassi, to salt. Fachomach, pipapa
chomach, ipachomach-a, ipachomach, inipachomach, ino-ipa chomach, to do
as above. Chummomach o abo, to plaster with lime.
ori-def.294: chi, cha, to root, to poke.
ori-def.295:
chinummo-acho-ar, chachummo-acho-ar, g: cho-acho-arra, I: cho-acho-arren, 
chino-acho-ar, inocho-acho-arren, to mix one thing with another; to stir up from
the bottom, as chummibar. Pacho acho-ar, transit.
ori-def.296:
chinummobbechob, chachûmmobbechob, g: chobbechobba, I: chobbechobben,
chinobbechob, ino-chobbechobben, to tuck up, to strip up, as the sleeves of a coat.
Also to stir up to diligence in work. Pachobechoob, transit: chachobechoob, nomen.
Chummobechoob o tummaap, to stir up. Cho, chobechoben, chûmmobechoob, riba,
lili, o liba, the clothes or sleeves stripped up.
ori-def.297:
chinûmmobon, chachûmmobon, g. echoboma, I. ichobon, inichobon, ino-chiobon, 
to put into the sheath, the sheath. Chobonnan, chinobonnan, inochobonnan. 
Pachobon, transit. Chobon, nomen. a sheath.
ori-def.298:
chinummod, chachûmmod, g: chodda, I: chodden, chinod, inochodden, to commit 
adultery, to seek an improper connection: or the improper connection itself.
Sai sini, sù chummod ina, mirab palro achachoa, sjiem, ____ is a woman come to
ask me to ______ her son go free. Pachod, transit. Chachod, whoredom, adultery.
Ma-achachad, a whoremonger, an adultery.
ori-def.299:
chinummollichol, chachûmmollichol, g: chollicholla, I: chollichollen, chinollichol,
inochollichollen, to put out, to put away. Pachollichol, transit. Chachollichol, nomen.
ori-def.300:
chi, cha, chollietta, chollietten, inocholliën, inocholliëtten, 
the same as hûmmahimmotto; chachollien, nom. chûmmollicholp riba, to undress.
Chûmmollichol o bazigh, villen.
ori-def.301:
chinûmmollok, chachummollok, g: chollokka, I: chollokkan, chinollokkan, 
inochollokkan, to change things of the same sot one with another, whether openly
or in secret. Pachollok, transit. Chachollok, to exchange, barter, chachollok o arribil.
ori-def.302:
chi, cha, chinagha, chonaghen, chinonagh, ino-chonûghen, as lummalla.
Pachonagh, as lalala. Ma-achàchonag, als ma-alalala.
ori-def.303:
chinûmmoschos, chachummoschos, g: choschossa, I: choschossen, 
chinoschas inochoschossen, anything badly, or raggedly cut.
ori-def.304: chi, cha, chonchonna, plough. Chachonchon, a ploughing.
ori-def.305:
chinummo-o, chachûmmo-o, to spring out of the ground. Pacho-o, pi, pa, ipachooa,
ipacho-o, inipacho-o ino-ipacho-o, to arise, to spring up. Cho-o, a sprout.
ori-def.306:
chinummomochomo, chachummomochómo, chomochómoa, chomochomoon,
chinomochomoon, inochomochomoon, to rub anything gently with the palm of the 
hand. Pachomochomo, to rub with the hand the place that itches.
ori-def.307:
chi, cha, choschosse, pass. choschossen. chinoschos, inochoschossen, 
idem tùmmachos. Pachoschos, transit.
ori-def.308:
chinummoté, chachummote, choten, chote, chinoté, inochoten, to punish; as tummea,
and pachote; chachoté, punishment. Ma-achachote, punishing.
ori-def.310:
chinumpe, chachumpe, g: chuppea, I: chuppein, chinuppe, ino-chuppein, bamboos make
flat like boards. Pachuppe, transit.
ori-def.311:
chinumpir, chachumpir, chuppirra, chuppirren, chienpier, ino-chûppirren, to break through;
as men say, chunopir o arros, o to, o azijes, to push through the grass, the water, 
the enemy, &c. Pachûppir, pinachuppir, papachuppir, ipachûppirra, to do as above.
Chachuppir, a breaking through; chachuppir o to, the braking through of water.
ori-def.312: chinumpod, chachumpod, to spring out of the ground, as water.
ori-def.313: chi, cha, the shooting forth of many sprouts from the root.
ori-def.314:
chinumsan, chachûmsan, the in- and expiration of the breath. It differes from paucher,
which means to blow strongly; chachsas, nom. the breath.
ori-def.315: a flttened piece of bamboo. From chumpé.
ori-def.317: a well, a fountain. From chumpod.
ori-def.318: an aflix, as macha-da, dead, dry; ma-bada, wize, to know.
ori-def.319: a straw; after the seed is threshed out.
ori-def.322:
over, done: ka dagh ja zichil, the sorrow is over: ka dagh ja mapich, the fight is done:
ka dagh ja oba, the drowsiness is past.
ori-def.323:
the shadow or darkness which the clouds make on the ground, when they obscure the sun;
for otherwise the shdow of a tree is called eonno. Verbum, midach-um. Paidach-um, transit.
ori-def.325:
cannot well be trasnlated(???): dakrap ja mampa, there sits the bird: innai bonna da mai
dakrap, I am come out of the field, and here I sit.
ori-def.328: the bank of a river; written dûtta: lallûbbo, lobbokas, the sea shore.
ori-def.329: a double flute on which people plat with their nostrils.
ori-def.332: the blade of a sword or knife, to which the handle is fixed.
ori-def.335:
any evil that we deserve, or have brought on ourselves; thus they say, jo a deeg, or dillij, it
is well arranged, you have your deserts.
ori-def.337:
indema, indea, inde, de, are all of one meaning, as pana dema, pana de, where are you going?
N. B. Nûmma is sometimes used for dema, as mosse-numma, for mosse-dema.
ori-def.340: all sorts of yound birds, just hatched and not yet fledged.
ori-def.341:
zinemmo, dadimmo, g. doa, I: doon, zinoon, inodoon, to pull upwards, to hoist, as people draw
water out of a well. Pado, transit. Dummono dale, to. draw up a pitcher: dale kadoon, means also
to take a pot off the fire.
ori-def.343: a jungle full of reeds and rushes, such as grow on the banks of rivers and morasses.
ori-def.344:
manner, custom: kadogh, constume, ceremonies: kadóg o assaban, kadog o anibaas, maibas
madarrain.
ori-def.346: to beat: ka doogh ja na öeno, my head beats; as tummok. Doogh has no tenses.
ori-def.348:
zinûmmaraû, tadûmmaraû, g. daraû-a, I. daraûn, zenaraû,inodaraun, to bend half round, 
to make a semi-circle. Padaraû, transit. modaraû, semi-circular: neutr. daddaraû, a semi-circle.
ori-def.349: dsi, tad: dadacha; dadachen, &c. to climb. Padadach, transit.
ori-def.350: to make into a circle; imp: daraûdaûn.
ori-def.351:
the same; imp. taribodiboa, modaaraûdaû, modaribodibo, like a circle; daddaraûdaû, 
daddaribodibo, a circle.
ori-def.352:
zinummaries, tadummarries, g: darriesa, I: idarries, inidarris, inoidarries, darriessan, inidarries, 
darriessan, to lock up, or fasten. Padarries, transit. chachap idarries, don darriessan: dandarries,
a lock.
ori-def.353:
zinummarrogigodoggo, tadûmmarogodoggo, g. darroggodoggo-a, to walk double, as old people
or those who are deformed do, to spy out anything. Maibas kakkollen. pikkon sies: 
daddarroggodoggo, nom. as ababad  pikkon, a hunch back.
ori-def.354:
to do anything in the place of another, or to succeed to one, dsi, tadum: imp. daua: nomen dau,
instead of another. Maanaû, one who comes in the place of another to do or suffer anything for them.
ori-def.355:
zinûmmaûko. tadúmmaûko, g. daûkóa, to lift up the head high, either because people can see with
difficulty, as mitébabo baak, or that they do it, inomaso kummeriel, to pay the more attention.
ori-def.356: zinûmmo-an, inodùmmoan, to sweat. Dûmmoan ja ina, I sweat. Dûmmo, sweat.
ori-def.357:
zinûmmaûkàûka, tadûmmaûkaûka, g: daûkaûka-a, is said of drunkards who go staggering about the
streets.
ori-def.358:
zinûmméódeo, tadûmmeódeo, long and trailing, as a long garment, a long tail, long hair, &c.
Dûmeódeo, arriba, taa, the gown trails, the hair hangs long.
ori-def.359:
zinûmmeogh, tadûmmeogh, g: déogcha, I. deógchen, zineogh, inodeogchen, to brush, or rub off.
Dûmmeógo o sesnab, to brush down with a brush: dûmmeog o rima. to rub down with the band. 
Padeoch, transit. taddeoch, nomen. subst. Dûmmeogh o magcha, to rub the eyes: dûmmeogh o
nok, to blow the nose.
ori-def.360:
zinumbor, tadûmbor, doborra, doborren, zinobor, inodoborren, padabor, transit. to take away 
against one's will: as maûpis, poas: ka sai dumbor na mochan ja mado, the dog has taken away my
food; to constrain another to do any thing, either willingly or not; to hold fast, and not to left go:
as madabdab, elli pittol o meacha, dombor o maùmali o meroos. Dûmbor o arribil, dûmbor o cho,
to force any one, to take any thing away: nomen. subst. daddobor, daddobor o ballag, depriving
another of his goods. Ma addobor, an oppressor, a tyrant.
ori-def.362:
dsi: tad. dach-alla, dachûllen, zinach-al, ino-dach-allen, to turn over the over the ground with a
spade or hoe. Padach-al, daddach-al, a digging up, also a hoe. Ma ataddach-al, a digger.
ori-def.363:
zinummaggo, tadûmmaggo, imp. daggo-a, not to stand upright, to over hang; is generally said of men,
houses, trees, &c. padaggo, transit. Dummaggo, o moddan asjoddon, the gable or wall hangs over.
Tadaggo, nomen. subst.
ori-def.364: dsi, tad, see tûmmakkal, to bind. Daddakkal, a ribbon, a bandage.
ori-def.365: dsi: tadum: dalappa, to thatch a house with grass. that is when a portion of the old thatch remains.
ori-def.366:
h, zinûmmalimogh, tadûmmalimogh, is said of the sky, when it appears hazy as in a drizzling shower.
Dûmmalimogh o busûm.
ori-def.367:
zi, tad, dalizia, dalizian, zinalizau, inodalizian, to dance. Padalizi, transit. daddalizi, a dance. 
Maadaddalizi, a dancer.
ori-def.368: zinûmmap, tadûmmàp, dappa, dappen, zinap, inodappen, as chûmmachil.
ori-def.369:
zinùmmarrab, tadûmmarrab, g: darrabba, I: darraban, zinarraban, ino darranban, to line, or to fix the
lining in a garment. Also to put one garment over another. Also to live in aultery. Padarrab, transit.
ori-def.370: the plural of the preceding. Padarrab, transitiv. Hence dardarab, lining.
ori-def.371:
zinummalpal, tadûmmapal, g. dapûlla, I. dapallan: dapallan baron, baro asiel, rima oenoete idapal,
idapal, inidapal, inoidapal, zinapallan, inodapallan, to run against any thing, as kadoog; padapal, transit.
daddapal, apush, a clash: daddapal o asiel.
ori-def.372:
zinúmmarram, tadûmmarram, g: darrama, to practice one's self in any thing, is used both for teacher
and learner. Passi. darramen, dsimarran, inodarranmmen, dummarran, tûmmoch o bido, 
to practice one's self in reading; is verbum act: dûmmarram o sisjien o tûmmoch o bido, the children
exercise themselves in reading. Madarram, as maba. Padarram, dûminarram, acho maba. Dûmmarram
meach ta Deos, to practice one's self, or to learn to pray. Daddaram, nom. exercise. Daram, to exercise
one's self, nom. exercise. Taddaram, one who is practised. Daddarran o aiacha,a meeting for prayer. 
Ma adaddarram, one who exercises himself or another.
ori-def.374:
dsi, tad, imp. dasdissen, to sit, to squat down, as when men sit on their heels. Padasdis, transit. nom.
daddasdis.
ori-def.375: zinûminittin, tadûmmittin, g. dittina, to stop half way, not to go out.
ori-def.376:
dsi, tad, doassa, doassen, dsinoas, inodoassen, is said of liquor when it is too fresh, that people may
make it more sour or more sweet. Padoas, transit. daddoas, dummoas machoch, put some more acid in
it: daddoas. make it sweeter.
ori-def.377:
tsi, ta, dobdobba, dobdobben, dsinobdob, ma dobdobben, to wake up any one. Padobdob, transit.
Sadobdob, nom. Ma addobdob, one who wakes up another.
ori-def.378:
zinûmmochol, tadûmmochol, docholla, dochollen, zinochol, ino dochollen, to strike with the fist on the
breast. dadochol, nom.
ori-def.379: dsi, tad, didossa, pass. dosdossen, &c. ja to, to tap, or let off liquor. Padodos, transit
ori-def.380:
zinûmmoelallis, tadûmmoelallis, g: doelalissa, I: doelalissen, zinoelallis, inodoelallissen, to hit people 
slightly, without hurting them.
ori-def.381: zi, ta, g: doragcha, I: to flay, chûmmorach, idem.
ori-def.382:
zinûmmorat, tadûmmorat, g. doratta, I. doratten, zinorat, inodoratten, to relieve. Chûmmorat, idem.
Padorat, transit. dadorat, nom.
ori-def.383: zinûmmori, tadûmmori, g: dorria, to deny, to speak against.
ori-def.384:
(the last o sounded short) zinummoro, tadûmmoro, g: dorro, to go in. Contract, dorro, dsinorro, &c. 
daddoro, nom.
ori-def.385: dsi, tad, dosdossa, passi. dosdossen, &c.  ja ta, to trail one feet. Padosdos, transit.
ori-def.386: zi, ta, dûppûlla, dûppûllen, dsinûmpûl. inodûppûllen, to set on fire. Paduppul, transit.
ori-def.387: nom. arson. Ma adûddûpûl, one who sets on fire..
ori-def.390: anything to drink out from. From micham, to drink.
ori-def.392:
to deny, as with us, no: but it is only used in connection with another word: as elli mabisse oaseis.
your heart is not true. Elli pa, is so common that nothing can exceed it. and yet i do not know that is 
the real meaning of it (then what about me?????). It seems to signify that some thing is not in 
existence, as elli pa ja adda de assaban o amicien: or that some thing is not in one possession; as ellipa
ja oa bido ina-ai, the first of which I cannot otherwise understand than that "there is no rice in the village
on the north:" and the other "I have not got your book." See in alli.
ori-def.397:
a point. From Maggaat. Gûmmaat, gi: ga: gata: gatan: ginaat, to sharpen, to bring any thing to a point. 
to carve. Ginaat, cut. Gagaat, a sharpening. Ma-agagaat, to sharpen. Ma-aggaat, a sharpener.
ori-def.399: gi, ga, gea, to belch, to eructate. Pagea, transit. nom: gagea, a belching.
ori-def.400: water mixed with herbs, with which the women wash the houses.
ori-def.402: a word that is used when any thing tears.
ori-def.404: gi, ga, imp. gomila, pass. gomilan, &c. to blow out the gills. Pagomil, transit. gagomil, nom.
ori-def.405: a dove. Don o gorrogot, dove cot.
ori-def.406: gi, ga, gabgabba, the cutting of paddy, or millet. Rûmmabies, idem. Pagabgab, transit.
ori-def.407:
gi, ga, gachhacha, pass, gachhachen, &c. Pagachhach, transit. to hoe away the ground from a house
in a sloping direction. Gagachhach, nom.
ori-def.408: gi, ga, gagidsia, to tickle active. pagagiesi, transit. Gagidsi, a tickling. Maagagidsi, a tickler.
ori-def.409: gi, ga, gagria, the same as gummagissi.
ori-def.410:
gi, ga, ga-iecha, pass. ga iechan , gina-iech, ino-ga-iechen, to bear, to endure: act. paga-iech, transit.
gagariech, a lengthening, act. Ma-agagaiech, to lengthen, to delay.
ori-def.411:
gi, ga, gatacha, gatachen, ginatach, inogatachen, pagatach, transit. gatach, nom. to split up large pieces
of wood; but when bamboos are spoken of, pilla is used. It is also used in the cutting up of pumpkins,
melons, plantains, &c.
ori-def.412: gi, ga, geocha, to thatch house.
ori-def.413:
(let the (e) be scarcely heard) gi, ga, gesarra, gesarran, the same as gummiddiggit: gesar, just as if
people said gsar, a gripe, a handfull.
ori-def.414:
gi, ga, giacho, giachen, giniach, ino-giachen, to fence, or secure; people say also, giûchen ja sabba,
as if the river were suddenly swollen and therefore a fence was made. 
Pagiach, transit. nom. gigiach, a fence.
ori-def.415:
gi, ga, giacha, giachen, giniach, inogiachen, to stretch out the arms, as lazy people do; as paggeas,
merely, to reach out the arm, leg, finger, &c. neutr. magiach.
ori-def.416:
gi, ga, giddiggitta, giddiggitten, ginigddiggit, ino-giddiggitten, to close the hand. Also to grasp any thing
fast. nom. gagiddiggit, a fist.
ori-def.417: gi, ga, gnabba, gnabben, ginab, ino-gnabben, to begin. As ptat, and pto. Gagnab, nom. as paptat.
ori-def.419: gi, ga, gocha, gochen, ginoch, ino-goch, pagoch, transit. Gagoch, nom: to bind together.
ori-def.421:
gi, ga, gomacha, gomachen, 
ginummach, inogomachen, 
to rub out any thing that is drawn or written.
Pagomach, transit. gûgomach, nom.
ori-def.422: a bambo pole to carry with.
ori-def.423:
a denial, used only in forbidding, 
as hai magiepe, make no noise.
ori-def.424:
all kinds of fat man or beast; written Ema.
Hemo tillij, a badger's fat; written Emotillij.
ori-def.427:
a particle denoting interrogation, 
ja madûrram jonoe ta Deos o Baûsie, do you know the God of the Dutch?
ori-def.428: why do you give me that.
ori-def.430:
a snake.
*ibien ota, small red snake, makaka.
ibien o aras, korrokorroan, a spotted snake.
ibien abo, a large bellied snake, matoatsi.
ibien baron or isaijs, a snake hard in the back, mattilo, maraas asieg
ibien marali, a snake with large eyes, matoto macha.
ibien e ribij, snakes that creep quietly along the ground, and remain in the granaries.
*ibien o atei, a snake that blows its cheeks up: mato a ri.
*ibien o boesûm korrokorron maûsi, snakes spotted with black and white.
*ibien tagotago de abas, korrokorroan mekach maûsi, mali kach ja ki-or, snakes found in the sea. spotted green and white with broad tails.
ori-def.431: a hook, like a parrot's bill.
ori-def.434: a shell, also a spoon; from midod, to lade out.
ori-def.435: a fan, a species of mouse.
ori-def.436:
a mulberry. Baron o iel-iel, the mulberry tree. 
Bo' o iel-iel, the fruit.
ori-def.439:
inimigh-igh, amigh-igh, g: igh-igha: l: igh-ighen, migh-igh, inoigh-ighen,
to gnaw, to nibble. Imighigh o ûso, to bite the nails.
ori-def.441: all kinds of herbs that spring out of the ground; weeds.
ori-def.442:
I, mine, it serves also to put out every kind of cause, (except the immediate;)
Ina o elli arioon, pattas o bido, ina papagcha jo, because yo do not write well, I will flog you
ori-def.443: because, therefore; perhaps from innaû and innaû numma.
ori-def.444:
asks every kind of cause, except the immediate. 
Inaûmmima jo pagcha ina, why do you strike me.
ori-def.445:
who, what, in what place?
indea, the same: also edea.
ori-def.447: a line drawn. From kummir rich, passivum praet.
ori-def.448: from a place; as pana, to a place.
ori-def.449:
whence, from what place.
ka mai jana, innai takais; people also say innai dema
jo mabaddai, whence know you that?
ori-def.451:
in a place: inni Taiwan, in Taiwan. 
inni don, in the house.
ori-def.452:
betokens the immediate cause.
ino airien o arrar, in order to make a railing.
ori-def.453: why, where for? this asks after the immediate cause.
ori-def.459:
i, inisa, a-isa, imp. passi, isasan, inisa, inoisasan, to imitate.
Paisasa, transit. isas, nom. a likeness.
ori-def.460:
inisabhesab, ino-isabbesab, struck down.
lsabbesab ita, beat down to the ground; as millet or rice in the field.
ori-def.462: a sack made of bulrushes, a purse.
ori-def.468: in order that, perhaps not, asdopa.
ori-def.469:
the left. Ma kairi, verbum. 
Kair‘i a rima, left hand. Kairi a tea, the left arm.
Kairi o magcha, the left eye.
ori-def.473:
the right. Kallamas a rima, atea, o, macha, the right hand, arm, or eye.
Verbum Makallamas.
ori-def.475: a line, or long stripe; see chachirrich, in Ch.
ori-def.479:
kaminachaggi, kamamachaggi, to know certainly.
Kamachaggi o maba, idem.
 Merien o chagchi, to do anything to purpose.
ori-def.481:
makes the superlative degree,
as kûmmasies a mata, mario, the greatest, best.
ori-def.485: compounded with nouns, signify the same as mau, when compounded with nouns or verbs.
ori-def.487:
kinarri-apiech, ka karrì-apiech, karrì-sapiecha,
to fight with each other: id mau-apiech.
ori-def.488:
karri-atita, to speak together or to converse.
idem karrì-ala, and mau-ala, to tell each other.
ori-def.489:
to cast lots. In the change of tenses karri, is inflected and not babisso.
Ki, ka karri, babissoa, dito maûbabisso.
ori-def.490: karrisasopatta, to stand over against each other.
ori-def.493:
a piece of anything. 
Differs from bitil: and is said of fish or flesh.
Kattach o arierfi, o bilpìl, o abì, o baaf, written gatach, see gûmmatach.
ori-def.494:
to throw before each other.
Kinartattis hakartattis,im. karraìtìsa.
ori-def.495: kariau, aûnisa, belonging to each other.
ori-def.496: to pay visits backwards and forwards: id. mautattubboel.
ori-def.497: karri auana, to eat together, to give food to each other.
ori-def.498:
aan a tammas, or harri or man, aan, o rarozì, is the manner of the natives. when they will make a treaty
of peace with each other; they pluck a thread out of each other's clothes and eat it up; which is a sign
of peace: this contract is made midway between their villages.
ori-def.500: a reap hook, or scythe. From Kûmmaûr.
ori-def.509: a flute, blown through the nose.
ori-def.510: a word of strong denial, as no, by no means. Sometimes also Koa, Ko-ai.
ori-def.511: few, small of itself; smaller than many is ma-jed. Written kotsi.
ori-def.517: kole a kis, a yellow finch.
ori-def.522:
kinumbor, kakumbor, g. koborra, I koborren. Kinebor, ino-koborren,
to draw water, to lade.
ori-def.523: kaarchabba, to break wind: ka kaarchab,, foul wind.
ori-def.524:
ki, ka, k‚abacba, kabachen, kina bach, inokabachen, pakabach, trans. nom. ka kabach,
a sort of binding from under the bottom.
ori-def.525:
kinummaat, kakummaat, g. kaatta, l: kaattan, kinaattan, ino’kaattan, to clip, to cut.
written gûmmaat, Kummaat o chaar, to make a pen.
ori-def.526:
kablierra, kaberren, kinabber, ino-kabberren. Pakabber.
Also a kind of binding, as kûmmabach. 
Kakabber, nom. such kind of binding. Ma akakabber, a binder.
ori-def.527:
kinûmmados, kakûmmados, g: kadossa, I: kadossen, kinados, inokadossen,
to take in the arms.
ori-def.528:
kinummaggimo, kakummaggimo, g: kooggimoa, kooggimoon. kinaggimo, ino-kooggimoon,
to bring to confusion. Written gûmaggimo.
ori-def.529:
kaihacha, kaibachen, kinaibach, ino-kaiûachen, to put in a sling.
Pakûibach, to do so. Kakaibach, a sling.
ori-def.530: kinum maizizi, kakūmmaizizi, kaizizia, to do anything softly.
ori-def.532:
kinûmmalossikos, kakummalossikos, kalossikossa, I: kalossikossen, 
kinalossikos, ino-kalossikossen, to uncover, to discover.
ori-def.533:
kalossikotta, kalossikotten, kinalossikot, inokalossikotten, to curl, act. 
pakalossikot, trans.
kakalossikot, nom. a curling, a curl.
ori-def.534:
kinämmai, kakūmmai. g. kaia,
I: kai-in, kinai, ino-kai-in, to carry on the back. Written gummai.
ori-def.535:
kinummallobos, kakūmmallobos, g: kallobossoa, 
I. kallobossen, kinallobos, inokaliobossen, to fold any thing up, as tobacco, money, &c. in paper.
ori-def.536:
kinum mammo, kakummammo, g: kammoa, I: ikanimo, inikammo, inoikammo, 
to fold the arms lazily.
ori-def.537:
kapiera, pas, kapieren, kinapier, ino-kapieren, to hook on.
Pakapier, trans.kakapier, a hooking on.
ori-def.538:
kinummapos, kakūmmapos, g: kapossa, kapossan, & kinapos, kinapossan, 
inokap ossan, to stop up. Kammapos, o kallaman, to close a pot:
kûmmapos, o tarran, to stop up a road.
Kakopos, the stopping of an action.
Ma akakapos, to stop up.
ori-def.539:
kinûmmaram, kakummara,
g: karama, I: karaman, and kinarram,
kinarraman, inokarraman, to rake together.
ori-def.540:
kinämmargar, kakömmargar, kargarra, kargûrran, kinargarran,inogargarran, 
when a house is in danger of being blown down by the wind to fasten it to a pole stuck in the ground. 
Also a vessel lying at anchor. 
Written gûmmargar, gagargar, nom. an anchoring, a cable. Gagargaran aijan, an anchorage. a roadstead.
ori-def.541:
kinämmartúppo, kakūmmartúppo, g: kartúppoa, to dive underwater. 
Kakartúppo, a ducking. Maakartuppo, a diver.
ori-def.542:
kinummarummokummo, kakūmmarummokummo, g.
karummokummoa, I: karūmmokūmmoon, 
kinarummokummoon, ino-karummokammoon, to wrinkle together.
ori-def.543:
to roll. Kiilummarinikini, kinum marrinikini, kakūmmarrinikini,
g. karrinikinia, l: karrinikinien, kinarinikinien, inokarrinikinien,
to make round like a ball, to roll up, activ.
written gåmmarini.
ori-def.544:
impe. kasa, to dream.
Pakasa, transit. kasa, nom. a dream.
Minit o nûa kasa, I saw in my dream.
ori-def.545:
kinûmmaskas, kakûmmaskas, kaskassa, I: kaskassen, kinaskas,
imokaskassen, to scrape. l. gimmasgas, gagasgas.
ori-def.546:
kinummatos, kakūmmatos, g: katossa, I: katossan, kinatossan,
inokatossan, to scrape the beard.
ori-def.547:
kinummattir, kakummattir, g: katirra, I: katirren, kinattir, inokattirren, 
to bind with a long cord, as a fence, and the roofs of houses are bound.
ori-def.548:
kinummatto, kakummatte, g: kattoa, I: kattoon, kinatton, ino-kattoon, to draw, to pull to one's self.
Pakatto, transit. kakatto, nom: people say, kūmmatto no morabbies, the ebb begins to draw.
ori-def.549:
kinûmmaar, kakûmmaar, g: kaura, I: kańron, kinaar, inokańron, to reap, to mow. 
Kaur, nom. a scythe, a reap hook.
ori-def.550:
kinum melokkolo, kakummelokkolo, g: kolokkoloa, I: kolokkoloan, kinolokkoloan, inokolokkoloan, 
to jump over any place.
ori-def.551: kûmga, kinumga, kinûmûch, &c. to close the sleeve of a coat.
ori-def.552:
kerisa, pass: kerises, kirieries, inokerises, to lay the head on one side, to take aim. 
Pakeries, transit. kakeries, nom.
ori-def.553:
kinûmmenis, kakummenis, kinissa, kinissen, kininis, inokinissen,
to appropriate what was common by division, or to tear any thing in two. 
Written gåmmenees.
ori-def.554:
kinûmmeriel, kakûmmeriel, g: kriella, I: kriellan, kiniriellan, ino-kriellan, to listen sharply. 
Kakriel, a listening. Ma-akakriel, a listener.
ori-def.555:
kinûmmeroa, kakûmmeroa, g. keroa, or eroa, I: keroan, or eroan,
kineroa, or ineroa, ino-keroan, or inoercan, to divide in two; 
written gûmmeroa, gageroa, such division.
*The inflections come from peroa, see in P.
ori-def.556: kinummi, kakûmmi, g: kia, l: kian, kinian, inokian, inikkan, to look behind.
ori-def.558:
kinûmmibokibo, kakûmmibokibo, g: kibokiboa,
I: kibokiboon, kinibokibo, ino-kibokiboon, 
to disturb, as by quarrelling. Pakiboki
bo, transit. kakibokibo, nom.
ori-def.559:
kinummikiet, kakummikiet,
g. kiekiedda, I. kikiedden, kinikiet,
inokikiedden, to tear any thing in pieces. Pakikied, trans, kakikied, a rip.
ori-def.560:
kinûmmirigh, kakûmmirigh, g. kierga, 
I: kiergan, kimirgan,inokirgan, to draw a line on paper or wood, 
&c. Kakirmich, a line, a ruler.
ori-def.561:
kinkinna, kinkinnen, kininken, inokinkinnen, 
to click as with small bells. 
Pakinkin, transi. kakinkin, a clinking.
ori-def.562:
kinummio, kakimmio, ki-o-a,
kioon, kineo, inokioon, to but with the head, as goats, oxen, &c.
ori-def.563:
kiolia, kiollen, kiniol, inokollen, to sharpen at the point;
act. pakiol, trans, kakiol. Ma-akakiel, to point.
ori-def.564:
kinûmmir, kakûmmir, g: kirra, I: kirren, kinir, inokirren, 
to fish with a net called kagir, l: gummir, nom: gagir, a net, also fishing.
ori-def.565:
kinummirgir, kakûmmirgir, g: kirgirra, I; kirgirren, kinirgir, inokirgirren, 
to erase, to cancel. See gûmmirgir, nom, gagirgir, an erasion, a cancelling.
ori-def.566:
kirkira, kirkirren, kinirkir, inokikirrren, 
to gnash with the teeth; act, pakirkir, trans, kākirgir, a gnashing. Mla-akakirkir, to gnash.
ori-def.567:
kinummirragh, kakummirragh, g; kirragcha, I:kirragch en, kirrirragch, inokirragchen, 
to tear to pieces.
ori-def.569:
kintiminissikissiel kakûmmissikissiel, g: kissikissilla
slowly, to do anything quietly, whether walking, eating, working, &c.
ori-def.570:
kissokissoa, kissokosoon, inokissokissoon, to move up and down as the tail of an animal.
Mado kūmmissokisso, kior, kissokissot, nom. kakisso, 
is said of the rudder of a ship because it moves backwards and forwards: 
otherwise kakisso, and kakissokisso, the motion itself.
ori-def.571:
kinummitor, kakūmmitor, g: kittorra, I: kittorren, kinitor, inokitorren, 
to plait any thing as a reed, bamboo, &c.
ori-def.572:
kitta, kittan, kinitta, inokittan, to stick the foot out behind.
Pakitta, trans. kakitta, a sticking out.
ori-def.574:
kinummoagh, kakûmmoagh, g: koageha, l: koagchen, kinoagh, inokoagehen, 
to loose, to unbind, to put off, as clothes. It is also used respecting the mind, 
and means to draw in one's courage. 
Paka-ach, pi, pa, ipako-ach-a, &c. to loose. Kûmmoach obre, to unstring a bow.
ori-def.575: to chizel, ki, ka, kakoesach, a chisel.
ori-def.576:
kinummoar, kakûmmoar, g: koarra, I: koarren, 
kino-ar, inoko-arren, to jump over. 
Kakoar, nom. a jump. Maakakoar, to jump.
ori-def.577:
kinummoen, kakummoen, g: koeaa, l: koenen, kinden, inokoen, 
to imprison, to bind. Kakoen, chains.
Ka koen-an, a prison.
ori-def.578:
(written gúmmoch) kinûmmoch, kakûmmogh, to bind, 
g: kogcha, I: kogchen, kinogh, inokogchen,
kummogh, o baan i barron, to tie the
horse to a tree, mom. gagoch, a binding.
ori-def.579:
kinûmmoghkoch, kakûmmoghkoch, g: koghkogeha, I: koghkogchen, 
kinoghkogh, ino-koghkogchen, to wash out.
ori-def.581: kinûmmokot, kakûmmokot, g: kokotta, to lie bent.
ori-def.582:
imp. kolotta, passi. kolotten, kinolot, inokolotten, to loathe.
Pakolot, transi, kakolot, a loathing.
ori-def.585:
kinummomokummo, kakummokûmmoa, kummokummoon,
kinummokûmmoon, inokummokummoon, to rub the hands one against the other.
ori-def.586:
kalachkacha, kalachen, kinalachkach, inokalachkachen. Pakalachkach, transi, 
to cut an animal in two, lengthways; the same as simmarabsab.
ori-def.587:
kintimmono, kakummono, g: konoa, kono-an, kinoloan, inokonoan, 
to bear, to endure. Kakoeno, patience, endurance. Ma-akakoeno,patient.
ori-def.588:
(written gûmmorach,) kinummoragh, kakûmmoragh, g: koragcha, l: koragehen, kinorach, 
intend. nom. gagorach, ma-agagorach, a flayer.
ori-def.589:
kossia, kossian, kinossi, ino-kossen. Pakossi, transi. to disobey. 
act. kakossi, wickedness, disobedience. 
Ma-akakossi, a wicked fellow. 
Pakossi, pi, pa, pakossia, ipakossi-in, inipakossi, inopakossi, to disobey.
ori-def.590:
kinûmpi, kakûmpi, g: kupia, I: kuppien, kinuppi, inokuppien, 
to fold up, to roll up, to pack together in a box.
ori-def.591:
kāmkämma, to lay hold of with all the fingers at once.
Pakuˋmkuˋm, transit. kakûmkûm, nom.
ori-def.592: karra, to open, to unfold the hands only: kûmrar o rimai.
ori-def.593: any thing folded or rolled up, a bundle. Küppio zikakas, a roll of silk, Kûppi o bazigh, a roll of deer skins.
ori-def.594: to crawl: used only of plants and vegetables.
ori-def.595:
kinſmzijr, kakûmzijr, g: kizijrra, I: kizirren, kienzijr, inokizijrren, to nip, to pinch, to pick, to pluck.
People say also, kumzijr o to-i, draw out a splinter. Kakezijr, a nip.
ori-def.596: a pan, a shovel. From Palablab.
ori-def.597: added to ta, means fruitful; joined to baron, it means weak, unable to work. Malabo, the verb.
ori-def.600: pap made from rice and water.
ori-def.601: a fine yellow kind of bark, which people use, and sometimes insert for ornament: as their spears are wound round with red rattan and this bark alternately; the natives also weave the same split very fine, here and there, in their own coats, for ornament.
ori-def.602: a wooden stand, for a light. From Lûmmatagh.
ori-def.604: in, within. Molalitim, in, deep. Paolallum, transi. to make any thing deep, to dig deep.
ori-def.605: the dew; verb. malamo, to bedew; bedewed, or damp.
ori-def.606: an out house, where people keep all kinds of implements, rice, &c.
ori-def.607: an out house; where people keep fish or flesh. Compounded of la-ob, and momas.
ori-def.612: I: linenesoleso, lalenesoleso, lenesolesoa, to shout after the native manner, when the women have concluded a dance or song.
ori-def.613: meaning, interpretation, explanation, li, la, lidoa. Palido, transit. Lido, opinion, meaning.
ori-def.615: linimmichob, lalinimmichob, lichobba, lichobben, linichob, inoli. chobben, to sip.
ori-def.616: li, la, labitta, labitten, linabit, inolabitten, to pinch between two; but to press underneath is summelit; it means also to press against another.
ori-def.617:
linimiod, lalimiod, liodda, liodden, liniod, inoliodden, to wring
once round, to give one turn.
ori-def.618: to lighten, to blink with the eyelids.
ori-def.619: a horse, cow, buffalo, &c. also a servant, a slave. In this last sense the word is used in contempt or in anger.
ori-def.621:
to induce, to incite to evil. Also to haunt.
Palala, to tempt; lalala, a temptation, a ghost.
ori-def.622: to threaten by word or action.
ori-def.625:
linummapilapies, lalûmmapilapies, lapilapiessa, &c. the same
as lûmmapies, lallapilapies.
ori-def.626: to redeem any one from punishment, with money.
ori-def.628: to court, in order to marriage.
ori-def.629: to make burn brighter or clearer. Also to cook or boil anything by a clear fire.
ori-def.633: to glow, also to look angry.
ori-def.634: to totter, to wave; is only used concerning great things, as trees, bamboos
ori-def.639: li, la, logotta, logotten, linogot, inologotten, to vow; as kûmmotkot.
ori-def.640: linûmmokogh, lalûmmokogh, lokogcha, lokogchen, linokogh,inolokogchem, to comb.
ori-def.641: to drive together from all sides; is used of animals, as deer, goats
ori-def.643: to touch, also to trifle, to pass away the time.
ori-def.644: li, la, loomma, passi. loommen, limoon, ino-loommen, seems to mean, to arrange any thing with the acknowledgement of a previous benefit; as làmmoon oatite, oramied. Lalloom, nom. Whenever any one will acknowledge that another has done a service for him, he presents something of what he has acquired to him who procured it for him; which people call Lûmmoon oatite.
ori-def.645: to dig any thing up that was buried, also to bring up old things long since done.
ori-def.646: to twinkle as the fixed stars, to blink.
ori-def.648: a wise man. From maba. Maaijaab, a prophet. From Me-aab.
ori-def.649: a messenger, one who brings tidings.
ori-def.651: fruitful, used generally of plants, animals, or men.
ori-def.655: one who understands cooking, a cook.
ori-def.656: a rewarder of good or evil.
ori-def.663:
kind, benevolent. Dan minaallal mamallaal a-allalla, a-lalal-len,
ina-alallen, ino a-alallen. Al-al, bland.
ori-def.668: one who receives or obtains much.
ori-def.670: unemployed, one who has nothing to do. Also at peace, and undisturbed. g: a-arra.
ori-def.672: one who can sing well in company.
ori-def.675: a sort of fish, like the cod.
ori-def.676:
activ. fond of distinction, shame-faced, to carry oneself modestly towards another whom men honour. Aärichag. Paarich, to honour any one; or to be ashamed before any one,
a-arich, honour, a sense of shame. Ma-aarich, one who honours another, or conducts himself modestly.
ori-def.677:
to catch, as chūmmaü: also a certain mode of fishing with a net, to catch shrimps, called audn.
Aas, a besom, but only such as are made of a certain plant called alsoaas; otherwise it is chachań.
ori-def.680: a fifer, one who plays well on a flute.
ori-def.689: one who has a good memory. From tumpa.
ori-def.693: is used only of the swelling of rivers, not occasioned by the sea ortide: proût, mi, fut, ma; transi. paat; nomen ańt. Mabarrija ačt o sabba, the fresh of the river is very strong, or the stream is strong, Aataijan, the lower part of a river where the running out of the water makes the river greater and stronger.
ori-def.694:
mi, ma, aata, is used for fire wood;
thus they say; maat-eeb, to cut fire wood: trans, paat. pi. pa. ipaata.
ori-def.695:
or ma-atattose, a liar.
From tummosik, from tûmmose.
ori-def.697:
one who speaks openly to the people, a preacher. Ma-atil, a minister.
From pattite, from patil,
ori-def.699: one who is always drowsy: from moba.
ori-def.701: a man or woman, who deserts his or her partner: from moriedda.
ori-def.702: one who sets any thing on fire: from ponnadi or monad.
ori-def.704: one who hides any thing in play.
ori-def.705: minaba, mamaba, to know, to understand; ma bada saan, and zies, an understanding heart, g: maba, seems also to mean, to acknowledge. Maabam charsar ja ta Labba; I know Labba's voice. Pala, transi. Aba, knowledge, science. Ma-aba, a wise man. Intendit. mababa; nom. ababa; abako taposai, omniscient.
ori-def.706: minabaas, mamabaas, abasa, abasem, inabaas, ino-abasen, to creep. Pabaas, trans, to crawl: mabaas morab is very fine weather; malaas mariollo, when the beasts eat grass: when it is foul and rainy weather, and the beasts lie in the grass: nom. abaas, a creeping. Ma-abaas, a creeper.
ori-def.707: minababat, mamababat, ababadda, the gait of men and beasts. Also the moving onwards of any thing that moves locally. Pababat, transit. imp, ababadda, ipababadda. Ababad, a path, a way. Pass. ababadbad, iniden, inababad, inoababadden, ipabapababad, inoiapabad. Ababadden iata, the ground is trodden.
ori-def.708: an old man, one who is getting old.
ori-def.709: mi, ma, abachasa, to be dry; bachas, drought. Pabachas, to dry; activ. imp. ipabachasa, transi. passi. abachassen, activ. obachassen, inobachas, inoabachasen, ipabachas, inipabachas, inoipabachas; people say in short, mabas en palas. Ma-abachas, dryness, drought.
ori-def.710: unbent. From pabach-ich, mi, ma, an unbending, a diversion. Ma-abachchich, one who diverts.
ori-def.713:
mi, ma, abadda, abadden, inabaddan, inoabaddam, the running of the paper in writing. Mabad o barritok. 
Differs from momach. Pabad, trans. abad, a flowing.
ori-def.714: mi, ma, oballa, o ballaan, inoballa, ino-oballaan, to leak; differs from misosso; maballa, when the hole is large and it leaks much, and misosso, when the hole is smaller and it leaks a little. Patiballa, transi.
ori-def.715: to be strong; g; abarra, mi,ma, barra, strength. From Mabarra. Ma-abarra, a strengthener. Pabarra, trans. ipabarra, et activ. imp. abarra. Pass. ipabarra,inipabarra, inoipabarra, acti, abarran, inabarra, inoabarran.
ori-def.716: minabarras, mamabarras, abarrassa, abarrassen, inabaraas, inoabarrasen, to proceed against the enemy, in order to fall on him by surprise. Pabarras, ipabarrassa, imp. trms. nom. abarras, a going forth against the foe. Ma abaras, to go forth.
ori-def.717: ma, abarranna, neutr. not naked; pabarran, act. et trans.
ori-def.718: minabarri, mamabarri, abarria, to blow; pabarri, transi. abarria, ipabarria, imp. to blow. Pas. barrin, binarrin, ino-barrin, trans. ipabarri, inipabar-ri, inoipabarri. Barri, nomen. the wind.
ori-def.720: scented; mi, ma, abassoa, also well tasted, neutr. is said of salmon. which smells or tastes well. Basso, nom. taste or smell. Pabasso, smelling good, to make tasty; imp. act. abassoa, trans. pabassoa, pas. bassoan, binassoan, inobassoan, pabasso, inipabasso, inoipûbasso.
ori-def.721: (the o short) to taste well, activ. mi, ma, imp. achopulla, pass. achopullen, inochopul, inchopullen a taster, one who prepares the food.
ori-def.722: mi, ma, imp. abauasa, a dangling in play after which they shout.
ori-def.723: mi, ma, abazibadda, just, even; mapospos, contrarium, mi, ma, apospossa, papospos, transi. pospos, nom. Pabazibat, pi, pa, ipabazibadda, transi. act. abazibadda, nom. bazibad. Pass. act. bazibadden, binazibad, inobazibadden, trans. ipazibad, inipazibad.
ori-def.724: (the last a is scarcely heard,) minabagh, mamûbagh, abûgcha, abagchen, inabagh, inoabagchen, to embrace, to take in both arms, also to carry on the arms. Pa-bag, transit.
ori-def.725: mi, ma, abidoa, to be black. Pabido, transi. and imp. ipabidoa, ipabido, inipabido, inoipabid, acti.abidoa, passi. abidoan, inabidoan, ino-abidoan.
ori-def.726: mi, ma, abilloa, neutr. cloven. Pabilla, act. and trans. Billa, a cleft. Maabilla, cleft.
ori-def.727: mi, ma, abillaga, pabillaag, to enlarge, nom. billaag, breadth. Maabillaag, trans. en acti. one who enlarges. imp. abillaga, pas. abillagen, inabillaag, inoabillagen, ipabillaga, ipabillaag, inipabillaag, inoipabillaag. Mabillabillaak, flat.
ori-def.728: mi, ma, abinnassa, healthy. Pabinnas, trans. to heal. transi. et act. impr. abinnassa, ipabinnassa, pas. a binnassen, inabinnas, inoabinasa, i. pabinassa, ipabinnas, inipabinas, inopa-binnas. Binnas, health. Abinnas, a healing. Mabinnas, a restorer, a healer.
ori-def.729: mi, ma, abinnia, fat, fleshy. Pabinni, to fatten, trans. et acti. imp. abinnia, abinni-in, inabinni, inobinni-in, ipabinnia, pas. ipabinni, inapabinni, ino-ipabinni. Binni, fatness, abinni, a fathom. Maabioni, a fattener.
ori-def.730: mimabior, mamabior, abiorra, to remain behind without going forth. Pabior, trans. et act. imp. abiorra, ipa-biorra, pas. inabiorran, inoabiorran, ipabiorra. ipabior, inipabior, inaipabior. Bior, nom. is used as a preposition. Ma-abior, to remain behind.
ori-def.731: mi, ma, abirbirra, abirbirren, inabirbir, inoabirbirren, abirbirren, a composing of the mind in anger. Mabirbir itsies, to pacify. Pabirbir, ditto. Abirbir, nom. a composing, a pacifying, a pacifier.
ori-def.732: minabissas, mamabissas, abisassa, to make one's self ready, to go any where or do any thing. Perhaps also ready. Pas. pabissas; trans. et act. abissassa, abissassan, inabissas inoabissassen, ipabissassan, pas. ipabissas, inipabissas, inoipabissas. Abissas. nom. preparing. Maabissas, a preparer.
ori-def.733: mi, ma, abissa, upright in mind, virtuous. Pabissen, trans. et act. imp. abissea, abissei, inabisse, inoabissein, ipabissea, pas. ipabissi, inipabisse, inoipabissen. Ma-abisse, to make righteous. Babisse, righteousness.
ori-def.734: as mabise; bisse, is only said of many. ja mabisse bisse tape ja tatakorroe, as straight as a line; intend. mabisse. Bisse bisse, intend. babisse, see pisse. Ma-abisse bisse, to make right, upright.
ori-def.735: minabo, mamobo, aboa, aboan, inaboan, ino-aboan, to pity, to forgive, to deliver. Pabo, pinabo, papabo, ipaboa, ipabo, inipabo, inoipabo, ditt?. Anything done out of compassion. abo, iniabo, ino jabo, Abo, nom??? forgiveness, abonno babossi. Bo, grace, mercy; bo no tsies. Ma abo, one who pities.
ori-def.736: mi, ma, ab-oa, neutr. to rot: pas. rotten. Pab-o, trans. ab-o, a rotting.
ori-def.737: minaboas, mamaboas, aboasa, to remove. Paboas, trans. pass. aboasas, inaboasas, inoaboasas, ja, ta, i-aboas, ini-aboas, ino0iaboas ja ballag; nom. aboas, a removal. Ma-abaas, a remover.
ori-def.738: minaboch-o, mamabogh-o, to stink. Paboch-o, trans. et acti. imp. aboch-on, pas. aboch-oan, ipaboch-oa, ipaboch-o, inaboch-oan, inoaboch-oan, inipaboch-o, ino-ipabocho. Bocho, stink.
ori-def.739: miniaborra, mamaborra, aborra, to be pacified, neutr. Borra, an ally, from maborra. Ma-aborra, a peace maker. Aborra, pacifying. Paborra, trans. et act. imp. aborra, ipaborra, to pacify.The pas. act. trans. aborran,inaborra, ino-aborran, ipaborra, inipaborra, inoipaborra.
ori-def.740: mi, ma aborrieda, neutr. overturned; the root, porried.
ori-def.741: raised, bumpy, angular, not round. Maborroch a sies, maborrogh a torran, maborroch ja morra &c. Paborrogh. trans. et act. imp. aborrogga, ipaborrogga, pas. aborroggen, inaborrogh, inoaborroghen. ipaborroggen, inipaborrogh, ino ipaborroghen, Borroch, a bump.
ori-def.742: mi, ma, abosoa, neutr. to wear away, to change. Paboso, pi, pa, imp. abosoa, pass. abosoan, inobosoan, ipabosoa, inipaboso, inoipaboso, to wear off.
ori-def.743: dead. Cho macha, a dead man; also, dried up. Macha da baron, dry wood. Macha da ta, dry land. Pacha, to kill, acti. imp. acha, achar, inûcha, ino achan, trans. ipacha, inipacha, inoipacha. The neutr. has no other noun than macha itself. It is also the verb macha, mi, ma, acha, to die. Acha, a death blow; nom. Ma-acha, a murderer.
ori-def.746: an adulterer or adulteress. From chûmmod.
ori-def.747: minachab, mamachab, achabba, achabban, inachabban, inoachabban, to do any thing secretly. Pachab, transi. Achab, theft. Ma achab. a thief.
ori-def.748: near, not far, mi, ma, achaddikka: neutr. paehaddik, trans. et acti. nom. chaddik, is used as the preposition prope. Radix chûmmaddik. Maûbe a chaddik, to look near. Ma-achaddik ocho, a neighbour, one who is near.
ori-def.749: mi, ma, achalloa, clear; machallo a to, clear water: machallo a boesûm, clear air: machallo a tattorrodauron, a clear mirror. Pachallo, trans. et activ. Gallo, nom. clearness. Machallochallo, intend. Ma-achallo, clearer. Pachallo, act. achalloa. pas. ipachalloa, trans. achalloon, inachalloon, inoachalloon, ipachallo, inipachallo, inoipachallo.
ori-def.750: the end, mi, ma, achal-pod-da, to come to the last, completed as machil. Achalta, or achalpodda dûmmoro tapos, come in together. Minachalt, or minachal-pod sohsa tapos, they are all gone in together. Pachalt, is acti. et. Pachalpod, trans. finished. Achalta, achalten, inachalt, inoachalten, imp. pas. Pachalta, ipachalt, inipachalt, inoipachalt.
ori-def.751: deep. Machammochammo-nochaûch, spoken of a well. Mina, mama, achammochammoa, any thing dark and dismal as in a well. Mamarorammo, is used also by the Takey people Chammochammo ai? morammo, nom.
ori-def.752: mi, machanacha, nertr.? notched. See chûmmanach. Chanag, a notch in an arrow.
ori-def.753: mi, ma, g: achaporra, of few words, not to speak much, to be sti? Pachabor, transi. et acti. Machapochapor, intend. Chapor, nom. silence. ? is chapachapor. Ma achapor, one which keeps silence: imp. ahaporra, ?, inachaporran, inoachaporra, ipachaporra, pas. ipachapor.
ori-def.754: pitted, rumpled, rough. Pachauch, trans. et acti. imp. achaûcha, achaûchen, inachaûch, ipachaûcha, pas. ipachauchen, inipachauch, inoachauchen, inoipachauch. Chaûch, a well. Ma achauch, a well digger.
ori-def.755: glowing, metaphorically used of ardent spirits; because th? make the face to glow. Pagappo, glow. acti. trans. imp. apappoa, agpoan, inagappoan, inoagappoan, ino ipagappo.
ori-def.757: mi, ma, acharriebba, invisible, is used of wind, spirit, &c. Acharrieb, nom. Ma acharrieb, one who renders any thing invisible.
ori-def.758: mi, ma, achattoa, to smoke. Pachatto, acti. trans. imp. achattoa, achattoan, inachattoa, inoachattoan, ipachattoa, pas. ipachatto, inipachattoa, inoipachattoa. Chatto, nom.
ori-def.759: mi, ma, imp. achea, pass. acheën, inache, inoacheën, to guess whether any thing is even or uneven.
ori-def.760: minacheaubon, mamachaeaûbon, pas. acheaubonnan, inacheaûbonnan, inoachaûbonnan. Acheaubonnan, to jest, to joke, to sit idle, to dally. Acheûabon, nom. dallying. Ma acheaubon, to trifle. Ta ja don acheaubonnan, the place where people play.
ori-def.761: sweet: mi, ma, achedoa, (the e short) chedó, sweet. Ma achedo, a sweetener. Pachedo, transi.
ori-def.762: ingenious, mi, ma, acheer. Pacheer, trans. et act. pi, pa, imp. achera, acheran, inacheran, inoacheran, ipachera, pas. ipacheer, inipacheer, inoipacheer. Cheer, wit.
ori-def.763: intend. machedacheda; mi, ma. acheda, pas. achedaûn, & c. to change one's word or will. Pacheda, trans. Cheda, changeableness.
ori-def.764: an elder brother or sister: eousin or nephew.
ori-def.765: minachia, mamachia, achia, to repent, to change one's mind. Pachia, transit. to change any one. Achia, repentance. Ma achia, one who exhorts to repentance.
ori-def.766: mi, ma to drivel: achi achi erab, or machi achi, mi, ma, achi a chia, this is also to leak; nom. achi a ch, and achi a chi erab, slaver. Ma achi achi, one who drivels. Pachia chi erab, and pachi a chi, transi. Ma chiagchi, composed from machiagchi, to leak, and erab, spittle. Machiagchi ohallaonan, the pot leaks. Achiagchi in, inachiagchi in, ina achisgchi in ja to, the water is leaked out.
ori-def.767: minachiegh, mamachiegh, neutr. to roast; achiecha, to broil, trans. Pachiech, to boil, the root is chummiegh, see the nomina; activ. siet P.
ori-def.768: mi, ma, achigilla, nearly like medadorri, Takeijs. Chiegh, a roasting. Ma achiegh, a roaster, as ma achachieg. Chieg, roast. Ma achieg, any thing roasted
ori-def.769: mi, ma, achimta, spruce, neat, clean, avoiding filth. Pachimit, trans. et act. imp. achimta, achimten, inachimtin, inoachimtin, ipachimta,pass. ipaehimt, inipachimt, inoipachimt. Machimchimit, idem. Ma achimit, a clearer. Chimit, nom. subst. cleanliness, neatness; used also as an adverb.
ori-def.770: sour, mi, ma, achich-a. Pachich, trans. et act. imp. achichos, achich in, inachich in, ino achich in, ipachich a, pas. ipachich, inipachich, ino ipachich. Chich, sourish.
ori-def.772: mi, ma, mamagcho, ipagchoa, ipagcha. inipagcho, inoipagcho, to speak.
ori-def.773: rumpled, rough; mi, ma, pachobot, transi. et acti. Machobochobo intend. Chobor, a ruffler. Ma achobor, one who makes ruffles. Imp. achobotta, pas. achobottan, inachobottan, inoachobottan, ipachobattu, pas. ipachobot, inipachobot, inipachobat.
ori-def.774: mi, ma, achobbechobba, neutr. i. chummobbechob, to be hasty. Chobbechob, act. et trans. Chobbechob, nom. hasty.
ori-def.775: mi, ma, achomorraja, frightened, confounded. Pachomorraja, trans. et act. Achomorraja, confusion,. Ma achomorraha, fright, imp. act. achomorraja, achimorraja, inachomorraian, tran. ipachomorraja, pas. ipachomorraja, inipachomorraia, inoachomorraia, ino ipachomorraia.
ori-def.776: minacho, mamacho, achoa, achon, inachon, ino achon, to take elsewhere; but this word in construction with nouns takes (n,) as machon o bido.
ori-def.777: everlasting. Pachonsar, trans. Machonsar, one who perpetuates. Acho, nom. ma acho, one who causes continuance.
ori-def.778: mi, ma, achochonna, neutr. ploughed. See chûmmûchon, nom. chonchon, a ploughman.
ori-def.779: mimachonagh, mamachonagh, achonagh=cha, to haunt. Pachonagh, trans. Achonagh, haunted. Ma achonagh, a haunter. Pachonagh, act. achonagcha, inachonagh, trans. ipachonagcha, pas. ipachonagh, inipachonagh, inoipacho-nagh.
ori-def.780: mi, ma, achorapa, neutr. the same as pedara. Pacheraap, trans. achoraap, nom. as aidarra. Pachoraap, act. trans. imp. achorapa, achrapen, inachoraap, ipachorapa, pas. ipachoraap, inipachoraap, ino achorap, ino-ipachorap.
ori-def.781: minachote, manachote; acho-tea, averse to any thing that is unpleasant. Also to suffer punishment. The root is chûmmote, see also act. pachote, in p. punishment. Maachote, a sufferer. chote, suffereing.
ori-def.782: mi, ma. achotulla, neutr. bent, not straight, physically and morally. Pachotul, act. et tran. pi, pa, imp. achotulla, ipachotulla, pas. ipachotul, &c. Chotul, a curve.
ori-def.783: mi, ma, achúmmachûmma, indistinct, the opposite of marimasal. Chûmmachûmma, nom. Ma achûmmachûmma. Pachûmmachûmma, act. achûmmachûmma, achummachumman, inachummachumman, inoachummachumman, trans. ipachûmmachumma, pas. ipachummachûmma, &c.
ori-def.784: minada, mamada, ada, adan, inadan, inoadan,  to divide. Pada, trans. Ada, a share. Ma ada, a sharer.
ori-def.785: minadaap, mamadaap, adapa, dadpen, inadap, ino-adapen,  to make haste. Padaap, imp. ipadaba, trans. ada aba, acti. Pass. ada aben, inadaab, inoadaaben, padaab, inipadaab, inoipadaab, adaab, haste. Ma adaab, one who hastens another.
ori-def.786: mi, ma, ada-alla, neutr. dishonourable, shameless. Pa-da-al, act. et trans. da-al, nom.
ori-def.787: to be satisfied, mi, ma, adabbia. Padabbi, trans. satisfied, dabbi, satiety. Ma adabbi, a satisfier. Adabbi, satisfying, act. Padabbi, act. adabbia, adabbin, trans. ipadabbia, pas. ipadabbi, inipadabbi, ino adabbien, inoipadabbi.
ori-def.788: ininadaddo, mamadaddo; adaddoa, to refuse: pas. adadoan, inadadoan, adaddoan. Padad, daddo, a refusal. Ma adaddo, a refuser.
ori-def.789: g: mi, ma, adaldalla, gentle, as ma-allal. Padaldal, pa-al-al, trans. Daldal, mildness. Ma-adaldal, one who wishes to be kind. Padaldal, act. adaldalla, adaldallen, inadaldal, paal-al, trans. imp, ipadaldalla, pas. ipa-daldal, inipadaldal, inoadaldallen.
ori-def.790: mi, ma, neutr. glistering, shinning, as if well scoured: but this only refers to any thing that has a white ground, and differs from raosan.Dallolees, nom. a shining, it is also the name of a tree, the bark of which shines like the European beech.
ori-def.791: minadarram, mamadarram, adarrama, darrammen, madarram, inodarrammen, trained; see the root dummarram, and there the neutr. daram, experience. Ma-adarran, one who is trained.
ori-def.792: minadas, mamadas, adassa, adassen, inoadassen, to praise. Madadas, also padas, praise. Ma-adas, a praiser.
ori-def.793: minaddik, mamaddik, adikka, &c. to forbid. Paddik. Adik, a prohibition. Ma adik, a prohibiter.
ori-def.794: mi, ma g: addoborra, busy, encumbered, neutr. Padobor, trans. Ma-adobor, troubled. Adobor, trouble, act. dobbor, care. Padobor, act. adoborra, adoborren, inadobor, trans. imp. padoborra, pas. padobor, &c.
ori-def.795: sick, mi, ma, adicha, nom. adject. Ma-adig, a sickness, one who makes sick, Adigh, a sickening. Dich, nom. sickness. Madeadig, intend. nom. Padich, act. adicha, adich, inadich, trans. ipadicha, pas. ipadich, inipadich, inoadichen, inoipadich, &c.
ori-def.797: mi, ma, g: adiddena, firm, close, fast holding.Madidden o arrar, a strong railing. Adidden ja tataap-oe, hold it dast. Applied to the mind, firm undaunted. Dadden, firm. Pa-didden, trans. Ma adidden, one who makes fast: adidden, a fastening. Pa-didden, act. adiddena, &c. trans. padiddna, pas. ipadidden, &c.
ori-def.798: minadirdir, mamadirdir, adirdirra, to tremble. Padirdir, act. et trans. dirdir, nom. a shaking
ori-def.799: minado, mamado, adoa, adoan, inadoan, inoadoan,  to cook. Pado, trans. Ado, a cooking. Ma ado, a cook.
ori-def.800: minadobdob, mamadobdob; dobdobba, dobdobben, zinobdob, inodobdobben, hurried and in difficulty. Padobdob, trans. See dûmmobdob, to hasten, neutr. nom. dobdob. Ma adobdob, one who hastens another.
ori-def.801: minadochallam, mamadochallam, adochallama, the calming and clearing up of wind and weather; also of anger. Padochallam, act. et trans. imp. adochallam, adochallaman. ipadochallama, pas. ipadochallam, inadochellaman, inoadochalleman, inipadochallam, inoipadochallam. Adochallam. Ma adochallam, one who calms people.
ori-def.802: Madodevbo-ibo, faint, weak; mi, ma, adodeibo-iboa, lax. Padodeibo-ibo, trans. et act. imp. adodeibo-iboa, adodeibo-iboan, inadodeibo-iboan, &c. pas. ipadodeiboibo, &c. Adodeibo-ibo, faintness. Ma adodeiboibo, one who makes faint.
ori-def.803: mi, ma, gareogera, flat, and round like the wheels of a coach. Pagareogeo, tran. et act. nom. gareogeo.
ori-def.804: and magagri, mi, ma, both neutr. from chûmmagids and gûmmagri, ticklish.
ori-def.805: minaggaga, &c. see magga, to throw after. Maggag o bato, to stone.
ori-def.807: mi, ma, agaiecha, neutr. from gummaiech, to delay. Aguiech, lateness, used adverbially. late. Ma agaiech, a delaying, adject.
ori-def.808: mi, ma, agakka, pass. agakken, &c. to call out, as pallieb. Pagak, trans. intend. magagak, agak, nom.
ori-def.809: mi, ma, unsettled, changeable: mi, ma, agchitagchitatta, is not said of men's will or words, but refers to things that exist now and then, as magchitagchitat moetas, it rains some times.  Agchitagchitat, changeableness.
ori-def.810: minagga, mamagga, agga, the means in order to an end, yaga, miagga, inojagga, the object or aim; agan, inagan, inoaggan, to throw out of the hand. Maggo taggargar, to cast anchor. Paga, trans. Aga, the throwing of projectiles. Ma aga, one skilful in throwing.
ori-def.811: Maggo-aan, mi, ma, aggo-ana, compounded of magga, to throw, and ann, food; when tow parties, after having promised their children, previous to the marriage, feed each other. Paggo-an, trans. aggo-aan, nomen. subst.
ori-def.812: mi, ma, sharp: agaata, pointed. Maggaat o zinoe, a sharp knife: maggaato raro, a three cornered hat. Maggagaat, intend. from gummaat. Gaat, a point. Ma agaat, any thing pointed.
ori-def.813: mi, ma, imp. aggea, tough, sticky, paste made from rice, starch, &c.
ori-def.814: mi, ma, aggocha, to annoy by vexation. Maggogh ja na, azijel o mababat, maggoghja, maggogh ja na babiaro machip. Pagoch, trans. goch, vexation. Ma agoch, vexer. Pagoch, act. agocha, &c. trans. ipagocho, &c.
ori-def.815: mi, ma. agossa, to fish with a sweep net, bu which the fishes are inclosed. Pagos, transi.
ori-def.816: mi, ma to bend any thing on the edge or end, as the edge of a napkin, &c. Also to go slanting upwards, as a way. Pagotarrar, trans. et act. imp. agotarrarra, agotarrarran, ipagotarrarra, pas. ipagotarrar, &c.
ori-def.817: Magoûlyk, mi, ma, agoulyka, neutr. to sprain the foot, to wrench. Pagoûlyck, act. et trans. a sprain of the foot. The natives cure this by the leaves of a certain tree, called satik, with which they bind up the limb in order to soften the skin, or to disperse the extravasated blood.
ori-def.818: mi, ma, agomacha, neutr. blotted out. See gûmmach.
ori-def.819: mi, ma, agoracha, the skin rubbed off; magoragh ja rima, the skin is off my hand. Magar aggorach, intend.
ori-def.820: mimai, mamai, imp. moa, to come. the 3rd person has sai, sanai, sasai, trans. only in the 3rd person, pasai, pi, pa: ipasaya. Mai, is he well? interrogatively.
ori-def.821: Mai-acho, all those who are related to us, whether male or female; also step father and mother. Seems to be compounded from the verbs Mai, to come, and macho, to bring; because when the daughters marry, they bring their husbands home to dwell.
ori-def.822: alike: mi, ma, imp. aubasa, aibas, nom. likeness. Ma aibas, one who makes alike. Paibas act. et trans. imp. aibasa, aibasan, inaibasan, inoaibasan, ipaibasa, ipaibas, &.
ori-def.823: minaibat; mamaibat, aibadda, aibaddan, inaibaddan, ino-aibaddon, to work for another for one's board. as the poor do for a meal. Men say also mikat. Paibar, trans. with respect to the person who is served; aibat, nom. service. Maibat, a servant, a labourer. Pas. aibadden, inaibda, inaibadden, inaibad, inoaibadden, with respect to the hire that is obtained.
ori-def.824: mi, ma, small, fine; but it is only said of many, for with regard to few it is keuzi; also than not thick. As makied. Paied, to make small. Ma-a-ied, or makikied, thin, Pa-i-ied, pakikied, trans.
ori-def.825: Ma-allas, calm, cleared up; is said of wind and weather, also of the feelings. Pa-allas, act. et trans. imp. a-allassa, a-allassen, ina-allassen, ino-a-allassen, ipallassen, ina-allassen, ino-a-allassen, ipallassa. &c. Allas, nom. calmness, clearness. Ma-a-allas, a soother.
ori-def.826: Ma-im-it, makiki, idem. Me-imimit, intend. makilikili, idem. middling, not too much, passable, neither too large nor too small. Is also used as machapor, and machapochapor, and then means moderate in conversation, neigher too still, nor too talkative.
ori-def.827: kagmairo, mi, ma, aiman, airoan, airoa, inairoan, ino airoan, to change; as men do the teeth, or bucks the horus. Pairo, trans. nom. airo, a changing. Ma-airo, a changer.
ori-def.828: minais, mamais, assa, aisan, inaisaa, inoaisan, to laugh. Pais, transais, a laugh. Ma-ais, a laugher.
ori-def.829: Ma-issal, mina-issal mama-issal, a-is-salla, to repeat, as children do before their master. Ma-issal o bido, to say out of book. Ma-issal o sies, to say by heart.
ori-def.830: mi, ma, aizia, near, at hand: people say also maizi, aizi, and arri, neighbourhood. Aizi, paizi, act. and trans. amp. aizia, aizian, inaizi, inoaizian, ipaizia, pas. ipaizi, inoipaize. Maaizi, nom. and ma arzi, one who brings near.
ori-def.831: mi, ma, akabollan, to be angry, to chide, ace. trans. Pakabol, akabolla, akabollen, pak-bolla, pas. ipakobol, inakobol, inoakobollen, &c. Kobol, anger, wrath. Ma-akabol, angry, wrathful.
ori-def.832: minakagh, mamakagh, akacha, akachen, &c. to bite. Pagach, trans. Agach, a bite. Ma agach, a biter.
ori-def.833: minagagach, mamagagagh, agagagcha, to itch after, to desire strongly. Magagagagach, intend. magagach. Pagagach, trans. gagach, an itching, a disire. Ma-agagach, one who itches.
ori-def.834: Ma-kairi, mi, ma, to do any thing with the left hand; as makairi ja simioch, pattite, &c. Ma annigh, idem. Ma akairi, a left handed man.
ori-def.835: Ma-kallamas, mi, ma, to do any thig with the right hand; as makallamas ja simioch, pattite, &c. Ma allamas, do.
ori-def.836: to be red; mi, ma, akakama, pakakam, trans. et act. imp. akalanna, ipakakanna, kakan, redness. Ma akakan, a red dauber. Pass. akakanna, inakakannan, ipakakan, inikakannan, inipakakan, inokakannan, &c.
ori-def.837: agamgamma, to be covetous. Pass: minagamgam, fut. mamagamgam. Ma agamgam, covetous, a miser. Gamgam, covetousness. Pagamgam, act. trans. imp. agagmgamma, agamgammen, ipagam?amma, pas. ipagamam, inagamgammen,&c.
ori-def.838: to be solitary, alone; mi, ma, akammigia. Pakammieg. trans. et act. imp. akammichia, akammichiin, inakammichi, inoakammichi-in, ipakimmichia, pas. ipakimmichi, &c. Kammichi, so itude. Maakammigi, one who is solitary and alone.
ori-def.839: mi, ma, to be covetous. (as magamgam) akammocha, imp. Pakammoch, act. trans. imp. akammocha, akammochan, ipakammocha, pas. ipakammoch, inakammo inoakammochan, inipakammioch
ori-def.840: mi, ma, akapossa, close, ped up. Also clownish, incapable of understanding. Makapos atsies: kûmmapos. Pakapos, act. et kapos, a closing up. Makapos thing stopped up.
ori-def.841: mi, ma, akakossia, disobedient. Pakakossi, pi, pa, kossia, akakossi-in, inakakossi, i?kossia, pas. ipakakossi, inipaka?fut. pass. inoakakossi-in inoipak?si; see act. kummossi, to render one disobedient.
ori-def.842: minakaries, mamakaries?riba, to run; written magarieb. garieb, trans. pas. agarieban, rieb, inoagarieban, a circle in ?men run. Ma-agarieb, a runne?
ori-def.843: mi, ma, akapiera, nertr. hooked on: kapier, a hook, Mapier, adject. hooked to.
ori-def.844: mi, ma, makarrichi, m?karrichi, akarrichia, to quarrel snarl. Pakarrichi, trans imp. i?richia, pass. ipakarrichi, inipa?chi, inoipakarrichi, pass. aka?ipakarrichi, inoakarrichi-in. Ka? a quarrelling. Ma-akarrichi, angry. Mizy, idem.
ori-def.845: mi, ma akinkinna, neutr. to ring as little bells; see kûmminkin, nom. kinkin, a little bell.
ori-def.846: mi, ma, akarroa, as mausse-lakko. Pakarro, to be idle, act. akarro, nom. Ma-akarro, a lazy fellow. Pass. akarroan, akarroan o tsinoep aarrien, the work is neglected.
ori-def.847: mi, ma, akirkirra, neutr. see kûmmirkir, to gnash the teeth. Pakirkir, act et trans. Akirkir, a gnashing of the teeth.
ori-def.848: mi, ma, akiolla, as maggaat. Kiol, nom. pointed. Makiol ja oog pama dol, a pointed bamboo, tapering towards the top. Ma-akiol, any thing pointed. Pakiol, trans. et act. to sharpen to a point imp. akiolla. pakiollen, inakiollen, inoakiollen, ipakiolla, &c.
ori-def.849: ma, mi, akkassa, akkassen, inakkas, inoakkassen, to revile any one, to accuse, to reproach. Pakkas, trans. Makkas o ma atattosik, to accuse falsely. Akkas, a reviling. Maakkas, a reviler.
ori-def.850: proper, just, suitable, sufficient; mi, ma, akkieshappa. Keshap and akkeshap, nom. Ma-akkeshappa, act. et trans. pakkeshap, imp. akkeshappa, akkeshappen, inakkeshappen, inoakkeshappen, ipakeshappa, &c.
ori-def.851: minakos, mamakos, akossa, akossen, to scratch, to scrape. Pakos, trans. akos, nom. Ma-akos, an extortioner.
ori-def.852: mi, ma, akorilasa, neutr. the same as meroobroob.
ori-def.853: minakas, mamakas, aksasaa, aksassan &c. to desire. Paksas aksas, desire. Ma-aksas, one who desires.
ori-def.854: Makosûm, to be jet black, mi, ma, akosûmma. Pakosum, paosûm; trans. et act. imp. aosûmma, aosum, inaosûm, ipoasumma, pass. ipaosum, &c. Osum, blackish. Ma-aosum, blackener.
ori-def.855: minalabagh, mamalabagh, choosing things equally good, not to know which to take, imp. allabagha. Ma allabagh, act. et trans. Pallabagh, pi, pa, allabagha, allabaghen, ina-al-labaghen, inoallabaghen, ipallabacha, ipallabagh, iaipallabagh, inoipallabagh. But Mabag, mi, ma, abagga, abaggen, inabag, not to know what to choose, to be anxious about a choice. Palag, abag, nom. Ma-abag, one who brings another into anxiety.
ori-def.856: mi, ma,alaga, alagen, &c. to catch, to surprise one in sleep, as the natives catch game while asleep, or pierce them with a spear.
ori-def.857: minalla, mamalla, alla-a, alla-an, &c. to adorn one's self. Palla, trans. to adorn another. Al-la, ornament. Ma-alla, an adorner.
ori-def.858: mi, ma, alachacha, loose, not tied tight, the opposite of madidden.  Falachach, act. et trans. intend. malachalachach, imp. alachacha, ipalachacha, a?chachen, inalachachen, inoalachachen, pas. ipalachach, &c. Lachach, looseness. Ma-alachach, one who makes any thing loose.
ori-def.859: minakadik, mamakadik, aladikka, aladikken, inaladik, inoaladikken, to take care, to protect, to rule over. Aladik, nom. a protection, rule, Ma-aladik, a protector, a ruler. Aladik, aijan, a seat of government.
ori-def.860: mi, ma, alachabba, long, slow, intend. Malachalagab. Palachab, act et trans. imp. alachabba, alachabben, inalachabben, inoalachabben, ipalachabba, pas. ipalachab, &c. Lachab, laziness, slowness.
ori-def.861: a sluggard. alachûlachab, as mûlachab, intend.
ori-def.862: and malalpielpi, mi, ma neutr. glittering, from lumpi, and lumpielpi.
ori-def.863: minalam, mamalam; alamma, one who fights with missile weapons, alûnna: inalam, ino-alammen, the place where; alammen; inalâmman, inoalamman. Alam, missile weapons, karri alam, to tight on, and maise alam, a fight. Ma-alam, one who is skillful, with missiles. Alam-an aijan, a tield of battle.
ori-def.864: minalama, mamalame, alama, alaman, inalama, ino-alaman, to cook pap. Palama, transi. Lallama, pop. Ma-alama, a pap maker.
ori-def.865: to be flat, mi, ma, alapama, palapa, trans. et act. imp. alapanna, alapannen inalapannen, ipalapanna, pas. ipalapan, &c. lepan, nemen. Ma-alapan, one who flattens.
ori-def.866: mi, ma alapitapsa, knended, pressed down; see lûmmapilapies.
ori-def.868: Malaûlaûb, minalaûlaub, mamalaulaub, the sparkling of a flame; hence clear, to burn well. Palaûlaûb, pi, pa, &c. see gûmmaûlaub.
ori-def.869: mi, ma, aliodda, aliodden, inaliod, to blow a whirlwind. Paliod, trans. Aliod, nom, a whirlwind.
ori-def.870: Malakkûm, minallakkûm, mamallakkûm, allakkûmma, to turn things upside down. Allakkûm, the turning as of a ruler. Ma-allakkûm, one that does that. Pallakkûm, pi, pa, imp. act. et trans all kkumma, ip llakumma, allakkûmman, inallakkûmman, inoallakkûmman, , pas. ipallakkûm, &c. To turn things over and over, but is only said of such things as nature or art has adapted for tunring over.
ori-def.871: mi, ma, alitullitoa, to reel: neutr see lûmmitullito.
ori-def.872: mi, ma, alleakka, as machote, neutr. pas. alleakken. inalleak, inoalleakken, act. trans. ipalleuk, inipalleak, inoipalleak. Palleak, to be averse. Alieak, aversion. Ma-alleak, a person who is loathsome.
ori-def.873: and mallegallegallich, mi, ma, pallegallich, and pailegalligich, as malachach, and makachakechach, pal. chach, and palach lechach.

and intensively, mariggoriggo, mi, ma, ariggoa, neutr.
changeable; mariggo o atite airab. &c.
to change one's word or will. Pariggo, act. et trans.
ori-def.953: mi, ma, arimasalla, clear-sighted, to look with wide open eyes.
ori-def.954:
minarior, mamarior, ariorra, to follow after; neutr.
parior, to leave behind; imp.
ariorra, ariorran, inarior, inoariorran, ipariorra, pass.
iparior, &c. rior, a following behind.
Arior, a leaving behind; ma-arior, to leave behind.
ori-def.957:
mi ,ma, aripoedpoedda, to clew up, to wind, aripoedpoed, nom.
one who clews.
ori-def.958:
mi, ma, arikakka, neutr. straddling wide.
See also rûmmikak.
Parikak, pi, pa, imp. arikakka, arikakken, &c. iparikakka, pass.
iparikak, &c. act. et trans. to straddle.
ori-def.959:
to doubt; minarmimi, mamarmimi, mamirmia, armimian, inarmimian, &c.
aramimi, a doubting.
Parmimi, trans. Ma-armimi, a doubter
ori-def.960:
mi, ma, as maritûp, even, cut of straight, as a bamboo, or piece of wood transversely.
See rûmmichum.
ori-def.961:
whole, not in pieces, nor broken.
Written marunmo, mi,ma, arûmmoa.
Parûmmo, to make a whole. imp. arûmmoa, act.
arûmmoan, iparûmmoan. inoarûmmoan, iparûmmoa, pass.
trans. iparûmmo, &c. iummo, soundness; ma-arumm_, a healer; arummo, a healing.
ori-def.962: mi, ma, to earn; same as marichum and marisap.
ori-def.963:
still, calm, also weak, pass.
See parne, and rummene.
Arne, calmness, stillness.
ori-def.965:
far, deep, mi, ma, aroû, ro, distance, deepness.
Paro, imp. aroa ,aro-an, aroan, inaro, inoaroan, iparoa, pas.
_p_o iniparo, inoiparo; ma-aro, one who deepens. Aro, a deepening.
ori-def.966:
round, neutr. from rûmmomorromo, mi,ma, rommorromo, roundness.
Ma-aromorromo, one who rounds.
ori-def.967:
mi, ma, shadows, neutr. See rûnuûinno; ronno, shadow. Ronno an aijan, a shadowy plce.
Paronno, act. et trans. pi, pa, aronnoa, aronnoan, inaronnoan, *inoaronnoan, iparonnoa, pas.
ipûronno iniparonno, inoiparenno.
ori-def.968: the time from  afternoon till  sun set. mi, ma, verbum.neutr.
ori-def.969: mi, ma, arorra, arorren, &c. to run against any thing.
ori-def.970:
the squeamishness of the stomach after having eaten any thing nauseous. 
mi, ma, marossoal ja ma-achaan inai o micbam.
ori-def.971: arorroa, together in common, &c. a crowd. or assembly. See pûrorro.
ori-def.972:
minûrpibi. mamarpibi. *arpibi, neutr. to wake up to awaken. Parpibi. pi, pa, imp. act, trans.
arpibia, arpibi-in, inarpibi, inoarpibian, pas. iparpibi. &c arpibi, a waking up.
ori-def.973:
without any thing, deprived of everything. Ta Deos marotul ja bog, God is incorporeal, i.e.
without a body, *pr. iut. ma, nom. deprivation, see the root rummûtul. Ma-arotul, one who is destitute. 
The Favorlang people do not use this word thus, but as the end of a chair, or table; 
still it comes to the same thing, for where any thing ends. there it exists no more.
ori-def.974: to pick out a splinter with a knife or needle, minarri, mamarri, arrio, arrien, narri, inoarrien.
ori-def.976: oebes to dig out, mi, ma, arria, pas. arrin, &c. see above.
ori-def.977: roughly, cut off, from rummisup, mi, ma, as a bamboo, round stick, &c. transversely; item marrichum.
ori-def.978:
loose, notclosetogether. 
Marroak onaupoot, a loosely woven stuff, marroak o adda, paddy thinly sprung up.
ori-def.980: minarup, mamarup, arûppû, aruppen, inoaruppen, to waive with the hand.
ori-def.981:
mi, ma, arsoasoalla, neutr. to seethe, or bubble up, as water does when it boil.
Parsoalsóal, imp. 
arsoasoûlla, arsoasoûllen, inarsoasoûl, inoasoasoal, iparsoasoalla, pas. soasoûllen, a seething.
Ma-arsoasoal, a seether.
ori-def.982: ripe, spoken of field fruit. Artsi, nom. ripeness.
