pineam papea, ipea, ipe-a, inipea, inoipea, to give; changed into ea, ean,
inean, &c. it means to be presented. Paya, pinaya, papaya, ipaya, inipaya,
 inoipaya, to cause to be given; this is written Paia, pi, pa, to distinguish it
from Paija, to lean backwards. Aija, a gift. Ma-aija, a giver.
ori-def.1656:
forms into tpea, as Pea, to prepare and dish up food and drink; in order to
treat anyone.
ori-def.1657:
pinébe, papébe, bebéa, bebeén, binébe, inobebéen, bebea, to dissuade.
Pabebe, pi, pa, ipabebe. to do thus.
ori-def.1658:
pinebé, papebé, ebéa, ebéan, inebéan, inoebéan, as pedarra. Paibe, pi, pa,
ipáibea. Aibe, nom. Aibe o rarobo, dough, i.e. flour mixed with water.
ori-def.1659:
pinechab, papechab, echábba, echabban, inechabban, inoechábban,
to murder secretly. Paichab, pi, pa, ipaichábba, ipaichab, &c. to fo thus.
ori-def.1660:
pi, pa, edarra, edarran, inedárran, inoedarran, when different things are
mixed together, as machoraáb. Aidarra; original substance with which 
anything is mixed, is edarran. Two different things, pedárra. A man, paidárra.
ori-def.1661: pi, pa, e-eoa, to dangle. Pai-eo, trans. E-eo, one who swings.
ori-def.1662:
pi, pa, eesá, pass. eesán, ineesan, inoeesan, to file; Paees, trans. Aees, a
file; also steel, because they file with things in which there is much steel.
ori-def.1663: pi, pa, e-ella, e-ellan, ine-ellan, ince-ellan, to acknowledge.
ori-def.1664:
pineroa, paperoa, éroa, eroan, ineroa, inoeroan, in two parts. Pairoa, pinairoa,
papairoa, ipairoa, inipairoa, inoipairoa, to divide into two parts.
ori-def.1665:
pinesasa, papesasa, esasá, esásan, inesasa, inoesasan, to begin. Paisasa, pi, 
pa, ipaísasa, ípaisasa, &c. to be first to begin. Tackalla ja pesása ûmmop
tûmmaapo bonna Tabaipaû ja rior. Tackalla has finished his field before Tabaipau.
Aisasa, a beginning.
ori-def.1666:
pinesasorri, inesasorrian, inoesasorrian, to change similar things, but knowingly
and on purpose, thus differing from Paûtatarrogi. Páisasorri, pi, pa, ipáisasorria,
ipaisasorri, &c. thus to change.
ori-def.1667: pi, pa, pesikkan, pass. pesikken, pinesikken, to break in pieces.
ori-def.1668:
pi, pa, pesilla, pesillen, pinesillen, inopesillen, is said of two fruits on one stalk,
or when one root divides into two. Paisil, trans
ori-def.1669:
pinesor, papesor, esorra, esorrán, inesorranm, inoesorran, to mean, to imagine,
to suspect. Paisor, pinaisor, papaisor, ipaisorra, ipaisor, inipaisor, inoipaisor,
to imagine in general.
ori-def.1670:
pinespattil, papespattil, espattilla, espattillen, inespattil. inoespattillen, to divide
into four. Paispattil, pi, pa, ipaispattilla, ipaispattil, inipaispattil, inoipaispattil,
to do so.
ori-def.1671:
pinetam, papetam, etamma, etamman, inetamman, inoetamman, to lean upon
the hand. Paietam, (to be distinguished from Paitam, to borrow,) pi, pa, 
ipaietûmma, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1672:
pinetórro, papetórro, etorroa, etorroan, inetorroan, inoetórroan, to divided into 
three. Paitorro, pinaitorro, papaitorro, ipaitorroa, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1673:
pinetûmmo, papetummo, epetûmmoa, epetummo, inipetummo, inoipetummo,
to spit upon. When it is also etûmmoa, etummoan, inetummoan, inoetummoan.
Paitummo, pinaitummo, papaitummo, ipaitummoa, ipaitummo, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1674:
(with an aspirate, not as fon,) the insects which eat out, and render hollow 
the bamboos.
ori-def.1676:
pinia, papia, bia, bian, binia, inobian, to drive away the wild animals, such as
hogs, and stags, who come and devour the fields. Babia, the nouns.
ori-def.1677:
piniách, pápiach, biácha, biachen, biniach, inobiachen, to separate fighters. 
Pabiach, pinabiach, pápábiach, ipábiacha, ipábiach, &c. to set apart.
ori-def.1678:
pinian, popian, biárra, biárren, biniar, inobiarren, to pull out. Piar o bar, to lift up
the arm. to strike. Pábiar, pinabiar. pa. ipábiarra, ipabiar, inipabiar, inoipabiar,
to reach out.
ori-def.1680:
pinido, papido, bídoa, bídoan, binidoan, inobidoan. to write. Pabido, pinábido,
papábido, ipábido, inipábido, inoipábido, &c. dit to. Bido, nom. a book, a writing. 
Babido, a writing, instruments for ditto.
ori-def.1681:
(let the first i be scarcely heard) pinichir, papichir, bechirra, bechirren, binechir, 
inobechirren, to let go anything that is bent. Also to push away any thing into a
stick. People say also Pichir o chacháap, to haul up a scoop net: pabichir, pi, pa,
ipabichirra, ipabichir, inipabichir, inoipabichir, ditto.
ori-def.1682:
piniepied, papiedpied, biedbida, biedbiden, biniedbied, inobiedbiden, to rub away
anything between the fingers. Pabiedoied, pinabiedbied, papabiedbied, 
ipabiedbida, &c. ditto.
ori-def.1683:
piniéd, papied, bida, bidan, binidan, inobidan, to girdle. Pábied, pinabied, 
papábied, ipabida, ipabied, &c. to do so. Babied. a girdle. Babied an aijan, the 
place for the girdle.
ori-def.1684: pi, pa, igcharra2, pass. igcharran, &c. same as pigchilla. Chárra, lattice work.
ori-def.1686:
pinigeno, papigeno, to skim; gabigeno, pinabigeno, papabigeno, ipabigenoa, 
ipabigeno, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1687:
pi, pa, igchilla, pass. igchillán, &c. to put one thing between two others, where
it does not adhere, but where it has room. Pichchárra, ditto. Paigchilla, trans. nom.
aigchilla, the doing so. Chilla, lattice work.
ori-def.1688:
pinila2, papila, ilá, dán, inila, inoflan, to hit, to touch. Paila. Pinaila, papaila, &c.
to touch. Thus people say, pila ja áúbo, the fish have got into the right basket, 
whenever there are fish therein. Aila, nom. a hitting.
ori-def.1689:
pinilla, papilla, billa, billaan, binilla, inobillaan, to cleave, to split. Babilla, pinabilla,
pa2pabilla, ipabullá, &c. ditto. Babilla, a cleaving. Billa, a cleft from Malilla, anything
to split with. Ma-ababilla, cleaver.
ori-def.1690:
pinillála, pi, pa, &c. to split frequently. Pabillabilla, &c. increases the sense. 
Pabilla, ditto.
ori-def.1691:
pinillibilli, papillibilli, billibilia, billibdien, hinillibilli, inobilliblien, binillibilli, inobilliblien.
to turn around, act. to twist. Pabillibilli, &c. to cause to be twisted. Pillibilli o saris o
aroot, thread, &c.
ori-def.1692:
pinilliech, seems to mean to put one's body in a position to do any
thing imporatant. Pilliech o maûadet, o makarrieb,o tûmmaap, &c. to put one's
self in a posture to pull out hair, to run, or to work. Pabilliech ditoo.
ori-def.1693:
intend. pillepillik, pi, pa, billika, billikken, binillik, inobillikken, to press or join anything
underneath, (not between) as summiet. Pábillik, trans. babillik, nom. a pressing, also
that which people lay on a thing to press it down.
ori-def.1694:
pinióp, papióp, ioppa, &c. to blow up. Piop o chau, to blow the fire. Piop o tabillo, 
to blow up or in. Piop o tattallo, to blow out. Paiop, pi, pa, ipaioppa, ipaiop, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1695:
pinior, papior, ipiórra, what? ipior, inipior, inoipior, to leave behind; to whom? biorran, 
bioiorrán, inobiorrán. Pábior, pi, pa, ipábiorra, ipábior, inipábior, inoipábior, to do so.
Bior, a remainder, is also used as preposition.
ori-def.1696:
piniri, papiri, iria, irian, inirian, inoirian, to search out, to choose, to reject, pairi, pináiri,
ipairia, ipairi, to do so.
ori-def.1697:
pi, pa, birbirra, birbirren, binirbir, inobirbirren, the blowing about of the flame of a fire or 
candle.
ori-def.1698:
irraba, irraban, &c. to weed, to pull up the weeds or grass out of the streets or places 
near the houses. But to weed fields is ummo-o; nevertheless this difference exists
between the two, that Pirraba is used when people gather the weeds from amongst the
good seed, but ummo-o when people pull up weeds out of a field, where no no good seed
has been sown.
ori-def.1699:
pinirras, papirras, pirrassa, pirrássen, pinirras, inopirrassen, to tear, act. Papirras, 
pinapirras, papápirras, ipapirrassa, ipapirras, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1700: (the i barely heard) the barley that is used in brewing liquor.
ori-def.1701:
(the i barely heard) pineries, papirris, iperisa, iperies, iniperies, iperies, to close, to button up.
bries, trans. Babries, nom. a ______
ori-def.1702:
(the i barely heard) pinirroos, papirroos, birroossa, birroossen, biroos, inobirroossen, 
to pull in ____ behind, to let go by. Pabirroos, pi, pa, ipabirroossa, ipabirroos, inipabirroos,
inoipabirroos, to let go by.
ori-def.1703:
pinisbis, papisbis, bisbissa, bissen, binisbis, mobisbissen, to _____ fast. Pabisbis, pi, pa,
ipabisbissa, ipabisbis, inipabisbis, inoipabisbis, ditto.
ori-def.1704:
pinisor, papisor, isorra, isoninisor, inoisorren, to set on. Pis chau, to set on fire. Pisor o tazi, 
send up a kite. Paisor, pinai, papaisor, ipaisorra, ipaisor, inipai, inoipaisor, to cause to set on.
ori-def.1705:
Pinissárra, papissárra, issárran, inissarra, inoissarran, to ____ in to company. Páisarra, 
pinaisarra, papáisarra, ipaisarra, inipaisarra, inoipaisarra, ditto. Aissarra, an accompanying.
Ma-aissárra, a _______ . Sarra, a lineal succession, where chiledren and grand-children
follow each other. See below
ori-def.1706:
pi, pa, &c. when _____ follow one after the other, in the manner of the natives. Paissarrasarra,
pi, pa, &c. to csuse _______ to be done.
ori-def.1708:
pinisse, papisse, bissea, bissein, binisse, inobissein, to rectify. Pábisse, pinábisse, papábisse,
ipábissea, ipábisse, &c. to cause to be rectified. Nom. Bisse, justice, righteousnesss. Babisse,
rectitude, from Pisse. Abisse, a justifying; act. Passese; intentd. Pisse; nom. Bisse.
ori-def.1709:
piensillo, papisaillo, bissilloa, bissilloan, biensillo, inobissilloon, to wrap up anything in order to
take care of it, as, silk, money, tabacco, &c. Pábissillo, pi, pa, ipábissilloa, ipabissillo, &c.
to cause to be done.
ori-def.1710:
(let the i be scarcely heard) pienso, pápisso, bissoá, bissoan, inobissoan, &c. to draw out, as
people do i ndrawing lots, and all kinds of drawing. Pábisso, pi, pa, ipábissoa, to cause to be 
drawn. Babisso, a drawing; this noun compunded with mau or karri signifies lots, 
because such are made by the drawing out of tickets. Maababisso, a drawer.
ori-def.1711:
piensir, papissir, pissirren, piensir inopiensirren, to close the gand fast, to press anything with
the hand. Papissir, pinapissir. papápissir, ipápissirra, ipapissir, inipapissir, inoipápissir, to cause
the ahnd to be closed.
ori-def.1712:
pinitítil, papititil, bietbitilla, bietbitillen, to break, cut, or slice a thing into small pieces; but is often
used of things that are long, and _____ (which?) by many transverse sections may made
smaller, as a bamboo. a fish plantain, &c. Paititil, pi, pa, ipaititilla, to cause this to be done.
ori-def.1713:
pi, pa, pittassa, pittassen, pitássen, inopittassen, to cut the hind legs of an animal in two, or
sever anything in two.
ori-def.1714:
pinittassir, papittassir, ittassirra, ittassirran, inittassirran, inoittassirran, to do anything by the side
of another, as walking, standing, lying, sitting, &c. Paitassir, pinaitassir, paitassir, ipaitassirra,
ipaitassir, to cause the above to be done.
ori-def.1715:
pinittas-tassir, papittas-ttas-tassira, ittas-tassirran, as palalat. Paitastassir, pi, pa, ipaitas-tassirra,
ipaitas-tassir, to do thus.
ori-def.1716:
pinittatik, papittatik, bittebittikka, bittebittikken, bientibbittik, inobittebittikken,  the multiplication of
________.
ori-def.1717: pi, pa, imp. ittaûa, to believe.  Aittaûa, belief. Ma-aittaû, a believer.
ori-def.1718:
pinittik, papittik, bittikka, bittikken, bientik, inobittikken, a pause in ____ (working? )when people 
have  finished ____ . Also to rest one's self, from _____ of work, in order afterwards to work with
new strength. pinitik, pinibittik, papábittik, ipábittikka, ipabittik, to cause to pause. pi, pa, bittoa, 
same as pazinado.
ori-def.1720:
pinittol, papittol, ittollaen, ittóllia, ittollen or anai or aijan, initollan, inoittollan, to let anything alone,
either while from despair of ever be able to reach the end. Páittol, pinaittol, papáittol, ipaittolla,
&c. to cause this to be done.
ori-def.1721:
an expression by which it is meant that we are constrained to do something. Na a pizio. 
summarada, pizio na a man, na a pizi o merieo o bido. Pinizi, papizi, imp. Paizi, pinaizi. inipaizi,
&c. to require any one to do anything, trans. izia, ipizia, pas, izian, &c.
ori-def.1722:
pinizich, papizich, bizicha, bizichen, binizich, inobizichen, to direct; pizich o pach a, o mabarieb,
o man, to lead on any one to fight, to run, to eat, &c. Pábizich, pi, pa, ipábizicha, ipábizich, 
o cause such to be done. Babizich, nom. a leading on. Ma-ababizich, a leader.
ori-def.1723:
papo-poa, the cry and song of birds. Pábo, pinabo, papabo, ipaboa, ipabo, inipabo, inoipabo,
to cause the birds to cry. Po, signifies also the cry of rats, mice, snakes, &c. Bábo, nom.
ori-def.1724:
pinoa, papoa, imp. boa, to bring forth fruit. Páboa, pinaboa, papaboa, ipaboá, &c. to cause to
bear fruit. Boa, nom. fruit, seed; person, flesh. Ma-ababoa, fruitful. Ma-ababoa o baron, a fruitful 
tree. But Poa, pi, pa, poá, pas. poán, pinoa, inopoan, to dye. Papoa, tans. papoa, nom the dying, 
and dye-stuff.
ori-def.1725:
pinoach, papoach, o-ach-a, oachen, inoach, ino-achen, to forget. Paûach, pinaûach, papauach,
ipauacha, ipauach, &c. to cause to forget. Aûach, nom. a forgetting. Ma-auach, one who forgets.
ori-def.1726:
pinó-ar, pápo-ar, bo-arra, bo-ar-ran. binoar, inoboarren, to make honey, also to chew rice or
barley, and to prepare the spittle wherewith strong drink is made. Paboar,  pináboar, papabóar,
ipabóara, ipáboar, &c. Baboa, nom. some spittle, from Massjekaû.
ori-def.1727:
pinóas, papóas, boasa, bóasin, binóas, inoboasin, to rob, to lay waste, to destroy. Páboas, pi,
pa, ipaböasa, ipáboas, &c. to cause to lay waste.
ori-def.1728: obasa, to set up a flag or vane; obáas, a flag which the young men stick on their heads.
ori-def.1729:
pinoberies, papoberies, oberisa, oberisen, onoberies, ino-oberisen. to take leave, or to bid 
farewell; those who take leave say, kamossa ma: and those who bid farewell say, sasa;
páûberies, pinaûberies, papáûberies, ipauberisa, inipaûberies, to cause to take leave.
Aûberies. nom.
ori-def.1730:
pinóbo, papóbe, boboa, boboan, binoboan, inoboboan, to sift, to lat any thing pass through a
sieve whether wet or dry. Pabobo, pinábobo, papáboba, ipaboboa, ipabobo, to cause this to be
done. Moparraparra, idem. Bábobo, nom. a sieve, a sifting.
ori-def.1731: pinoch, papóch, bocha, bochen, binoch, inobochen. to shoot. Páboch, pináboch, papaboch, ipaboch, inipaboch, inoipaboch.
ori-def.1732: pinocharráddan, papocharraddan, to have the cramp. Paûcharraddan, &c. to cause anyone to have the cramp. Aucharraddan, the cramp.
ori-def.1733: a large fruit, outwardly not unlike the european pumpkin.
ori-def.1734: pinoch-poch, papóch-poch, to smoke, to make dusty. Papoch-boch, pinapoch-boch, papoch-boch, to cause to smoke, ipâpoch-bocha, ipapoch-boch, inipapoch-poch.
ori-def.1735: pi, pa, intend. podarrodárros, to go on further and further in doing anything. ex gr. podarrodarros o macheaûban, to make game first with one and then with the other.
ori-def.1736: pinodda, papódda, boddá, boddáan, binodda, inoboddaan, to bring forth, to breed; pabodda, pinabodda, papabodda, ipabodda, to cause to bring forth. Bodda, birth. Baboddaan. birth place. Ma-ababodda, fruitful. Poddo tattaula, to regenerate.
ori-def.1737: pinoddik, papóddik, to become thick, to swell, also to be swollen. Paûdik, pinaûdik, papaûdik, ipaudikka. ipaudik, &c. to cause to become thick. Audik, a swelling.
ori-def.1738: pinoddelon, papoddelon, to be costive. Pauddillo, pinauddillo, papaûddillo, ipauddilloa, ipaûddillo, &c. to cause costiveness.
ori-def.1739: pinoddo, papoddo, boddoa, boddoan, binoddoan, to calculate with an abacus. Papoddo, pinaboddo, papaboddo, ipaboddoa, ipaboddo, &c. to cause so to reckon. Boddo, an abacus.
ori-def.1740: pinóddodo, papóddodo, oddodoá. oddodan, inoddodoan, to complain. Pauddodo, pinaûddodo, papaûddodo, ipaûddodoa, ipauddodo, &c. to cause to complain.
ori-def.1741: pinoelakies, papoelakies, oelakisa, oelakísan, inoelakisan, to wander. to err from the way, to have a misunderstanding. Paulakies, pi, pa, ipaulakies, to cause to err.
ori-def.1742: a water bubble, a blister on the body. To be written, hoelassi.
ori-def.1743: pinotach, pipoetach, oetach-a, oetach-an, inoetachan, ino-oetachan, to stay anywhere. Paûtach, pinautach, papaûtach, ipaûtacha, ipautach, inipaûtach, ino pautach, to cause to remain.
ori-def.1744: pi, pa &c. as poetach. to remain anywhere long. Paûtaûtach, pi, pa, to cause to remain.
ori-def.1745: pi, pa, oetanna, oetannan, inoetannan, to do anything by way of provision, to lie in wait, or to lurk in secret. As poetan o aras, to fetch a quantity of grass.
ori-def.1746: pinoetat, papoetat, oetatta, oetattan, inoetattan, ino-oetattan, to mean, to suppose, to suspect. Paûtat, pinaûtat, papaûtat, ipaûtatta, ipaûtat, &c. to cause such to be done. Aûtat, nom. meaning. Ma-aûtat, a believer.
ori-def.1747: pi, pa, &c. intend. poetat, to mean sincerely, to believe firmly, nom. aûtaûtat, belief.
ori-def.1748: pinogámgam, papogámgam, ogagámma, ogamgammen, inogamgam, ino-ogamgammen. to do anything shorty or quickly after another. Pogámgam ja micham, to drink shortly after one another. Paûgamgam, pi, pa, ipaûgamgamma, ipaûgamgam, inipaûgamgam, inoipaûgamgam, to cause to be done.
ori-def.1750:
pinoggogo, papoggogo, oggogoa, to rub, in general either with ____, in which case it is oggogoon, 
inoggogoan, ino-oggogoan (整頁模糊)
ori-def.1751:
pinókbok, papókbok, bokbokka, bokbokken, binokbok, inobokbokken, to beat with the hand. Pábokbok,
pinabokbok, papabokbok, ipábokbokka, ipabokbok, inipabokbok, inoipabokbok, to do so.
ori-def.1752:
pinokkor, papókkor, okkorra, okkorran, inokkórran, ino-okkórran, to put a stopper on anything, on a can,
&c. Paûkor, pinaûkor, papaukor, &c. to cause this to be done. Aukor, nom. a stopprt. Pokkor, a peg.
ori-def.1753:
pi, pa, ipolliboa, pass. ollibo4an, inolliboan, ino-ollibóan, to disguise, to conceal any
dishonourable expression. Paûllibo, trans. Aûllibo, nom.
ori-def.1757: mould, the canker worm, see phon.
ori-def.1759:
a boil that comes of itself. For whenever any part of the body, as the head, swells up, or whem any swelling
occurs through a fall, &c. the same is audik.
ori-def.1760:
pinónnad, papónnat, onnadda, onnadden, inonnad, ino-onnadden, to make fire burn, to make a fire.
Paûnad, pinaûnad, papaûnad, ipaunadda, &c. to cause this to be done.
ori-def.1761:
pinochacha-a, paporchacha-a, borchacha-á, borchacha-an, binorchacha, inoborchachan, to push in
between so that people on either side must get out of the way. Paborchach-a, pinaborchach-a, &c.
to cause to be done.
ori-def.1762:
pinorpor, papórpor, porpórran, pinorpórran, inoporporran, to raise. Papórpor, pináporpor, papaporpor,
ipaporporra, ipáporporr, ipáporpor, inipaporpor, inoipaporpor, to make dusty. Barrabór, dust.
ori-def.1763:
pinórra, papórra, iporrá, borra, borráan, borráan, &c. to dry, to put out to dry. Paborra, pi, pa, to cause this
to be. Baborra, a drying. Babor an, babor aijan, a dying place, as a frame in which people dry flesh.
ori-def.1764:
pi, pa, orrátta, pass. orrattan, inorráttan, ino-orrattan, to wager, to guess at any _______ . Paûrrat, trans.
aurrat, nom.
ori-def.1765: it seems to mean to fall suddenly, as a beast that is _______ .
ori-def.1768:
pinorroog, paporroog, orroogga, orrooggan, inorroog, ino-orrooggen, to overthrow. Paûroog, pinauroog,
papauroog, paurogga, to cause to do so.
ori-def.1769:
pinorrot, paporrot, borrotta, borrotten, bi crrot, inoborrotten, to bind. Paborrot, pinaborrot, papáborrot, 
ipáborrotta, ipáborrot, papáborrot, ipáborrotta, ipáborrot, &c. to cause to bind. Baborrot, a binding.
ori-def.1770:
pínosa, papósa, osaá, osaán, niosaán, inosaán, to make the ground clean, by the rooting out of weeds 
or jungle. Paüsa, pinaûsa, papausa, ausa-a, ipausa, inipausa, &c. see Mausa.
ori-def.1771: pinosi, paposi, osia, osi-in, inosi, ino-osian, to scour, to whiten. Paus, pinausi, papausi, ipausia, ipausi, inipausi, to cause to be scoured.
ori-def.1772:
pinosi, paposi, osiam osien, inósi, ino-osien, where? osian, inosian, inoosian, to stow anything away.
Pausi, pinausi, papausi, ipausis, &c. to cause to do so. Osi, a sheltering.
ori-def.1773:
pinossirrere, papossirrere, bosxsirrerea, bossirreri-in, binosirrere, ino-bosirrerein, to hang up by 
the neck. Pabosirrere. pi, pa. ipabosirrerea, ipabosirrere, inipabosirrere, to suspend; people say
also Pausirrerea.
ori-def.1774:
inosisi, paposisi, osisia, osisian, inosisi, and inosisian, ino-osisian, to end, to leave off.
Pasisi o rior, and sisi o rior, to be the last. Pausisi, pi, pa, ipausisia, ipausisi, inipausisi, inoipausisi,
to cause to end.
ori-def.1775:
pinosos, paposos, osossa, osossen, inosos, ino-osossen, to put up the hair in the native 
manner, to bind together grass, to dress the head, to adorn a field or any place with knots of grass.
But then, osossa, inosossan, ino-ossosan are used. Pausos, pi, pa, ipaûsossa, to cause such 
to be done.
ori-def.1776:
pinossor, papossor, bossorra, bossorran, binossorrar, inobossorran, to castrate. Pabossoor,
pinabossor, papabossor, to cause the same to be done.
ori-def.1777:
pi, pa, ottaia, ottaián, inottaián, ino-ottaian, to sleep on the same bed, and under the same 
covering.
ori-def.1778:
pinottan, papottan, ottanna, ottánnan, inoittannan, ino-ottannan, to lie in wait in secret. Pautan,
pinautan, papautan, ipautanna, inipautan, inoipautan, to cause such to be done. This is the
same with Poetan, above, for if any one will surprise another secretly, he must first lie in wait.
ori-def.1779: a knot, a knuckle, a knot in wood.
ori-def.1780:
pinottup, papottup, otuppa, ottuppen, inottup, ino-ottuppen, to put out; sjajo, potup o chau, elli
mamaninabonna, of you had put out the fire, it would not have burnt my field: ja
ottuppen ja tattullonoe, is the candle put out? Pautap, pinautap, &c. to cause to be put out:
ipautuppi Takalla ja tattullonoe, let Takalla put out the candle.
ori-def.1781: pinottup, papottup, otuppa, ottuppen, inottup, ino-ottuppen, to put out; sjajo potup ochau, elli maman inabonnam if you had put out the fire, it would not have burnt my field: ja otuppen ja tattullonoe, is the candle put out? Pautap, pinautsp, &c. to cause to he put out: ipzuppi Takalla ja tattullonoe, let Takalla put out the candle
ori-def.1782: pi, pa, oulaboa, same as Moah.
ori-def.1783: pinoz-i, papoz-i, oz-ia, inoz-i, ino-oz-ieu, to awaken. Pauz-i, pin#uz-i, papauz-i, ipauz-ia, ipauz-i, inipauz-i, inotpauz-i, to cause to awake
ori-def.1784: pinozios, papozios, oziossa, oziossan, inozinossan, to come in any one's place, to succeed any one. Pauzios, pinauzios, papauzios, ipauziossa, inipauzios, inoipauzios, to cause to succeed. Ozios, succession. Mzaózios, successor.
ori-def.1785: pinozirries, papozirries, ozirrisa, pzirrisan, inozirrisan, ino-ozirri-san, to miss one's aim. Pauzirries, pi, pa, ipauzirrisa, &c. to cause one to miss the mark.
ori-def.1786: the hard gummiress which sometimes sticks to the eye lashes
ori-def.1787: pineries, paperies, iperisa, iper##, iniperies, inoiperies, to be close. Pabries, pi, ,pa, ipabrisa, ipabries, inipabries, to cause it to be done.
ori-def.1788: pientat, paptat, ptadda, pass. ptaddan, pientaddan, to begin, to do anything from the first. Paptat, nom.
ori-def.1789: pienso, papto, ptoa, pass. ptoon, piento, inoptoon, same as ptat. Papto, same as paptat.
ori-def.1790: pinûlla, papûlla, bulla-a, bulla-an, binulla-an, inobulla-an, to knock in pieces. Pabûlla, pinûbulla, papabulla, ipabulla, to cause to be brokern to pieces. Written poulla.
ori-def.1795: a joint, as between the knots of bamboos. Writen Raag, the verb, Paraag, see the letter P
ori-def.1807: bad, in general. Verb Marapies, to be wicked. Ma-arapies, a bad man.
ori-def.1808: (let the a be scarcely heard.) beneath. Morpo, the verb to be low. Patapo, pi, pa, to cause to be low
ori-def.1809: a low place in a field, where rain water collects rûas
ori-def.1811: a song of many. From Rummait
ori-def.1813: a neighbors house. Raûmraûdon, a neighbor. Raraûdon o sjam o sini, neighbour man or woman.
ori-def.1817: a stripe marker off with a knife for a measure
ori-def.1818: a ring or ferrol, made to fasten anything.
ori-def.1819: a hat, a dog's collar. Raro daal, a straw hat. Raro osan, a bank.
ori-def.1823: bandages, with which anythinng is bound in order not to burst.
ori-def.1826: unwise, half foolish, as rûchoen, compounded of rau and saan because the understanding is wauting.
ori-def.1827: ri, ra, raûsûnna, rausannan, rinausannan, to shine, to glister, but is only said of that which had a black ground, otherwise it is madallolees.
ori-def.1828: it is fallen; there it lies
ori-def.1832: all sorts of upper garments, that cover the shoulders no matter of what form or length
ori-def.1833: or ribókkebok, a lined coat or jacker
ori-def.1834: a bank, not entirely covered by water, the strand, a sandbank.
ori-def.1835: a small house, where men put seed.
ori-def.1837: a hand; rim o kallamas, the right hand; rim o kaixi, the left hand.
ori-def.1839: (the e short) o erien, a pair of legs, as the hind legs of a deer, &c. joined as they are in nature
ori-def.1841: after. From Mûrior. Matarior, to be behind. Patarior, trans.
ori-def.1842: instruments about a fire place, where people set the pot on to boil, as with us trevets, roasters, &c. the natives, however, merely fix three stones in the ground.
ori-def.1845: distance, depth. Masanno a ro in Taijoan oe, how far is Taiwan? Masanno a ro ja chauch oe, how deep is the well?
ori-def.1846: the stalk or stem of a plant.
ori-def.1852: a wart; also a button on clothes
ori-def.1854: a shadow, as of an umbrella shed, or tree, &c. but not from #### which is dachûm, See #####
ori-def.1856: the bottom of anything, especially the fundament of the body.
ori-def.1857: a shore, also a root as Bossor.
ori-def.1859: rinorieb, inororieben, to grow dizzy, as if every thing went round, and people did not know where they were.
ori-def.1860: one with another, altogether, a heap of lifeless things, as wood, straw, paddy, millet, &c. Hence is derived rorronoûda, to disttribute equally; parorronoada, to cause such to he done.
ori-def.1863: ri, ra, rubboa, rubboon, parûbbo, trans. to grind. Rarubbo, meal. Rarubboan, or rarûbbo aijanm nail work.
ori-def.1864: rinûmchorcho, rarûmchorcho, to pitch up and down, as a ship at sea, or a weak bamboo, on which anything is carried. Pûarchorcho, pi####horcho, papûarchorcho, ipûarchorcho, &c to cause this to be done.
ori-def.1865: rinûmka, rarûmka, to gather branches. Pûarka, pinûarka, pnpûarka, ipûarka-a, &c. to do the same. To separate from one another, as the branches of tress, shoot out on all ####. Rumkara, nom. # shooting out, as the branches of trees.
ori-def.1866: ri, ra, rala, rûlen, rinaal, the (u) short, to sit on one's heels, as tsimsakal. Paraal, to cause this to be done
ori-def.1867: rinûmmab, araûmmab, received, pregnant, impregnated; also to pass by any time in doing anything. Then it is raba aud rabea, raban, rinaban, inoraban. Naraap o rummios tapos assaban rûmmûb elli tatumkach, six days the village will let pass by, that they do not go out to hunt, see Porab. Raben, rinab, inoraben, pregnancy is occasioned, rarb, nom. subs. rûmmab o sini, the woman is pregnant.
ori-def.1868: rinûmmaha, rarûmmaba, raba-a, rabaûn, to cover with the wings, as birds do thier young. Also to take any one for a father, in order to serve or help him. See paraba: raraba, a breeding: raraban, a breeding place.
ori-def.1869: is said of anything that people cannot well see either through distance or darkness, or any other obstruction
ori-def.1870: rinummain, rarummainrûinarainen, rinain, inorainen, to petrify. Parain, pinûrain, papûrain, ipûraina, ipûrain, inipûrain, inoiparain, &c to cause to be petrified.
ori-def.1871: rinummûmmik, rarûmmûmmìk, ramka, to take the property to another, under pretences that it belongs to ourselves; with regrad to the ###ter it is said ramlin, rinammik, inorûmkin: and to the person, ramkan, rinûmkan. Parammik, pinûrammik, paparammik, ipûramka, iparammik, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1872: rìnûmmûpal, rûíhmapal, rapûlla, rapallen, rinapal, to beat about ####dly Parapal, trans. rarapal, a ####ding. Ma-arûrapal, a blinder.
ori-def.1873: rinûmmait, rarûmmait, raida, raian, rinaidan, inoraidan, to sing in ####us. Paraid, pinarait, papûrait, iparaida, iparaid, iniparaid, inoparaid, to do so.
ori-def.1874: rinûmmapies, rarûmmapies, eapisa, rapisen, rinapies, inorapiesen, to be evil. Parapies, trans. to cause any ###in. Imper. iparapisa, iparapies, ##esa rûmmapies o airien oe, to spoil ##t any one has made or done. Ra## airien, the work is spoiled, nom rarapies, sin, also ûrapiessen marapies. Ma ûrarapies, a sinner. Rûm###rapies, intend. rapieapies, nom.
ori-def.1875: rinûmmaried, rarûmmaried, rarida, raridan, raridan, rinaridan, inoraridan, to make a division of land. Pararied, pinararied, papararied,  &c. to cause such a separation. Raried, nom, a separation. Rariedan and raried aijan, the place where the fields dicide
ori-def.1876: rinûmmach, rarûmmaûch, raûcha, raûchan, rinaûchan, inoraûchanm, to uncover the head for any one. Paraûch, pi, pa, iparaûcha, ipûrauch, &c. to cause the head to be uncovered. Ta Albert iparaûch o raro ta capitain ja sisjim, the children are charged by Albert to uncover the head before the Captains.
ori-def.1877: rinûmmaro, rarûmmaro, raroa, raroan, rinaroan, inoraroûn, to put on the hat, to put a collar on a dog. Pararo, pinararo, papûraro, paraûraroa, roa, oa, intede, ipararo, &c. to cause the hat to be put on, or a collar to be put on a dog. Raro, a har, a collar
ori-def.1878: rinummûno, rinummaûno, araûmmaûno, raúnoa, raûnoon, rinûûno, inoraunoon, to behead. Parauno, pinarauno, paparaûno, ipûraûnoa, ipûraùno, iniparaûno, inoiparauno, to cause to be beheaded.
ori-def.1879: ranummaut, rarûmmaut, rauda, raudan, rinaûdan, inoraûdan, to remian out; innai dema joa rummaût a milip ai; wherefore do you remain so long out? Paga sasaita Cabba, sa a rummaût de d' Hallibo Cabba will not come, he remians at Hallibo. Pûraut, pinaraut, paparaut, iparauda, iparaut, to cause to remian out. Rûmmaûraût, &c. paraûmût &c as above, to remian long out, or cause this to be done.
ori-def.1880: ri, ra, imp. redos, pass, parido, trans. to draw a bow
ori-def.1881: rinummedos, roddossa, rodossen, riendos, inorûddossen, to snuff up. Pûardos, pinardos, papaardos, ipaardossa, ipûardos, inipaardos, inoipaardos, to cause to snff up
ori-def.1882: ri, ra, rea, rees, rine, inoreen, to speak hard. Also to poke out the belly as if blown out, to threaten the opposite of kummibach, also to boast. Pare, trans. Ma-arare, a hard speaker
ori-def.1883: ri, ra, reessa, reesen, rinees, inoreessen, same as Chummisel.
ori-def.1884: rinûmmemorémo, rarûmmemoremo, remoremoa, remorémoan, rinimorémo, inoremoremoan, rontom, to look all around. Paremoremo, pi, pa, iparemoremoa, iparemoremo, inipûremoremo, to cause thus tto bedone
ori-def.1885: rinûmmene, raûmmene, rinmea, rinmeen, rinmene, inorinmeen, to cause to soak; that in which renean, rinean, inorinnean. Paarne, pinaarne, pa. ipaaarnea, ipaarne, inipaarne,  inoipaarne, to cause this to be done. Nom, raarne, a soaking.
ori-def.1886: rinûmmere, raruere, rerea, réreanm rineran, inorerean, to go round, to encompass. Parere, pi, pa, iparerea, &c. to go on the other side, as if to get our of any one's eye
ori-def.1887: rinummeries, rarummeries, rerisa, rerisen, rineries, inorerisen, to put anything over from one place to another; pareries, pinûreries, papareries, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1888: rinummi, rarummi, ri-a, ri-in, rini, inori-in, to keep watch, to guard. Pûri, pinûri, papûri, iparia, &c. to cause watch to be kept. Rari, nom. a watch. Rarian, or rariaijan a watch house. Ma-arari, a watch-man
ori-def.1889: ri, ra, riboû, to hold the feast which is celebrated in the evening after marriage, to keep a wedding. Nom. rariba, obaan o rariba, a wedding. To keep a feast the day after marriage they call Ummior o rariba, de rariba, i.e. to follow up the marriage. And when they drink with the new married couple it is micham o rûmain.
ori-def.1890: rinummibal, rarummibal, riballa, riballen, rinibal, inoriballen, to pull down, also to separate. Pûribal, pinaribal, paparibal, ipariballa, iparibal, to break down. Raribal, a breaking up. Ma-arûibal, one who breaks.
ori-def.1891: rinummibirrieh, rarummibirrieb, ribirriba, ribirriben, riuibirrieb, inoroibirribhen, to fly hither and thither, as those who are assailed on every side. Pûriberieb, pi, pa, ipariberiba, &c. to cause to do so.
ori-def.1892: rinummicheriech, rarummicheriech, richericha, richerichen, rinicheriech, to make a mark with a knife or such like, in order to fix a measure. Paricheriech, pi, pa, iparichericha, &c. to cause to be marked off, This does not mean to cut through a rope or bamboo with a knife or saw.
ori-def.1893: rinum: rarum: richumma, to cut off a bamboo or stick even Pariehum, trans. rarichum, nom, subst.
ori-def.1894: rirummiedda, rarummiedda, riedda, rieddan, rinieddan, inoriieddan, to make a separation. Parieddan, &c. to cause such to be done. Rariedda, a separation. Rarieddan and aijan, the place where the way separates. Rûmmia, as rûmmiedda.
ori-def.1895: a lapse of days. Ratórroa rummies, three days; Masanno rummies, how many days.
ori-def.1896: rinummiel, rarummiel, rila, rilen, riniel, inorilen, to dry skins in the native manner by spreading them out, in the rariel, nom. such stretching out. Pariel, pinariel, papariel, iparila, ipariel, inipariel, to make dry
ori-def.1897: rinum: rarum: riebrieba, same as rummichum, and rûmmisûp.
ori-def.1899: rinummiggo, rarummggo, riggoa, riggoon, riniggo, to turn one's self, or anything  else, from one side to the other; in which sense it agrees with poaried. Also to remove anything from one shoulder or hand to the other: that on which it is laid is roggoan. Pûriggo &c. to cause such to be done. Also to change, as rummiggo o ramied, to change, as rummiggo o ramied, to change one's word. See Mariggo. Riggoriggo, changeableness. from rûmmiggorriggo. Rummiggorriggo, intend. rûmmiggo
ori-def.1900: rinummikak, rarummikak, rukakka, rikûkken, rinikak, inorikakken, to stride. Parikak, pinarikak, paparikak, iparikakka,ipanikak, iniparikak,inoiparikak, &c, to cause to ### to be done. Rarikak, a striding.
ori-def.1901: ri, ra, rarikorikoa, to move backwards and forwards. Parikoriko, tran.
ori-def.1902: rinummiot, rarummiot, riótta, riotten, riniot, inoriotten, to environ, compass. Pariot, pinariot, papa## &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1904: rinummiseries, rarummiseries, riserisa, riserisen, riniseries, inoriserisen, to wash rice or millet. Pûriseries, pinûriseries, papariseris, ipariserisa, ipariseries, inipûriseries, inoipariseries, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1905: rinum: rarum: risûppa, same as rumrnichum. Parisup, transit,
ori-def.1906: rinummomirroom, rammmomirroom, romirroma, romirromen, rinomirroom, inoromirroom, to rinse the mouth. Paromirroom, pi, pa, iparomirroma, ipûromirroom, inipàromirroom, inoiparomirroom, &c. to do so.
ori-def.1907: ri, ra, roggoroggoa, to rumble water between the teeth, as when people wash their mouth, to gurgle
ori-def.1908: rinummomorromo, rammmomorromo, romorromoa, romorromoon, rinomorrómoon, inoromorromoon, to make round. Pûromorromo, pinaromorromo, paparomorromo, iparomorromoa, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1909: rinummonno, rarummonno, rónnoa, ronnoan, rinonnoan, inorónnoan, to overshadow. Paronno, trans. rarosnno, a shadowing.
ori-def.1910: rinummoop, rarummoop, rópa, rópen, rinóop, inoroópen, to shut the eyes. Paróop, pinaroop, paparoop, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1911: ri, ra, ropû, eropa, ineropû, inoeropû, to spit anything out of the mouth, but not spittle, for that is petûmmo. Paropû, trans. raropa, a spitting out.
ori-def.1912: rinummoos, rarûmmoos, rosû, rosen, rinoos, inoroosen. to run after, to pursue. Paroos, pinûroos, papûroos, iparosa, &c. to cause to pursue.
ori-def.1913: rinummorro, rarummorro, rorroa. rorroon, rinorro, inororroon, to call together, to put together, as clothes in a chest, drink in a pot, paddy in a sack, &c. also parorro, see in Parórro. Also to encircle. Rummorronocho, to encircle any one. Parorro, an assembly, act. arórroan, or aroroaijan, a place of assembly.
ori-def.1914: rinummorosûn, rarummorosan, to gasp at the point of death.
ori-def.1915: runrmmorroos, rarummorroos, rorrosa, rorrosen, rinorroos, inororrosen, to collect, to gather. Parorroos, pinarorroos, paparorroos, iparorrosa, iparorroos, to cause to gather.
ori-def.1916: rinummot, rarummot, rotta, rotten, rinot, inorotten, to wrap up anything. Parot, pinarot, paparot, to cause to be wrapped up. Rarot, a wrapper.
ori-def.1917: ri, ra, ruttossa, tuttossen, rinotos, inorotossen, to go against anything, as against the wind, stream, &c. Paûttos, transiti. Rarotos, such a going. Maararotos, such a goer.
ori-def.1918: ri, ra, rotulla, rotullen, rinotul, inorotullen, to take to one's self, and thus to deprive another of anything. or to cause that he has it not. Parotul, trans. rarotul, nom. a depriving. Ma-ararootul, one who deprived.
ori-def.1919: rinumpe, rarumpe, ruppea, rûppein, rienpe, inoruppein, to swallow up, Paarpe, pinâarpe, papûarpe, ipûarpea, &c. to cause to be swallowed up. Raruppe, a swallowing. Rûrâûppe, o man, o micham, the passage where eating and drinking goes thro'.
ori-def.1923: when; sasai o sabûnnojoa mamau oe, when will your father come ?
ori-def.1928: a carp, that is full grown; autobabot, half grown; barobablyi, about a span long; dille o barobabbi, a young carp of a smaller sort.
ori-def.1929: afterwards; sacha a nataap rûmmies, after six days; sacha a nattada eidas, over a month; sacha a natorroa baas, after three years.
ori-def.1930: a screen, to make a shadow.
ori-def.1935: the entrance of a house, including the door and threshold; inaúnûmina jo saide sandon ? talla alla mossei dummora don ? why do you stay at the door? why do you not come in?
ori-def.1937: any unpleasant and stinking smell; anything that stinks, or is nasty, so that the senses loathe it.
ori-def.1938: a house or shed, such as is generally seen in front of native houses
ori-def.1939: the nump of the Indian cow.
ori-def.1940: a row of persons or things, that stand one after the other. Sarró mababat, to go one after the other. Sarro makarieb, ditto. From Pissûrra.
ori-def.1941: persons who come from one family, as Taborron. It must be pronounced sarr-o-don, and means a race, a line. See Pissarra
ori-def.1944: the net that incloses the bowels.
ori-def.1945: mist, damp. Poch-poch a sûrroso, de bonna, the mist in the field. Sarrosoûn, misty.
ori-def.1947: white coral beads, which the young women wear on ther legs. Sabitoi o sasaat, the red corals which they wear about these, Aud tatte opô, those which are worn underneath.
ori-def.1948: and sasosaijan, the place of anything, hence peo sassaian, a dwelling house. Sino saijan, and inosasaijan, this has no other tenses than these three, præsens, praet. and fut. pas. it means also simply a residence. Sasaijan omerien, a work place. Contracted from sasaû merien.
ori-def.1949: praet, pass. sinoainasan, praes. inosaûinas, fût. a look out house: this has no covering, and differs from tarrakal, which has a covering.
ori-def.1952: a ring, such as men wear on the fingers. From Summallan.
ori-def.1954: a sheet, or anything spread out. Sasappo azaijan, a table cloth. Sasûp o ratta, a bed clothes. From summûppa.
ori-def.1958: a claw. From Summoat, or the clawing itself.
ori-def.1959: the measure, where two things with their ends are joined together.
ori-def.1961: a vessel in which people put food to settle, as with us, the skimming dishes.
ori-def.1966: disinclination, dissatisfaction, a murmuring disposition: annûmma sasonos? what do you murmur about?
ori-def.1967: a pot, or cup. Written sasûlan.
ori-def.1968: if: sia moetas a simma, matalam cho alli sasos' i tumkach, if it rain tomorrow, the people will probably not go out to hunt.
ori-def.1970: a marriedman, or one who has: been married: also a father.
ori-def.1972: anything broken off short: the back.
ori-def.1973: anything produced long, the end of a thing. Sies o atzaijan, the end of a table. Sies o bonna, the end of a field. Sies o abas, the end of the sea, where it washes the land. It is not applied to things that have no certain, quantity, like the word sisi, see below.
ori-def.1975: a child, whether boy or girl. Sjiem badda, a boy. Siem maûnuali, "a girl. Sjiem pûrrach, a bastard. Sjiem pattûla, a step son. Sjiem o kakan, a sucking child. Sjiem o siem, a grandchild.
ori-def.1977: sinimida, sasimida, an open space round a village or a field, to keep off fire. Pasida, trans. Sida, such a path.
ori-def.1978: sinimien, sāsimien, sina, sinan, siminan, inosinan, to be in the way between two, to strike in between two ways. Sina osi Ta Cabba inaos, come between me and Cabba. Pûsien, pinasien, papasien, &c. to cause this to be done. Sasien, nom. the name of that which people set between two.
ori-def.1979: sinimikasik, sasimikasik, sikasikka, sikasikken, sinikasik, inosikkasikken, to dangle with the legs or feet, as idle people do to drive away time. Pasikasik, pi. pa. ipûsikasik ka, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1980: sinimikósiko, sikosikoa, sikosikoon, sinikosiko, inosikosikoon, to drill, as people do with pikes. Pûsikossiko, pi. pa. ipasikosikoa, ipûsikosiko, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1981: sinimioch, sasimioch, siocha, siochen, sinioch, inosiochen, to bring before the hand, Pûsioch, pinûsioch, papûsioch, ipasiocha, ipasioch, inipasioch, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1982: sinimipir, sasimipir, sipirra, sipirren, sinipir, inosipirren, to throw the wrong way, or behind one's hand. Pûsipir, pinasipir, papasipir, &c. to cause anything to be thus thrown.
ori-def.1983: sinimisich, sasimisich, sisicha, sisichen, sinisich, inosisichen, to break or flatten anything with the palm of the hand or foot. Sisichen orima ja bart, to crush the musquitoes with the hand. Tapos sisjiem sasai simisich na-a babat donja cho' asjiel, let all the children come and merely rub the flog with their feet. Pasisich, pi. pa. ipûsi sicht, ipasisich, inipasisich, inoipasisich, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1984: sinimiri, sasiniri, sirig, siri-in, siniri, inosiri-in, to bawl out in the native manner. Pasiri, pi, pa. ipasiria, ipa siri, &c. to cause any one to bawl out.
ori-def.1987: sinimitik, sasimitik, sitikka, sitikken, sinitik, to bind anything tight, or to hawl anything tort. Pasitik, pinasitik, papûsitik, ipasitikka, ipasitik, inipasitik, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.1988: the female among beasts: applied: to men, it means a married woman, who has had children: or who is become old: in which case also an unmarried woman is called sini.
ori-def.1989: a certain bird, from which quills are obtained:
ori-def.1990: the end of anything; sisia oetas, the end of the rain: sisia makarieb, the end of traveling: sisia patite, the end of speaking: sisia tämmäap, the end of working.
ori-def.1991: the sun, a day: written zijs-ja.
ori-def.1992: a place where the grass is eaten of, and is now bare.
ori-def.1996: the darkness and storminess of the sky in the east: see summoloch.
ori-def.1997: a pestle, with which people beat paddy out of the stalk.
ori-def.1999: a sickness consisting of: rotten teeth.
ori-def.2001: sinu bach, sasumbach, sabûcha, sabachen, sienbach, inosabach, to administer a certain poison, called sasabach. Pāsabach, pinäsabach, papāsabach, &c. to cause to be poisoned.
ori-def.2002: sinûmbo, sasumbo, iseboa, isebo, inisebo, inoisebo, to set anything down. Pûsebo, pinasebo, papasébo, ipûseboa, &c. to cause anything to be set down.
ori-def.2003: sinumkir, sasumkir, isekirra, inisekir, inoisekir, to press down. Sûmkir orarro, to dip in the water; to put the hat on firmly, or to press it down. Pûsekir, pinûsekir, papasekir, ipasekirra, &c. to cause such to be done. Sûmkir i tono cho, to dip a person in the water. Sasekir i tono christan, Christian Baptism.
ori-def.2004: sekirran, sienkirrah, inosikirran, the making up of the betel nut. Pasekir, pi. pa. &c. as above.
ori-def.2005: sinummaam, sasāmmaam, saamma, saammen, sinaam, inosaammen, to entangle or entrap. Pāsaam, pl. pa. 1pasaamma, lpasaa, Inlpasaam, &c. to cause to be entrapped.
ori-def.2006: siniammabas, sasāmmabas, sabassa, sabassen, sinabas, inosabas sen, to try, to tempt, to make a trial. Pasabas, pinasabas, papasabas, ipasa bassa, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2007: a trial, a temptation. Ma-asasabas, a tempter, one who tries.
ori-def.2008:
si. sa.. imp. Sabadda, to arrange anything in rows, as fields, trees,
streets, plants, &c. Pasabad, trans.
ori-def.2009: si. Sa. Pasabougarro, trans, a certain manner of binding, as if it were braided.
ori-def.2010: sinummabot, sasummabot, sabotta, sabotten, sinabot, inosabotten, to do anything by guess, to guess at anything. Sümmabot osſimmot, to point out or lay out anything by guess.
ori-def.2011: sinummabsab, sasāmmabsab, Sabsabba, Sabsabben, sinabsab, inosabben, to whip, to beat any one openly. Pasabsab, pi. pa. ipûsabsabba, ipasabsab, &c. to causesuch to be done. Sasûbsab, such a blow, also the instru-ment, as a stick, &c.
ori-def.2012: sinummada, sasāmmada, sadda, Saddan,sinadda,inosaddan, to seek. Pasadda, pi. pa. &c. to cause to seek.
ori-def.2013: sinämmadich-iboch,sasummadich-iboch, sadaudich-ibocha, Sadaudich-iboch, sinadaudichiboch, inosadaudichiboch, to be hungry, to desire anything as hungry. Pasadich iboch, pi. pa, ipûsadich-ibocha, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2014: sinämmakimotto, Sasummakimotto, Sakimottoa, Sakimottoan, sinakimottoûn, inosakimottoûn, to make anything cross-wise, or with a cross Pāsakimotto, pi, aipasakimottoa, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2015: simummaksak, sasunamaksak, saksakka, saksakken, sitûksak, inosaksakken, to trample, to tread, to tread down. Pasaksak, pi, pa ipasak sakka, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2016: &c. the breaking forth of the morning in the east, Summaksak abajan, it dawns in the east.
ori-def.2017: sinum malla, sasunimalla, sal. la-a, Salla-an, sipalla, indsalla-an, to deceive with words or actions. Pasalla, pinasalla, papāsalla, ipûsalla, inipûsalla, incipasalla, to cause to be cheated,
ori-def.2018:
sinummallaban, sasāmmallaban, sallabānna, sallabannan, sinallabannan, inosallabannan, that which makes a shadow, (as an umbrella, &c.) to overshadow any one orthing. Pûsalaban, pinäsalaban, papasallaban, ipûsallabanna, ipasallaban,
to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2019: sinum mallad, sasāmniallad, salladda, salladden, sinallad, inosûl ladden, to discover, to be aware of. Pasallad, pinasallat, papasallat, ipasalladda, &c. to cause to be discovered.
ori-def.2020: si. Sa.. imp. Samgeanna, pass. samgeannen, sinamgean, to offer, is originally a Chinese word, but a dopted by the Formosan and declined after their manner. Samgean, offering.
ori-def.2021: si. Sa. Samoa, Samoan, &c. to twist, a three fold cord. Pasamo, tran.
ori-def.2022: sinum mallan, sasummallan, sallanna, Sallannan, sinallanan, inosallanan, to put a ring on the hand. Pasallan, pi. pa. &c. to cause to be done.
ori-def.2023: imp. Sammisamma, Sam misamman, &c. to crown. Pasammi san. Sammisam, a crown, garland: sasammisam, a crowning, Ma-asasammisam, a crown maker.
ori-def.2024: sinummannasanna, Sasummannasannā, sinannasanna, san, nasanna, sannasamnûan, sinannasanna, inosannasamaan, to hiss at. Pasannasanna, pi. pa. ipasannasanna, inipasannasanna, &c. to cause to be hissed.
ori-def.2025: sinummaod, Sasummaod, saodda, sinaod, inosaodden, to pour out, either on purpose, or by accident. PaSaod, pinasaod, papasaod, ipasaodda, &c. to cause to be poured out. Masaod, neutr. see in M. the acti. of which is Pasaod. Sasaod, a pouring out.
ori-def.2026: sinummapar, sasummapar, Saparra, saparran, sinoparran, to grasp anything furiously, as those do who fear that it will escape them. Naa sinumpar o masarro, I have seized a young hind. Pasapar, pi. pa. ipasapara, ipasapar, &c. to cause to be thus seized.
ori-def.2027: sinummapiel, sasummapiel, sapilla, sapillan, sinapil. inosapilan, to set down on the ground, without stool, mat, or other article. Pasapil, pinasa pil, papasapil, ipasapilla, ipasapil, ini pasapil, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2028: sinum mappa, sasunmapp sappa and Sappaja, sapanni, Sinapanni, inosapanni, to overspread. Pasappa, pi. pa. ipasappaija, ipāsappa, inipasap pa, to cause to be overspread.
ori-def.2029: sinuumara, Sasummara, sar ra, Sarranni, sinaranni, inisaranni, to lie down in order to sleep. Pasarra, pi. pa. ipăsarra, inipăsarra, inoipăsarra, to cause to lie down to sleep.
ori-def.2031: si, sa, to plait a rope of straw, i. e. from double. Saramoa, Sa ramoar, &c. Pasaramo, to cause such is be done. Sasûramo, a plaiting. a-asaromo, one who plaits.
ori-def.2032: Sinummar-O-asso, SaSu In mar-o-asso, to Seethe. Pasaro asso, pi. ps, sc. to cause to be seethed.
ori-def.2033: sinum marp, Sasummarp, sarpen, sinarp, inosarpen, the burning And singeing of fire. Pasarp, pinäsarp, papasarp, pasarpa, pasarp, Impasarp, the fire singeing or burning anything.
ori-def.2034: si. Sa. Sarriesa, sarriesen, simarries, inosarriesen, to lace, to string. Pasarries, tran. Sarries, thread.
ori-def.2035: sinum marroso, sasummarroso, to grow foggy or damp. Pasarroso, pl. pa. ipasarrosoa, ipûsarroso, imipûsarroso, to cause the same.
ori-def.2038: siuûmmasjien, sasummasjien, Sasjima, Sasinan, Sinasinan, inosasinan, to notch, to make a notch, to make teeth. Pasasien, pinasasien, papasasien, ipasasina, &c. to cause to be notched. Sasasjien, the notching.
ori-def.2039: sinûmmaso, sasummaso, sasoa, sasoan, sinasoan, inosasoa, to swim. Pasaso, see above in Pa.
ori-def.2040: sinummasoom, sasummasoom, isasoma, isasoom, inisasoom, inoisûsoom, to join together, so that the ends come together, but not over or in each other. Pasasoom, &c.
ori-def.2041: sinummasi, sasummasi, sasi, sasian, sinasian, inosasian, to mix salt, as people do in food when it is being cooked, or after it is dressed, but is too insipid. Pasasi, trans. Sasi, salt. nom.
ori-def.2042: si. sa. the shaking of the ground. Sasio, nom. earthquake.
ori-def.2043: sinûmmatsat, sasummatsat, satsatta, satsatten, sinatsat, inosatsatten, to forge, as a smith. Pasatsat, pi. pa. ipûsatsatta, ipasatsat, inipûsatsat, inoipasatsat, to cause to be forged.
ori-def.2044: sinûmmedo, sasummedo, siddoa, siddóon, siendo, inosiddóon, to feel.
ori-def.2045: sinummatta, sasummatta, summattan, sinummattan, inosummattan, to eat food raw and undressed, or alone and without mixing with other food, (as flesh without rice, or rice without any additions.) Pasummatta, pinasummatta, papasûmmatta, ipasummatta, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2046: si. sa. sealla, pass. seûllan,  sineal, inoseûllen, to spy an enemy. Passeal, tran. Saseal, a spying.
ori-def.2047: si. sa. seitta, seitten, sineit, inoseitten, to pinch, to join, i. e. under, as pillik, but between two is lummabit.
ori-def.2048: sinummerik, sasummerik, sirka, sirken, sinirka, inosirken, to press, squeeze, or wring out. Pûsirk, pi. pa. pinûsirk, papasirk, &c. to cause such to be done. Summerik o loan, to milk the cows.
ori-def.2049: (the e short) si. sa, sitton, ***toan, sinittoan, inosittoan, to limp, **ûmmotul. Pasito, trans. Sasito, a limping. Ma-asasitto, one who limps.
ori-def.2050: sinummis, sasummis, sissa, ***sen, sinis, inosissan, to sew, also to stitch, in which case it is sissan, **san, inosissan: also to backstiteh, in which case it is isis, misis, ino***, **sis, pinasis, papasis, ipasi***, ip***, inipasis, to cause to be sewed.
ori-def.2051: si. sa. siksikka, siksikkan, siniksik, inosiksikken, to button tight, also summiksik. Pasiksik, trańs.**iksik, a buttoning, Ma-asasiksik, one who buttons.
ori-def.2052: si. sa. soalla, soûllen, sinoal, *nosoallen, to remind of an old promise or debt. Pasoal, trans.
ori-def.2053: sinûmmoûsoap, sasûm*oûsoap, soasoûppa, soa-asappen, si*oasoap, inosoasoàp, to do anything blindly and by feeling.
ori-def.2054: sinûmmoat, sasûmmoat, soût-*a, soûtten, sinoat, insoatten, to pull up and remove the weeds with which the *ice fields are covered by means of a *ook or hoe. Pasoat, pinasoat, papaso*t, ipûsoat, inipasoat, inoipà-oat, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2055: si. sa. imp. sógoa, to bind two ends, as of string, rattan, &c. one over the other and thus to lengthen. Paso-*go, trans.
ori-def.2056: sinummokar, sasummokar, *let the o be scarcely heard) isokarra, *sokar, inisokar, inoisokar, to push away from one. Also to drive on people and urge them to do that which they are disposed to. Summaloso, si. sa. salosoa, salosoan, sinalósoan, ino*alosoan, to drive on and urge. Pasa*o*o, &c. Summekar o chan, to stir up the fire. Pasokar, pinasokar, papasokar, ipûsokarra, ipasokar, inipasokar, inoipasokar, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2057: sinûmmoes, sasûmmoes, to grow, to increase, to become great. Pasoes, pinasoes, papasoes, ipasoesa, ipasoes, inipasoes, to cause to grow.
ori-def.2058: sinûmmokad, sasummokad, sokadda, sokadden, sinokad, inosokadden, to push or kick with the foot. Pasokad, pinasokad, papasokad, ipasokadda, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2059: sinummokko, sasummokko, sokkoa, sokkoon, sinokko, inosokkoon, to push or thrust any one with a stick, poker, sword, &c. also to point with the finger. Pasokko, pi. pa. ipasokkoa, ipasokko, &c. to cause to be pushed.
ori-def.2060: sinummook, sasummook, soka, soken, sinook, inosoken, to kick with the foot behind. Pasook, pi. pa. ipûsoka, &c to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2061: sinûmmokkosokko, sasummokkosokko, sokkosokkoa, sokkosokkoon, sinokkosokkoon, inosokko-sokkoon, to push frequently as above, summokkosokko no zido, to churn. Pasokkosokko, inipasokkosokko, inoipasokkosokko, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2062: sinûmmoloch, sasummoloch, the threatening, drawing together of the clouds, over the hills, when the eastern quarter is set in for rain and thunder, as frequently in the southeast monsoon, takes place towards evening. Pûsoloch, pinûsoloch, papûsoloch, ipa-solocha, ipasoloch, to occasion such.
ori-def.2063: sinûmmóoso, sasummooso, soossoa, sóossoon, sinosso, inosoossoon, to follow up, to trace. Pû-oosso, pinasoosso, papûsoosso, ipasoossoa, ipasoosso, to cause to be followed up.
ori-def.2064: sinummopat, sasummopat, sopatta, sopatten, sinopat, inosopatten, to be over against, to do anything in opposition. Pasopat, pinasopat, papû-sopat, &c. to cause such to be done. Sasopat over againt: this word is joined with karri and mau, as (karri-sasopat) and means to be over against each other: thus karrisasopat patodon, to live opposite to each other. Summapat o meroos, o pattite, to sit or speak one over against the other.
ori-def.2065: sinummopisop, sasummopisop, sopisoppa, sopisoppen, sinópisop, to stroke or smooth with the hand, also to level, see Masopisóp. Pasopisop, pi. pa. ipûsopisop, in ipûsopisop, to cause to be stroked.
ori-def.2066: si. sa. suppoa, to put up in heaps, as is done with the paddy after it is cut down in the field. Pasuppo, to cause such to be done. Suppo, a heap of corn, such as is seen in the fields, in the time of harvest.
ori-def.2067: sinûmmoso, sasùmmoso, sosoa, sosoon, sinoso, to roast. Pasoso, pi. pa. ipasosoa, to cause to be roasted. Sasoan and sasosoaijan, a roaster or spit with which people roast.
ori-def.2068: sinummosa, sasummosa, sósasosanni and sosaijan, inososanni and sinososaijan, inososanni and inososaijan, inososanni and inososaijan, to dwell, to inhabit. Pasosa, pi. pa. ipasosa, &c. to cause to inhabit.
ori-def.2069: sinummas, sasummas, s***, sassan, sinas, inosassan, to put food to settle, as people do in a skimming dish. Pasas, pinasas, papasas, ipasassa, &c. to cause to settle.
ori-def.2070: sinummot, sasummot, sotta, sotten, sinot, inosotten, to point towards, either with the finger, or musket, arrow, sword, &c. Pasot, pinasot, papasot, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2071: sinûmpo, sasumpo, suppoa, suppoan, sienpon, inosuppoan, to help, to lend a hand in any work, as Molliol. Pasuppo, pi. pa. ipasuppoa, ipasûppo, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2072: a particle prefixed to all proper names of men, as Ta Cabba, Ta Bai, &c.
ori-def.2073: territory, land or dwelling place; the common road or street, the ground.
ori-def.2075: a snare, for catching wild beasts.
ori-def.2076: tsi. tat. imp. taamen o rapisa, pas. taamen o rapies, tsinaamen o rapies, inotaamen o rapies, to beg, to demand anything without shame, nom. Ma-ataamen o rapies a beggar.
ori-def.2079: a family sprung from one stock, relations.
ori-def.2081: a place where no water settles, when it rains. Matabtab, the verb.
ori-def.2084: shrimps that are taken in fresh water; also teor, a large kind; rauno, a small kind of shrimps, which are found in salt water, Aûan, very small shrimps.
ori-def.2086: an instrument with which people pull down earth
ori-def.2087: a sole, a sort of fish
ori-def.2088: a head band, such as the women wear.
ori-def.2090: the upper part of a man or beast
ori-def.2092: certain cross bamboos placed above the entrance of the door of a house, on the inside.
ori-def.2093: a cable, from takkat and arrat. See takkar, and gûmmûrgar.
ori-def.2094: a vein. Compounded of tagga and oggach.
ori-def.2095: zinûggogon, tataggogon, to thrist. Pataggogan, pinûtaggogan, p*pataggogan, ipûtaggoganna, to cause to thrist. Toggogon, nom. thrist.
ori-def.2096: a kind of beads, much esteemed by the natives.
ori-def.2098: an anchor, a post to which people moor a boat at a ferry.
ori-def.2100: exceeding, excellent, as talcho mabarra, talcho matadach, exceeding strong, uncommonly hot.
ori-def.2101: one who excels, or surpasses might, wealth, beauty, &c.
ori-def.2102: what? with indignation. Talla *mmara imónos, what* do you lie * rags?
ori-def.2104: o no adda, a grain of rice.
ori-def.2105: o noeno, the brain pan: written *lao-n-oeno.
ori-def.2108: continual perseverance. Tal-*hon sisa, the whole day. Tûllachon *n, micham, mababat, to be constant-eating, drinking, going, &c.
ori-def.2113: a particle of admiration, as ah! * that!
ori-def.2115: Takeis, a cart. Go-or, or *or. Tateûrraû loan, the poles of a *t. Asasûû loan, the yoke.
ori-def.2119: all kinds of pollution, as from snot, grease, &c.
ori-def.2120: anything defiled with tar, see below.
ori-def.2121: a thronback, of which there are two sorts, tarra boetsina, a thronback: tarra paga aubaas, a fish somewhat resembling the shark, with a broad blotch on the nose.
ori-def.2123: tsi. tat. the trickling of the eye. Patarra-ie-ra-ien, transit.
ori-def.2124: a small hut, standing highm in which the natives frequently sleep; such as are beside their houses, or in the fields.
ori-def.2125: a way; mitarom' o taran, two roads that meet together. Rariedda **ran, a way that divides into two.
ori-def.2130: tsinarran, inotûrran: and **ban, inarriban, inoarriban: and rib**jen, rinibaijen, inoribaijen. Seems ** mean loathsome, or hurtful. Thus people speak of unusual food, arriban o ** macha ja micho. It is possible that it ** injurious or deadly. But these words require to be more carefully examined.
ori-def.2131: zinûssaban, inotassaban, to hunger. Pûtassaban, pinûtassaban, pa-pûtassaban, ipûtassabanna, to cause to hunger. Nom. Tassaban, hunger.
ori-def.2132: tsinassinan, inotassinan, tassioa, to do anything for any one. Inatassinan ja rûmmozi-daû tamau, I will pay for my father. In the 2nd and 3rd person people do not say Tassinan, but Tassi. It is necessary that this word be examined. It is to be written tas-ina, just as daû-ina, for me; so also tasi-je, for you; tas-icho, for him. Præt. tsinas. fut. inosas, imp. tas ioa, sie d'r fas joa ina, take my place.
ori-def.2133: that which is new and untried. Is said of all implements, that people are accustomed to use, as clothes, cups, dishes, &c.
ori-def.2134: (the o short) long, is only used of lifeless things.
ori-def.2136: a particle wherewith people enquire after any place, as dema tassone Doubale, whither does Daubale lead to? Tassono don o Batsjekan, whereabouts are the houses of Batsjekan? Dema tassono Taijoan, which is the way to Taijoan? Tassono aisi, that way.
ori-def.2137: all kinds of implements that people use for house buildings or agriculture.
ori-def.2140: the ropes wherewith the deer are encircled in hunting.
ori-def.2142: instrument for stabbing, as a sword, knife, &c.
ori-def.2143: a dance, also the trampling of those who are about to fight.
ori-def.2144: and a-obog, both words of reservem when people do not dare to mention scandalous persons.
ori-def.2148: the first, the principal. Tummabach, and Matattabach, verb to, be the first.
ori-def.2156: a covering, a pavilion, a cord.
ori-def.2158: that with which people tread, as the feet. From tummallan.
ori-def.2161: the sting of anything that stings with the tail.
ori-def.2162: that wherewith we compose any one. From Tummalûttala.
ori-def.2163: that wherewith people cover themselves in order to perspire freely. From tummallumtum.
ori-def.2166: the shaft of an arrow, the stem of a spit.
ori-def.2167: a number. Masanno attoch, the larger number. From Tûmmoch.
ori-def.2175: a key. Tatto o chirrap, a toothpick. From tûm-o.
ori-def.2177: an instrument, wherewith ** to sprinkle water. From tummos.
ori-def.2179: the end where anything is broken off or torn. But especially pr**o extremitate membri virilis id quod e**st inhonestum.
ori-def.2180: the ornaments worn in the ears.
ori-def.2181: an offer, by the natives. a hard stone: from tummotto.
ori-def.2182: tattose, and tattosik, a lie. From tummorik, tummose, &c.
ori-def.2184: a wisp of straw, with which people make a smoke, to drive away the musquitos.
ori-def.2186: a number reckoned beforehand. From tumpuch.
ori-def.2188: a sort of fruit, conically shaped.
ori-def.2189: a kind of vegetable, which is cooked with the food.
ori-def.2193: all sorts of prepared food, whether fish or flesh.
ori-def.2195: a pencil to paint with. Taz-ipok o bido, a pen.
ori-def.2196: a pin or peg, on which to hang anything.
ori-def.2199: the pole or the upper part of the forehead.
ori-def.2201: a stalk, to which the fruit is attached, whether standing in the field, or already reaped.
ori-def.2202: is said of thous who strike every one. Eirreken, idem. Written teteen.
ori-def.2203: a sort of fish, called stone bream.
ori-def.2205: blindness of one eye, so that the white of the eye cannot be seen. for then it is tollas.
ori-def.2206: one who is blind of one eye, this is the præs. from tummillik.
ori-def.2207: before, with respect to place. Talla zummada zinoe, ka oa tinnûam ai, what do you seek, it lies there before you. Matatinnûan, mi. ma. forwards. Patatinnûam, trans.
ori-def.2215: a hole, a door, a window. From tummochab, tattochab, an opening.
ori-def.2216: zinochorochen, tatochoróchen, to be set a coughing.
ori-def.2229: tsi. tat. imp. tara, pass. ta-an, tsina, inota-an, the reading of a list. Pata-a, tran. nom. tattûa, the reading aloud; and Maatttata-a, one who reads the roll.
ori-def.2230: a sort of reed, of which men make arrows.
ori-def.2232: we, us. But differs from namo.
ori-def.2234: the same sort of flute; very long.
ori-def.2236: the top or upper part of anything.
ori-def.2237: blindness of one eye, but so that the white can be seen.
ori-def.2238: tsi. tat. tosasjiena, pas. tosa-sjienen, tsinosasjien, &c. to have the tooth-ache. Tos-asji, the tooth-ache.
ori-def.2239: tsi. tatsi. tsibarasabasûa, to aim at drectly, as tsimisi.
ori-def.2240: tsini. tatsi, tsianna, &c. see in Zimianna, to be distrustful.
ori-def.2241: tsini. tatsi. itsijka, itsijk, initsijk, inoitsijk, to filli p, to make a point thus [.] nom. tattsik, a tittle point. See zimiek, under Tummesik, ditto.
ori-def.2242: tsini. tatsi. &c. see under in Z.
ori-def.2243: tsini. tatsi. tsikia, to leer, to leok askance. Patsiek, trans. tatsiki, nom. Ma-atatsiki.
ori-def.2244: tsi. tats. tsikoa, pass. tsikoan, tsiniko, inotsikoon, to tight a house that hangs over. Patsiko, trans. nom.
ori-def.2245: tsini. tatsi. tsimisa, tsimisan, tsinimisan, inotsimisan, to take some food, to taste. Paksimi, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2246: tsi. tat. tsipisiepa, pass. tsipisiepen, tsimipsiep, inotsitsiepen, to suck (but not the breast) as a finger, tobacco pipe, &c. Patsiptsiep, trans. Tatsiptsiep, a sucking. Ma-atatsip-tsiep, a sucker. Tsiptsiepan, that of which men suck, as a tobacco pipe, &c.
ori-def.2249: tsini. tatsi. tsijtsijsa, to cut off the joint of wood or bamboo.
ori-def.2250: west. Matatsip, mi, ma, weatherly. Patatsip, trans.
ori-def.2251: tsinumbar, tatumbar, tubarra, tubarren, tsienbar, inotubbarren, to set one's-self down fast, as those do who fear being pushed away. Pûtûbbar, panatûbbar, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2252: tsinûmboel, tatûmboel, tubboela, tubboelen, tsienboel, inotubboelen, to seek any one. Patubboel, pinatubboel, papatubboel, ipatubboela, ipatubboel, &c. to cause to be sought. Tattubboel, nom. henve kar tattubboel, mau tattubboel.
ori-def.2253: tsinumcho, tatumcho, tûchoa, let the u be scarcely heard) tuchoan, **enecho, inotuchoon, to bow, Patû-**o, pi. pa. ipatuchoa. to cause to bow.
ori-def.2254: tsi. tat. tóchoa, the commencement of the north monsoon. Provb. **choa ja masias sai don ja dalij ma*roos ja badda, they use this pro**b, because the young men do not **rry unless in the cold season.
ori-def.2255: tsi. tat. tikka, &c. (let the u be scarcely heard) to support, to prop up.
ori-def.2256: pi. pa. ipatukka, &c. to cause support. Tattûkka, nom. a prop.
ori-def.2257: zinumkach, tatumkach, tuk-**cha, tukkachen, zienkach, inotuk-**chen, to hunt deer by concealing one's-self in the holes, and behind the edges. Patukkach, pinûtukkach, pa*ukkach, &c. to cause to hunt.
ori-def.2258: zinummaam, tatummaam, ta-*, tûmen, zinaam, inotamen, to an-*er. Pûtaam, pinûtaam, papataam, **tama, &c. to cause to answer.
ori-def.2259: tsinummaap, tatummaap, ta-*tapen, tsinaap, inotapen, to do all kinds of work, either in the house or in the field. Also to attack, to fall upon. **maap, husbandry, &c. passiv. pret. tataap, work, labour. Ma-atataap, a worker, a labourer.
ori-def.2260: zinummaas, tatummaas, tasutasan, zinasan, inotûsan, to begin, to do anything first, to be follwed by another. Pataas, pi. pa. ipatasa, ipataas, inipataas, to cause to begin, &c.
ori-def.2261: zinummabba, tatummabba, tabba, tabbaan, zinubba, inotabbaan, to stick. Patabba, pinûtabba, papatabba, ipatabba, &c. to cause to stick.
ori-def.2262: tsi. tat. imp. tabacha, pass. tabachen, tsinabach, inotabachen, to do anything first; see also matattabach. Patabach, trans. to cause to be done. Tattabach, nom. a commencement.
ori-def.2263: zinummabbak, tatummabbak, tabakka, tabakken, zinabakkan, inotabakkan, to dance, also the swaggering of those who fight, or who wish to fight. Pûtabbak, pinatabbak, papatabbak, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2264: zinummachal, tatummachal, tachalla, tachallen, zinachal, inotachallen, to remove the earth, as with a hoe, a spade, &c. It is changed into d see dummachol. Padachal, pinûdachal, papadachal, &c. to cause to be dug up.
ori-def.2265: zinummabbis, tatummabbis, tabbisa, tabbisan, zinabbisan, inotabbisan, to fan. Patabbis, pinatabbis, papatabbis, ipatabbisa, ipatabbis, inipatabbis, inoipatabbis, to cause to fan.
ori-def.2266: zinummach-il, tatummach-il, tach-illa, tach-illen, to win, to win a bet. Patach-il, pinatach-il, papatach-il, ipatach-illa, ipatach-il, inoipatach-il, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2267: tsi. tat. tach-oa. same as pazinado; mautadacj-o, idem patacho, nom. tattacho, interpretation, intercession. Ma-atattacho, an interpreter, an interceder.
ori-def.2268: zinummachum, tatummachum, tachumma, tachumman, zinachumman, inotachumman, to put on one's hat, to cover one's head. Patachum, pinatachum, papatachum, ipatachumma, &c. to cause the hat to be put on. Tattachum, the thing put on, (namely the hat.) Tummakkum, tsi. tat. imp. takumma, part. takkumman, &c. means all kinds of covering.
ori-def.2269: tsi. tat. tachossan, tsinachossan, inotachossan, grass, &c. to cut off. Patachos, also chummoschos.
ori-def.2270: tsinummagcha, tatummagcha, tagcha, tagchaan, zinagcha, ino*agchaan, to chop, to hack to hew. Patatagcha, pi. pa. ipatagcha, inipatagcha, to cause to be chopped.
ori-def.2271: zinummagcho, tatummagcho, tagcho, to overhang, not to stand upright: It is sometime changed in d, which see. Padagcho, pinadagch*, dagchoa, dagchoon, zinagcho, inodachoon, to cause to overhang: in which case it is ipadagchoa, ipadagcho, &c.
ori-def.2272: zinummagchoch, tatu*nmagchoch, tagchocha, tagchochen, zinagchoch, inotagchochen, to scoop. Tummagchoch o bigeno, to skim, to scoop off the forth. Patagchoch, ** natagchoch, papatagchoch, ipatagchocha, inipatagchoch, to cause to scoop. Tummagchoch o tono malla, to l*** water with a bucket.
ori-def.2273: zinummairs, tatummairs, **isa, taisan, zinaisan, inotaisan, to climb up. Tummaies i kittas, to climb up a ladder. Pûtaies, pinûtaies, papa***, ipataisa, ipataies, inipataies, inoip**ies, to cause to climb.
ori-def.2274: tsi. tat. taiba, to do anything together, or in company. P** &c. to cause such to be done. ** comes aurri a teiba, that is the ** money given when people work together, as if they said, aúrëdda a teiba, so that this noun seems to come from moriedda and tummûiba, to work together. For they say also, Moriëdda o taiba, and Moribal o taibe, to leave offm to cease such working together.
ori-def.2275:
zinummakal,tatummakal, ta kalla, takallan, zinûkallan, inotakal
lan, to put on a woman's head-band. Pûtakal, pinûtakal, papûtûkal, ipatakalla, &c. to cause such to be done. Written dummakal.
ori-def.2276:
zinummakas, fatummakas, takassa, takassan, inotakassan, to stop any one in the road, or to turn him out of the way. Patakas, pinatakas, papûtakas, ipûtakassa, ipatakas, &c.
to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2277: zinummakkis, tatummakkis, taksa, taksen, zinaksan, inotaksan, to stick together, and make one. Patakis, pi. pa. ipûtaksa, ipûtakkis, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2278: zinummakkoob, tatummûkkoob, takkoba, takkoban, zinakkoban, inotakkoban, to cover, to cover entirely. Tûmmakkoob o macha, to blind the eyes. Parakkoob, pi. pa. ipaipatakkoba, &c. to cause to be covered. Also to cover with a rug.
ori-def.2279: zinummala, tatummala, talûtûlanm zinala, inotalan, to find, ro welcome. Patala, pinatala, papûtala, ipûtala, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2280: zinummalattala, tatnmmalattala, tallattala, tallattalan, zinalattalan, inotallattalan, to pacify, to still, to calm all sorts of emotions. Patalattala. pi*atalattala, papûtalattala, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2281: zinummalas. tatummalas, talassa, talassen, zinalassen, inotallassen, to tread under foot. Patallas, pinûtallas, papûtallas, ipatallassa, ipatallas, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2282: zinummalizi, tatummalizi, talizia, talizian. zinalizian, inotalizian, to dance. Patalizi, pinatalizi, papûtalizi, ipatalizia, &c. to cause to dance. Sometimes the t is changed into d, see dummalizi.
ori-def.2283: zinummalpon, tatummalpon, talponna, talponnan, zinalponnan, inotalponnan, to betake one's seld any where, or set forward. Also to stir one's self up, and exert one's strength. **talpou, pi. pa. ipûtalponna, ipatalpon, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2284: zinummallo, tatummallo, talloa, talloon, zinalloon, inotalloon, to allure, to bait. Patallo, pinatallo, papatallo. &c. to cause to allure.
ori-def.2285: zinummattal, tatummattal, tattallan, zinattal, inotattallan, to trample with feet. Pûtattal, pinatattal, papatattal, ipatattalla, ipatattal, inipa- &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2286: zinummallumtum, tatummallumtum, inotallumtum, to cover up one's self or another in order to produce perspiration. Patallumtum, pi. pa. ipatallumtumma, &c.
ori-def.2287: zinummanna, tatummanna, tanna, tanuaan, zinanna, inotannaan, to open. Tanna osja chachab o donoe, open the door of the house. Patanna, pi. pa. ipatanna, &c. to cause to open. Tattannanna o parara, an opening to let ** light, that is, a window.
ori-def.2288: zinummao, tatummao, taoa, taoan, zinaoan, inotaoan, to sprinkle, as with water, salt thin m*d, &c. but to cover wood, stone, and other thhings that do not spread is magga. Wherewith * itaoon, inoitaoon. Patao, pinatao, papatao, ipatatoa, ipatao, inipatao, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2289: zinummammoos, tatummammoos, itammosa, itammoos, initammoos, inoitammoos, to crumble, to shred. Patammoos, pi. pa. ipat*mmosa. ipatammoos. &c. to cause such to be done. Tummammoos, means to stick anything in the mouth.
ori-def.2290: zinummapacha, tatummapacha, tapacha, tapachanni, and tapachaiyan, zinapachanni and zinapachayan. inotapachanni and inotapachayan, to put on one's breeches. Patapacha, pi. pa. &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2291: tsi. tat. tapalla, tapallan, tninapal, inotapallan, to stumble in the way. Patapal, trans. nom. tattapal.
ori-def.2292: zinummapies, tatummapies, tapisa. tapisen. zinapies, inotapisen, to beat with a stick, as people do their their clothes, in order to knock dust or dirt. Patapies, zinatapies, papatapies, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2293: zinummapitapies, tatummapitapies, inotapitapisen, to beat with many strokes. Patapitapies, pi. pa. &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2294: tsi. tat. tara, taran, tsirara, inotaran, to choose anything first: as tummar' o mioa, tummar o mammali balach, to choose to cut down a field; to choose a lady. Patara, trans. ta*ara, a choice. Hence karri tatta-a, mau tat-ta-a, to choose one another.
ori-def.2295: zinummarad, tatummarad, taradda, taradden, zinarad, inotaradden, to gather up what another has scattered, as rice thrown over the floor. Patarad, pi. pa. ipataradda, ipatarad, &c. to cause wuch to be done.
ori-def.2296: tsi. tat. tamaramarra, tamaramarren, tsinaramar, inotaramarren, to be here and there, separated from one another, some here and some there. Pataramar, trans. such a scattering.
ori-def.2297: tsi. tat. taratralla, to wave as grass, plants, and other little things do, &c. differs from lummitallito. Parakal, trans.
ori-def.2298: same as dummarau. Patarau, pi. pa. ipataraua, &c. as Padarau.
ori-def.2299: same as dummaraudau. Patarautau. pi. pa. same as padaraudau.
ori-def.2300: tsi. tat. tariesa, to intercept any one in his way. Pataries, trans. Tummariës o azies, to intercept the enemy. Nom. tattariës, an intercepting. Ma-atattaries, a hard runner, who overtakes another.
ori-def.2301: zinummaroggi, tatummaroggi, taroggia, taroggian. zinaroggian, inotaroggian, to change things which are so much alike that they can be easily mistaken one for the other, and this with intent to deceive. Pataroggi, pinataroggi, papataroggi, ipataroggia, &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2302: tsi. tat. taromman, tsinaromman, inotaromman, to betray. Pataromma, trans. tattaromma, treachery. Hence karri-tattaromma, mautattanom-ma. Ma-atattaromma, a traitor.
ori-def.2303: zinummaroob, tatummaroob, tarroba, tarroban, zinarroban, inotarroban, to cover as people do the head with a fan, to pretect them from sun or rain: thus not entirely covered. Or to cover with a rug or such like in which it differs from tummakkoob. Tatarroob, pi. pa. ipatarroba, &c. to cause to cover.
ori-def.2304: tsi. tat. imp. tarossa, to pick anything here and there, just as people pluck the ripe ears in a field. Patarros, trans.
ori-def.2305: zinummassal, tstummassal, *assalla, tassallen, sinassal, inotassal*en, to catch at once, to apprehend. Patassal, pi. pa. ipatassalla, &c. to cause such to be done. Tattasal, nom.
ori-def.2306: zinummassin, tatummassin, *assina, tassin, zinassin, inotassin, to entertain any one. Patassin, pi. pa. *patassin, inipatassina, inoipatassin, to cause such to be done. Tattassin, *n expectation, hope.
ori-def.2307: zinummatas, tatummatas, ta*asa, tatasan, zinatas, inotatasan, to fathom. Patatas, pi. pa. ipatatasa, &c. to cause to be fathomed. Tatas, a fathom.
ori-def.2308: zinummatta, tatummatta, tat-*a, tittan, zinattan, inotattan, to stamp *eed out of the husk. Patatta, pi. pa. patatta, inipatatta, inoipatatta, to cause to be stamped out. Tatta, a *ice stamper.
ori-def.2309: zinummattam, tatummattam, tattamma, tattammen, zinattam, *notattammen, to hold fast. Patattam, pi. pa. ipatattamma, ipatattam, &c. to cause to hold fast.
ori-def.2310: zinummau-aab, tatummau-aab, tauba and taûmasan, taûba and *aûmasan, tsinauaban and tsinauma*an, inotaulan and inotaumasan, to do anything first or before another, whether drinking, speaking, or tasting. Patau-aab, pi. pa. ipatauaba, ipatauaab, &c. to cause such to be done, as mananat. Tattau-aab, or tau-aab. nom. subst is used adverbially as before.
ori-def.2311: zinummauka, tatummauka, tauka, taukan, zinauka, inotaukan, to do anything over again. Patauka, pinatauka, papatauka, ipatauka, inipatauka, inoipatauka, to cause such to be done. Tummaukauka, zi. ta. to increase Tummauka. Pataukauka, &c. as patauka.
ori-def.2312: same as tummauka. Pataula, same as patauka. Gummalich, idem. nom gagallich: pagallich, idem, mon. gagallich.
ori-def.2313: zinummaulaula, tatummaulaula, taulaula, zinaulaula, inotaulaulan, to do anything very often; same as Tummaukauka. Pataulaula, pi. pa. &c. as Pataukauka,  to cause anything to be done frequently. Gummalle_allich, idem. Pagallegallich, id.
ori-def.2314: zinummaumasa, tatummaumasa, taumasa, taumasanni and taumasayan, zinaumasanni and zinaumasayan, same as Matinnaam. Pataumasa, pi, pa, ipataumasa, inipûtaumasa, inoipataumasa, same as patinnaam.
ori-def.2315: zinummauraya, tatummauraya, tauraya, taurayan, zinaurayan, inotaurayan, to put into a fright. Patauraya, pi, pa, ipûtaûraya, inipatauraya, inoipatauraya, to cause to be afraid.
ori-def.2316: tsinumme, tatumme, tea, teen, tene, inoteen, to angle. Pûte, pinate, papate, ipatea, ipate, inipate, inoipate, to cause thus to fish. Tatte, nom.
ori-def.2317: tsinûmmea, tatummea, te-a, te-ûan, tene-a, inote-aûn, to punish. Pûtea, pinatea, papûtea, ipûte-û, inipate-a, inoipatea, to cause such to be done. Tattea, nomen, that wherewith people punish, or the punishment itself.
ori-def.2318: tsi. tat. tsänna, tsean, tsinean, inoteän, same as tûmmaiba. Patsan, trans. Tean, nom.
ori-def.2319: tsinummear, tatummear, ettear, inetear, inoetear, to draw forth, to drag along. Pûtear, pinatear, papatear, ipatearra, ipatearen, inipatear, inoipatear, to cause to be dragged. Tattear, nom. a drawing forth; this word is also applied to the poles of a cart, between which an ox is fastened, in order to draw it.
ori-def.2320: tsinummear, tatummear, tearra, tearren, tsinear, inotearren, to support, to prop up. Patear, pinatear, papatear, ipatearra, ipatear, inipatear, inoipatear, to cause such to be done. Tattear, a prop.
ori-def.2321: zinummeer, tatummeer, tera, terin, zineer, or tineer, inoterin, to avoid, to shun either a stab, or a blow. Pateer, pinateer, papateer, ipatera, ipateer, inipateer, inoteer, to cause to avoid.
ori-def.2322: zinummenon, tatummenon, tinnona, tinnonnen, zininnon, inotonnonnen, also tinnonnan, zininnonnan, inotinnonnan, to weave. Patinnon, pi, pa, ipatinnonna, ipatinnon, inipatinnon, inoipatinnon, to cause to weave.
ori-def.2323: zinummepar, tatummepar, teparra, teparran, zineparran, inoteparran, to lean on anything with the hand or arm. Patepar, pinatepar, pa. ipateparra, ipatepar, inipatepar, inoipatepar, to cause to lean.
