ori-def.2324: zinummerap, tatummerap, terappa, terappen, zinerap, inoterappen, to lick. Paterap, pinaterap, papaterap, inoipaterap, to cause to lick.
ori-def.2325: zinummilla, tatummilla, itilla-a, initilla, inoitilla, to set in, to print in, to stick in, as people pierce a deer with a spear; or to imprint, as people press a seal on wax; while the impression is expressed by the pass. pret. of the verb initilla, that is, that which is impressed. It means also to cook food for children. Pûtilla, pinatilla, papûtilla, ipatilla, inipatilla, inoipatilla, to canse an impression to be made.
ori-def.2326: zinummillak, tatûmmillak, tillaggen, zinillag, inotillaggen, to appear, to seem. Patillak, pinatillak, papûtillak, ipatillagga, ipatillak, inoipatillak, to cause to appear.
ori-def.2327: zinummillik, tatûmmillik, tillikka, tillikken, zinillik, inotillikken, to be struck with blindness in one eye, so that the white of the eye cannot be seen, for then it is tollassen, from tummollas. Patillik, pinatillik, papatillik, ipatillikka, ipatillik, inipatillik, inoipatillik, to cause such to be done. Tûtillik, such a blinding.
ori-def.2328: to level the ground for the foundation of a house, and to beat it hard with flat pieces of wood.
ori-def.2329: zinummittil, tatummittil, tittilla, tittillan, zinittillan, inotittillan, to beat in. Patiltil, pi. pa, ipatiltilla, ipatiltil, &c. to cause such to be done. Tattiltil, a nail or peg which people drive in, also the driving in itself.
ori-def.2330: tsi: tat: tirtirra, to tremble, Patirtir, transit: tattirtir, nom. a trembling.
ori-def.2331: zinummis, tatûmmis, itissa, itis, initis, inoitis, to throw away, to lose. Patis, pinatis, papatis, ipûtissa, ipatis, inipatis, inoipatis, to cause to be thrown away. Maatûttis, one who throws away.
ori-def.2332: zinûmmissan, tatûmmissan, tissanna, to sigh. Patissan, pinatissan, papatissan, ipatissanna, ipatissan, inipatissan, inoipatissan, to cause to sigh. Tatissan, a sigh. Maatattissan, one who sighs.
ori-def.2333: zinummo-ach, tatûmmo-ach, toacha, toûch-en, zino-ach-an, inotoach-an, to come out, to come to light. Thus the sun and moon are said tûmmo-ach, to rise; grass and vegetables, tûmmo-achibabota, to come above the ground; and men, tûmmoach ta, to come out into the street. Pûtoach, pinatoach, papûtoach, ipatoacha, ipatoach, inipatoach, inoipatoach, to cause such to be done. Tattoach, a rising, a coming up.
ori-def.2334: zinummo, tatummo, toa, toon, zino, inotoon, to reach out the hand to receive anything. Pato, pinato, papato, ipato, inipato, inoipato, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2335: zinum-o, tatum-o, to-a, toûn, zino, inotoan, to pick, to stick. Tumo chirrap, to pick the teeth. Tûm-otaddarries, to put the key in a lock, to lock it up, the locking up itself. Also to gore, as a deer with his horns.
ori-def.2336: zinummoch, tatummoch, toch-a, tochen, zinoch, inotoch-en, to number. Tummoch o bido, to read. Patoch, pinatoch, papatoch, ipatoch-a, ipatoch, inipatoch, inoipatoch, to cause to be numbered.
ori-def.2337: zinummochab_, tatummochab, tochûbba, tochbàban, zinochabban, inotochabban, to make a hole. Pûtochab_, pinatochab_, papatochab, ipûtochabb_a, ipatochab_, inipatochab_, inoipatochab, to cause such to be done. Tattochab, the making a hole; tochab, a hole.
ori-def.2338: zinummod, tatummod, todda; (this passive is used respecting a field. Bonna todden, the field is planted. But itod, initod, inoitod, means the rice &c is sown;) todden, zinod, inotodden, cover the seed with earth when it is sown. Patod, pi, pa, ipûtodda, ipatod, &c. Tatod, the covering of that which is sown after the sowing. Taddodayan, the sowing time or place.
ori-def.2339: zinummoelakkies, tatummoelakkies, toelakisa, toelakisen, zinoelakies, inotoelakkisen, to do anything unexpectedly; same as Poelakies. Tummoelakkies o poch o cho, to shoot a man suddenly. Tûmmoelakkies, o payach, o riba, to soil a coat unexpectedly. Patoelakkies, pi, pa, ipatoelakisa, ipatoelakies, inipatoelakies, inoipatoelakies, to cause such to be done. Tattoelakies, a mistake, a missing. Hence, kar tattoelakkies, mau tattoelakkies. Mà-atattoelakkies, one who misses.
ori-def.2340: zinummok, tatummok, tokka, tokken, sinok, inotokken, to overthrow. Tummok o mallo, to upset a cup. Tummok o bato, to knock against a stone, to stumble. Tummok, o don, to knock at a house, or a door. Tummok o tazirrisan, to hit a nail or pin, in order to drive it in. Patok, pi, pa, ipatokka, ipatok, inipatok, inoipatok, to cause such to be done. Tattok, a knocking, also that wherewith we knoch. Tattok a oos, quasitattokaûs, the beat of a drum. Tattoksayan, the place where people beat, also the time when the gong is beaten.
ori-def.2341: tsi, ta tokkóa, tokkoûn, pass. &c. to heat up, to lay in a heap. Patokko, to cause such to done. Tokko, a heap.
ori-def.2342: zinum: tatum: tókkotokka, tokkotokken, zinokkotok, inotokkotokken, the redoubling of tummok. Patokkotok, pi, pa, ipûtokkotokka, ipatokkotok, &c. the redoubling of patok.
ori-def.2343: tsinûmmolillis, tatummolillis, (imp. tollalisa,part. tollolissen, tsinullllolis, inottollolissen, nom. tollalis, a spark, a bit of fire,) to give out sparks, as red hot iron does when it is beaten. Patollilis, pi, pa, ipatolollossa., ipûtolillis, inipatolillis, inoipatolillis, to cause to give out sparks.
ori-def.2344: tsi: tat: tullalla-a, tûllallaan, tsinullalla-an, the blossoming of trees: inotullalallû-an. Patullalla, transitiv. Tallalla, nom. blossom.
ori-def.2345: tsi, tat, tollassa, tollassen, tsinollûs, inotollassen, to be blind of one eye, but so as that the white can be seen. Patollas, trans. Tattollas, such blindness.
ori-def.2346: zinummollo, tatummollo, tollóa, tolloan, zinolloan, inotolloan, to set on fire. Tummollo, tatollo, to light a candle. Patóllo, pinatollo, papûtollo, ipatolloa, ipatollo, inipatollo, inoipatollo, to cause to be lighted; nom. tattollo, a candle.
ori-def.2347: zinummoltol, tatûmmoltol, toltolla, toltollan, zinoltollan, inotoltollan, to smoke with a whisp of straw, called tattoltol, in order to drive away the moschettoes. Patoltol, pinûtoltol, papûtoltol, ipatoltolla, ipatoltol, inipatoltol, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2348: tsi: tat: tonnoga, tomnogan, tsinonog, innotonnogan, the first rising of the water in the sea or rivers, Tmmonok sai o to, de abas, desabba. Tattonnog, nom. the commencement of flood tide.
ori-def.2349: zinummoob, tattûmmoob, itòbo, itoob, initoob, inoitoob, to sprinkle water, also to sprinkle with the same, when it is toba, tóban, zinoban, inotoban. Patoob, pinatoob, papûtoob, ipûtoba, ipatoob, inipatoob, inoipatoob, to cause to be sprinkled.
ori-def.2350: zinummo-ol, tatûmmo-ol, toolla, to-ollan, zino-ollan, inoto-ollon, same as tummollo. Pato-ol, pi, pa, ipato-olla, ipato-ol, &c. same as Patollo.
ori-def.2351: ziniummoos, tattummoos, tosa, tosan, zinosan, inotósan, where with? itoos, initoos, inoitoos, to rub. Patoos, pinatoos, papatoos, ipûtosa, ipatoos, intipatoos, inoipatoos, to cause to be rubbed. Tûmmóostoos, intend.
ori-def.2352: zinummorraich, tattummorraich, torraicha, torraichen, zinorraich, inotorraichen, to slide, or slip of, to slide out. Pûtorraich, pi, pa, ipatorraicha, ipatorraich, inipatorraich, inoipatorraich, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2353: zinummorrik, tatummorrik, torrika, torriken, zinorrik, inotorriken, to tell lies. Pûtorrik, pinatorrik, papatorrik, ipatorrikka, ipatorrik, inipatorrik, inoipatorrik, to cause to lie.
ori-def.2354: tsi: tat: torritorria, torritorrian, tsinotorritorri, inotorritorrian, to flicker, to glitter as the fire flies in the dark, also as the stars in the night. Tummaitas, idem. Pataitas, idem. Patorritorri, trans. Torritorri, nom. a glittering, also a fire fly. Taitai, idem.
ori-def.2355: zinummorritorrik, tatummerritorrik, torritorrikka, torritorrikken, zinorritorrik, inotorritorrikken, idem. Patorritorrik, an increase of tûmmorrik.
ori-def.2356: zinummorro, tatummorro, torroan, zinorroan, inotorroan, to leak, to leak out, either through roofs or through broken vessels and so forth. Patorro, pinatorro, papatorro, ipatorroa, ipatorro, inipatorro, inoipatorro, &c. Tummorrotorro, intend.
ori-def.2357: tsi: tat: torrocha, torrochen, tsinorroch, inotorrochen, to drag, to pull after one, neutr. Patorroch, trans. to draw, activ. to cause to be drawn. Tattorroch, nom. a dragging. Tummorrotorroch, intend.
ori-def.2358: zinummorrod, tatummorrod, torroda, torrodan, zinorrodan, inotorrodan, to look downwards, to look in a glass. Pûtorrod, pi, pa, ipatorrodda, ipûtorrod, inipûtorrod, inoipatorrod, to cause such to be done. Tummorrotorrod, intend.
ori-def.2359:
zinummose, tatummose, toséa, tosein, zinose, inotosein, same as tummorrik; patose, pinatose, papatose, ipatosea, ipûtose, inipatose, inoipatose, same as patorrik. Tummosetose and
patosetose, same as tummorritorrik and patorritorrik.
ori-def.2360: tsi: tat: toshieka, pass. to shiekan, &c. to spatter, to bedaub. Patoshiek, trans. Tattoshiek, nom.
ori-def.2361: zinummosik, tatummosik, tosikka, tosikken, zinòsik, inotosikken, same as tummorrik. Patossik, same as patorrik. Tummositosik, and patositosik, same as tummorritorrik and patorritorrik.
ori-def.2362: tsi: tat: tôtta, to let wind. Patot, to cause such to done. Tottat, foul wind.
ori-def.2363: zinummotto, tatummotto, tottoa, tottoon zinótto, inotottoon, to forge, to beat any thing to powder. Patotto, pinatotto, papatotto, ipaitottoa, ipatotto, inipatotto, inoipatotto, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2364: tsi: tat: tottoa, tottoòn, tsinotto, inotottoon, the budding, or shooting forth of the fruit after the blossoms fall off.
ori-def.2365: zinumpa, tatumpa, tuppa, tuppûan, zienpa, inotuppaan, to think, to reflect. Patuppa, pi, pa, ipatuppa, inipatuppa, inoipatuppa, to cause to to think. Tumpatuppa, intend. Tattuppa, thoughts. Maatattuppa, one who thinks.
ori-def.2366: zinumpas, tattumpas, tuppasa, tuppasen, zienpas, inotuppasin, to tread with the foot on one side. Patuppas, pinatuppas, papatuppas, ipatuppasa, ipatuppas, inipatuppas, inoipatuppas, to cause such to be done. Tattuppus, nom. Tumpatuppas, indicative tumpas.
ori-def.2367: zinumpies, tatumpies, tuppisa, tuppisen, zinupies, inotuppisen, same as tummagga. Patuppies, pi, pa, ipûtuppisa, ipatuppies, same as pataga.
ori-def.2368: zinumpoch, tattumpoch, ituppocha, ituppoch, inituppoch, inoituppoch, to fix in the ear rings: where to? tuppocha, tuppochan, zienpochan, inotuppochan. Patuppoch, pi, pa, ipatuppocha, ipatuppoch, inipatuppoch, inoipatuppoch, to cause such to be done. Tattuppock, ear-rings.
ori-def.2369: tsi, ta, tupporra, tupporren, tsienpor, inotupporren, the hatching of birds. Pûtûppor, transiti. tatuppor, nom. a hatching.
ori-def.2370: zinumpuk, tattumpuk, tuppukka, tuppukken, zienpuk, inotuppuken, to count, to reckon up any thing in the mind. Patuppuk, pinatuppuk, pa. ipatuppukka, ipatuppuk, &c.
ori-def.2371: zinumrach, tattumrach, tirracha, tirrachen, zinirrach, inotirrachen, the bursting of water through a dam. The escaping of a fish through a hole or rent in the net. The running out of paddy or such like article through a sack: the place where it leaks is tirrachan, zinirrachan, ino. &c. Patirrach, pi, pa, ipatirracha. &c.
ori-def.2372: tsinumsar, tattumsar, tsarren, tsiensar, inotsarren, to shine, to illumine. Pasar, pinazar, papazar, ipûzarra, ipazar, inipazar, inoipazar, to cause to shine. Tatsar, nom. appearance.
ori-def.2373: tsi: ta: tsarra, to stick, to stab. Tumsar o binnan, to stab a deer with a spear.
ori-def.2374: tsi: tat: tsika, tsiken, tsinick, inotsiken, to stain, to spot. Patsik, transit. Tatsik, a spot.
ori-def.2375: zinumtum, tattumtum, tumtumma, tumtummen, zinumtam, inotumtummen, to fast, to deny the stomach its food. Patumtum, pinatumtum, papatumtum, ipatumtumma, ipatumtum, inipatumtum, inoipatumtnm, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2376: tsinumso, tatumso, tsoa, tsoan, tsiensoan, inotsoan, to assent by a nod. Patso, pinatso, papatso, ipatsoa, ipatso, inipatso, inoipatso, to cause such to be done. Tatso, a nod.
ori-def.2377: between: tuppach o don, between the houses: tuppach o ranna, amongst the hills. The verb neuter is matuppach, to be between two, and the active, Patuppach, from the root tuppach.
ori-def.2378: the stalk wherewith the fruit is fastened to the tree or plant.
ori-def.2379: a troop of men or beasts, a generation, a principal reason.
ori-def.2380: the hair on the skin of men or beasts, excepting the hair of the head, beard, or eye-brows. it is written dûppoch.
ori-def.2381: sugar. Tuppoos o bato, sugar candy.
ori-def.2382: a fire-fly same as Taitai. The verb Maturriturri. Mataitai.
ori-def.2383: inummachol, aummachol, achòlla, achollen, inachol, inoachòllan, to lay any thing out of the way. Pûachol, pinûachol, papûachol, ipûacholla, ipûachol, inipaachol, inoipaachol, to cause to be laid aside.
ori-def.2384: inûmmadach, aûmmadach, adacha, adachen, inadachan, inoadachan,: what? iadach, iniadach, inoiadach, to hang up. Ummadach o tairien, to hang up beads; ummaadach o ballasau, to hang up a sword. Paadach, pinaadach, papaadach, ipaadach, inipaadach, inoipaadach, to do so to another, to cause to be done.
ori-def.2385: inummadok, aummadok, adokka, adokken, inadok, inoadokken, to pick and choose. Elli ohinûmmar o baûsje tapos ja assaban: inummadokchono kinummossi: the Dutch have not burnt down the whole village : they have picked out the disobedient. Paadok, pi, pa, ipûadokka, ipaadok. &c. to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2386: inummado, aummado, addoa, addoan, inaddoan, inoaddoan, to dissuade. Paadde, pinaaddo, pa. ipaaddoa, ipaaddo, inipaaddo, inoipaaddo, to cause to dissuade. Ummoossó, idem.
ori-def.2387: inummalappo, aummalappo, alappoa, alappoon, inalappo, inoalappoon, from which are derived alappoan, inalappoan, inoalappoon, to heave up, to lift up. Paalappo, pinaalappo, papaalappo, ipaalappoa, ipaalappo, inipaalappo, inoipaalappo, to cause to lift up.
ori-def.2388: inum: aum: aoa, aoon, inao, inoaoon, the melting of salt: trans. pa-ao, melted salt, brine: ao-no-soa, brine for washing wounds.
ori-def.2389: inummapar, aummapar, aparra, aparren, inapar, inoaparren (that out of which it is taken) aparran, inaparran, inoaparran, to take any thing out with the hand or fingers pinched close together. Ummapar o inochan, inai mallo: to take, food out of a dish. Ummapar o dassono, innai roboen, to take rice out of a bag. Ummapar o boono innai kallaman, to take out of a large pot, &c. Paapar, pi, pa, ipaaparra, ipaapar, inipaapar, inoipaapar, to cause such to be doue.
ori-def.2390: inummapach, aummapach, apacha, apachan, inapachan, inoapachan, to climb, to climb up. Paapach, pinaapach, papaapach, ipaapacha, ipaapach, inipaapach, inoipaapach, to cause to climb.
ori-def.2391: inummarras, aummarras, arrassa, arrasan, inarrasan, inoarrassan, to stride, to step over, to pass by. Paarras, pinaarras, papaarras, ipaarasa, ipaarras, inipaaras, inoipaarras, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2392: inummaron, aummaron, aronna, aronnen, inaron, inoaronnen, to roll up. Paaron, pinaaron, papaaron, ipaaronna, ipaaron, inipaaron, inoipaaron, to cause to roll up. NB. The r is sometimes doubled.
ori-def.2393: inummatat, aummatat, atatta, atatten, inatat, inoatatten, to chew. Paatat, pinaatat, papaatat, ipaatatta, inipaatat, inoipaat, to cause to chew.
ori-def.2394: inummillag, aummillag, illagga, illaggen, inillag, inoillaggen, to unfold, to open out. Ummelag o naupoot, o bido, to unfold a cloth or a book. Paillag, pinaillag, papaillag, ipaelagga, ipaelag, inipaelag, inoipaelag, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2395: inummelis, aumelis, olissa, olissoan, inolissan, ino-olissan, to take off the lid, or cover. Ummelis o babchab, to open the lid of a pot. Paolis, pinaolis, paaolis, ipaolissa, ipaolis, inipaolis, inoipaolis, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2396: inummenig, aummenig, enigga, eniggan, inoeniggan, inoeniggan, to speak gently, as one ashamed or abashed. Paenig, pinaenig, papaenig, ipaenigga, ipaenig, inipaenig, inoipaenig, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2397: inum: aum: illoiloa, illoilan, inilloilo, inoilloiloon, to continue to desire any thing long and earnestly. Pailloilo, nom. illoilo.
ori-def.2398: inummillc, aummillo, illoa, illoan, inilloan. inoilloan, the winding up of a child in swaddling clothes; also to speak behind one's back, either good or ill. Paillo, pinaillo, papaillo, ipailloa, ipaillo, inipaillo, inoipaillo, to cause such to be done,
ori-def.2399: inummerap, aummerap, erappa, erappan, inerap, inoerappan, same as Tummerap, to lick. Paerap, pi. pa. ipaerappa, ipaerap, inipaerap, inoipaerap, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2400: inummichich, aummichich, ichicha, ichichen, inichich, inoichich, to gnaw. Paichich, pinaichich, papaichich, paichicha, ipaichich, inipaichich, inoipaichich, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2401: inumietiet, aumietiet, ietita, ietiten, inietiet, inoietiten, to bite off the ends, as of thread, &c. Paietiet, pinaietiet, papaietiet, ipaietita, ipaietiet, inipaietiet, inoipaietiet, to cause such to be done.

ori-def.2407: to weed, to root weeds out of a field. Pao-o, transiti.

ori-def.2411: to halt, to limp, inummatul, aummotul, otulla, otullen, inotul, inootullen. Paotul, transit.

ori-def.2414: the south. Mat a wannan, mi, ma, southward. Patawannan trans.
ori-def.2418: the half or side of any thing; hence people say, zhabûan-anig and ûllûmas, the left and right side. An opposite party, written shabaan, verb. Mashabaan, pashabaan. It is also used as a preposition, against.
ori-def.2422: small worms generated in food; written tsiga.
ori-def.2424: a spot or stam. From tsimilak.
ori-def.2425: a silkworm; silk, either woven or raw.
ori-def.2427: zinimianna, tazimianna, zianna, ziannanni, ziniannanni, inoziannanni, to be suspicious, to do any thing from mistrust. Pazianna, pinazianna, papazianna, ipazianna, inipazianna, inoipazianna, to cause such to be done. Written tsimianna, see in T.
ori-def.2428: zinimichallo, tazimichallo, zichalloa, zichalloon, zinichûllo, inozichalloon, to skin off the clear portion from the top, so that the dregs underneath be not disturbed. Pûzichallo, pi, pa, ipazichûlloa, ipazichallo, inipazichallo, inoipazichallo, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2429: zinimichier, tazimichier, zichirra, zichirran, zinichirran, inozichirran, to resemble, to imitate. Pazichier, pi, pa, ipazichirra, ipazichier, inipazichier, inoipazichier, to make any thing like. Written tsinichier, see in T. Pataitach, idem; tatschier, nom. likeness.
ori-def.2430: zinimichzich, tazimichaich, zichzicha, zichzichen, zinichzich, inozichzichen, to smooth any thing that is folded or rumpled. Pazichzich, pi, pa, ipazichzicha, ipazichzich, inipazichzich, inoipazichzich, to cause to be smoothed.
ori-def.2431: zinimido, tazimido, zidoa, zidoan, zinidoan, inozidoan, the sucking of infants. Pazdido, pinazdido, papazdido, ipazdidoa, ipazdido, inipazdido, inoipazdido, to give suck. Tummis o zinido, to wean : shiem initis o zinidó, a weaned child.
ori-def.2432: zinimiek, tazimiek, izika, iziek, iniziek, inoiziek, to fillip, to give a fillip: to dip as meat in the sauce. Paziek, pinaziek, papaziek, ipazika, ipaziek, inipaziek, inoipaziek, to cause such to be done. Written tsinyk, nom. tatsyk, see in T.
ori-def.2433: zinimiesto, inozimiesto, ziestoa, ziestoan, ziniesto, inoziestoan, same tumpa. Paziesto, pi, pa, same pûtûppa.

ori-def.2435: zinimikak, tazimikak, zikakka, zikakkan, zinikak, inozikakkan, to open; as zikak o ranied, &c. Pazikak, pi, pa, ipazikakka, ipazikak, inipazikak, inoipazikak, to cause to be opened. Said of the mouth and ear. Written tsimikak, see in T.
ori-def.2436: zinimilak, tazimilak, zilûkka, zilakkan, and zinilakkan, inozilakkan, to befoul. Pazilak, pinazilak, papazilak, ipazilakka, ipazilak, inipazilak, inoipazilak, to cause such to be done. Written tsimilak, see in T. Nomen Zilab, under tsilak.

ori-def.2438: zinimioch, tazimioch, ziocha, ziochen, zinioch, inoziochen, to couple. Pazioch, pinazioch, papazioch, ipaziocha, ipazioch, inipazioch, inoipazioch, to cause such to be done.
ori-def.2439: zinimipies, tazimipies, zipisa, zipisen, zinipies, inozipisen, to cut. Pazipies, pi, pa, ipazipisa, ipazipies, inipazipies, inoipazipisen, to cause to cut. Written tsimipies, see in T.
ori-def.2440: zinimipó-o, zipo-oa, zipóan, zinipòan, inozipòan, to fall on one's knees. Pazipo-o, pinazipo-o, papûzipo-o, ipaeipo-oa, ipazipo o, inipazipo-o, inoipûzpo-o, to cause such to be done. Written tsimipo-o.

ori-def.2443: zinimiries, tazimiries, zirisa, iziries, iniziries, inoiziries, whereto ? zirisan, zinirisan, inozirisan, to hang any thing up. ori-def.2751: well, as it ought to be. Mab o chaggi, to know well

ori-def.2819: a tineture, any thing drawn out

ori-def.2917: the handle of a bill hook
